text: Food was just ok.  Service was kind but confused.  They kept taking my fork after clearing each course,  but never replaced it when food came back. So strange.   They need to figure our if they are a relaxed neighborhood spot or more fine dining. Salads were the best thing we ordered.  Garlic bread tastes like it has garlic powder sprinkled on it, calimari is ok.  Pasta was cooked perfectly al dente, but sauces were a miss. Eggplant parmesan was one huge under seasoned, under done slab of eggplant. Puttenesca was so watery. Tasted like it was just a jar of olives, brine and all. Too one dimensional. The Fra diavolo sauce was too spicey but also just not good.  I wish they wild give you an option of pastas when ordering. I wish I had gotten spaghetti instead of penne. Ambiance was nice, but I think food needs improvement. And that's coming from an East coast Italian American.  My daughter's spaghetti and meatballs from the kids menu was better than any of our entrees.

name: Bridget Galati
text:
I was really excited for Red Sauce to open and wanted to love it, but it was a bit disappointing for us. I'll sort this out into +/-
+the good
1)Pasta dishes were well prepared and very tasty
2) Ambiance was unstuffy and inviting
3)Service was attentive

- the not so good
1)Serving sizes were small for us. This has been billed as a big portions/take leftovers home kinda place and it was not that for us at all. My spaghetti and meatballs were tasty but they were also $16 and I left hungry. My husband left so hungry he had to grab food on the way home. Maybe we're just bigger eaters, but we've never had to do that before after a pasta dinner. This was by far the biggest negative for us.
2)Garlic bread was meh and still cold in the middle. Some plain, tasty bread for the table would go a long way here.
3)No kids menu. We thought we'd be ok sharing our plates with our carb-loving toddler (anticipating big portions) but were instead doling out bites to her from our not so generous pasta portions. My meatballs were very tasty and dialed in for the adult pallette but pepper flakes made them a no go for the 2 year old. Kids menu would help this, especially for a restaurant geared to kids and families.

In short, if you're a lighter eater and/or not trying to take kids to dinner here, it could still be a good spot for you. If Red Sauce increases portion sizes and makes it easier to bring kids here, we would love to come back.

name: Robert Fox
text:
My search of Denver for great barbecue continues. I'm starting to feel like Diogenes, stalking the streets of Athens with his lamp (I can't remember, was he also looking for barbecue?). Alas, SmokeHouse17 fails to be the place that satisfies my desires.

The space is small, but very attractive in a rustic way, with a nice bar, counter ordering, a reasonable amount of inside seating, and a patio with several picnic tables. The main focus of the bar is barrel-aged and specialty cocktails. The wine and beer selection is very limited. The menu features locally-sourced, all natural meats.

I tried the Wagyu brisket, the pulled pork, and the pork ribs with sides of green chili mac & cheese, bourbon baked beans, and cole slaw. I also tried both sauces. The brisket was very tender, but tasteless. The pulled pork was tender and reasonably juicy, but also had very little flavor. The ribs were tender, but dry and tasteless. I could not detect a smoke ring on any of the meats.

The mac & cheese was the highlight of the meal; very cheesy and well-seasoned. The cole slaw was also seasoned properly. The beans were terrible: tasteless, tough, and watery. I finished with the banana pudding. It was OK, although a bit gummy in spots.

The staff was pleasant and helpful and the food came out fairly quickly. The sauces were good, but barbecue should stand on its own. I had to drown the meats in sauce to get any flavor out of them. I never do this. I was also annoyed when I got home to find that the containers of sauce were not even half full and that the cold items had been intermingled with the hot dishes. An overall disappointment.

Luis-
I appreciate your patronage and always try to engage a guest when someone gives a midrange review. We continuously strive for improvement in areas we may have missed and whatever needs were not met. Leaving a three star review without any critiques on service, ambience, food or music leaves us in the dark. If there's something specific that warranted this review, we'd love to hear your perspective. It's the only way we'll get better. Thanks.
Thanks Terry!!!

Is there anything we missed or could have done better? I'd appreciate a bit more detailed critique so we can work on improving the areas we might neglect. Now more than ever, critical reviews impact businesses significantly and without information on your perceived less than stellar experience, we are flying blind.

name: Cody Li
text: I brought my date here last night and we liked the cozy dining room. Normally, we order delivery but the dining room was small but  clean and nicely decorated.They don't have alcohol at all so we got free hot green tea instead.  The waitress was really nice and helpful in answering our questions about the menu. We decided to split the Drunken shrimp rice noodles and Chicken with Asparagus ( gluten free)  over brown rice. It was really good and the portions are big.  This little restaurant has been a neighborhood favorite for over 10 years and I can see why. They do have some of the best Chinese and Asian food in Denver. Parking was easy and free! That is rare in Denver. We tried the Forest Berry Torte for dessert and it was delicious. Food is great and service is good... I would recommend Wok Uptown to anybody!

name: Michael Bucari
text: Great food. Really, some of the best Chinese I've ever had. Seriously, I didn't think it was possible to make flank steak as tender as these guys do. That said, service is lacking. Nearly every time I call, I'm greeted with "Thank you for calling Wok Uptown Chinese, please hold". I understand being busy, but the guy is always very curt. Also, I've been forgotten about and left on hold on several occasions.  Then there's the delivery. These guys will NEVER deliver to the apartment unit.  I've tried coaxing them to the door on numerous occasions, but they'll either say, "we're not allowed to enter secured buildings", or claim they that the front door is locked.  I do not live in a secure building. Anyone can walk through the door that they're standing in front of at any time. It NEVER locks. I know, because I test it every time I get delivery.  Maybe there's some other company policy they're not telling me about, but it's quite irritating especially since every other company I order from delivers to my door.

name: Virginia J
text: Our office orders lunch delivery from here all the time and it's always wonderful. The veggies are fresh and plentiful, the price is great on the lunch specials (but gotta admit, I probably wouldn't pay dinner prices). Delivery driver & the guy who answers the phone have always been friendly. It's one of my go-to lunch spots.

name: Gage Chapel
text: Good food, reasonably priced.  I go there for lunch and order take out.  Solid food and service.

name: J Rapp
text: Great food and nice people there. There are a bunch of trashy A holes giving them one star but this place is great!

text: The food is always hot, fresh and delicious. Best lemon chicken I've had.

name: Eric Woolcott
text: Ordered 2 dishes. In the order we said specifically "no onions on anything, allergy". Well when we received our food the dish that is specifically listed 'with onions' didn't have any. That's great. Then we see that the other dish, which shouldn't have any to begin with, has onions. It's almost like they took them out of one dish and added them to the other! OK, mistakes happen but when we politely called back to let them know of the mistake, they called us liars. IMMEDIATLY! They said " That dish (referring to the second one) doesn't even come with onions, you just want free food!" Trust me, I can afford the food.  They immediately accused us of lying even though we were polite... at first. They turned it up to ten as if we were trying to rip them off. They need to take their meds. Never ordering from them again and I would find a better place to eat if I were you.

name: A Hov
text: This place is a waste of money... food was not good, soggy meat, dollar scoop has better cuisine.. if that's saying anything.  They were rude over the phone, and weren't helpful when asked for opinion on dish.  Don't recommend eating here, unless you want to waste your money.

I had the BBQ Pork, greens, Mac & Cheese, jalapeno cornbread and southern sweet tea, and of course I put hot sauce on all of it, and it was amazing!

I raved about it when I got back to work, and when I got home to the roommates. I am looking forward to going back, and trying something else.

name: Melissa Aragon
text: Holy cow! I've been waiting 9 years for a decent Thai place in this area!!! I've tried every pad thai in a 5 mile radius and have been left disappointed every time until now. Thai hot was perfect! It's spicy though. Not hot like atomic wings but it'll make your nose run a little.

name: Devin McIntyre
text: We order from this restaurant regularly. It has good value for the price. It's better than most other Thai restaurants in the area.

text: The food was fresh and come out fast. Finally some good Pad Thai in our part of town.

name: Chris Meier
text: Very friendly staff and the Pad Thai was the best I ever had. Going to try country style pad Thai next time since I heard that one is as authentic as can be and very yummy. Definitely will keep coming back!

text: Authentic Thai food comes to North Denver! Everything on the menu is made from scratch, and you can tell. Very fresh. Highly recommended!

resp.text: Thank you for taking the time to leave your feedback. We value your business.

text: Good food, clean restaurant, and friendly employees. Since moving to Thornton this is the best Thai place we've eaten at. Why is this the only good Thai place Thornton has to offer!?

text: Food taste great! Wish they had dine in.

name: Justin Rybal
text: Have been here 3 times and the food is always been really good, but 2 out of 3 times the order was messed up but the food was good this last time I didn't eat the pad Thai. The first mistake was white rice when I paid for fried. Second was I ordered beef pad Thai and got your combo pad Thai with everything in it wasn't a fan of the taste and didn't eat it. But overall your food is great and I will be back to your establishment but I will pay more attention to what I receive.

resp.text: Thanks for your feedback, Justin.

name: Victor Acuna
text:
Their Pad Thai is good, but my favorite dishes are The Singapore Noodles and the Royal Chicken! So good!!

Picture is of the Chicken Pad Thai

resp.text: Hi Victor. It's so nice to see our customers venture beyond Pad Thai. Which is a great dish but we have so much more yummy options, as you know! Thank you so much for your review! 🎉🎉🎉

name: Christian Dunham
text:
I feel bad for giving most of my reviews 5 stars (or one star).  That said we, as people, tend to only give opinions on very good or very bad experiences.

SO!  This place is very good.  I had never had Thai before this place, I am now a Thai fan.  I got basic white person food the first time (Pad Thai) , it was wonderful.  I’ve also now gotten their pork egg rolls every time I order, they’re hands down the best egg rolls I’ve ever had.

So now that I’ve tried other plates and other Thai places, I feel I can give this a proper 5 stars.  It is EXCELLENT.  Best Thai place I’ve been to thus far.

Give them your business.

resp.text: Thanks Christian! We love the feedback and look forward to serving you again. 😀😀😀

name: Joshua Busnelli
text: Dang. This place is so good and they're so friendly! Ive had two experiences here thus far. First, the Pad Thai on the very spicey level. It was amazing. Second, the curry at medium spicey level. Very good. So happy an authentic Thai restaurant opened so close to home. Will be back regularly!

resp.text: Thanks Joshua! We are so happy to be here in Thornton. 👍

name: James Childs
text: Did take out which is all they are currently providing. Outstanding food, panang curry and jungle curry. Will definitely return.

resp.text: Hi James. Thanks for your review. :) We hope to be opening our dining room to at least partial capacity very soon! We will put the word out via google, facebook, and our website. Stay tuned! 👍👍👍

name: ROBERT aka ACE Munsen
text: Absolutely the Best Thai this side of Denver!👌A Must try! We tried the Springs Rolls, Pad Thai with Chicken, Sesame Chicken and Fried rice all of which had amazing flavors! They were generous enough to provide me with a Delicious Thai tea while I waited due to a system error😁 Can't wait to try more of the menu!! 🤤 Coming back for more!👌

resp.text: Thanks Ace! 🎖

name: Gina Harvey
text: We had a wonderful experience at Country Thai. The service was amazing, the space simple and clean and the food was the best Thai food we've had in a long time. We ordered the fish cakes as an appetizer. They were crispy and flavorful. For our enteee, we shared the mango curry with steamed rice. The flavor was fresh, delicious and well-balanced. We will definitely be back.

resp.text: Thanks Gina! We hope to see you soon. :)

name: WhisperJet America
text: Superb. Friendly, Fresh and Full of Flavor. Tucked away, but next to Chipotle, for a delicious meal that'll stick to your bones, seek and enjoy.

resp.text: Seek and enjoy. Nicely said! Thanks for your review and we hope to see you soon!

name: candan duran
text:
Last Friday, we had a big take-out order.  The veggie rolls were great.  The yellow curry accompanying scallops was also yummy.  The scallops themselves were quite overcooked and full of sand . The panang curry lacked flavor completely. While the brown rice was good, both the steamed and fried rice were mushy and tasteless.  As a matter of fact, the fried rice was a beige blob!  The chicken satay was extremely dry and the peanut sauce was anything but peanut sauce.  Fried tilapia was incredibly dry.  The fired bananas were an utter disappointment.  But the worst was, my favorite, Tom Kha  This Tom Kha soup was extremely watery, with nothing but raw onion slices in it.  The "extra" shrimp (+3 dollars) amounted to 2, yes, 2 shrimps.  We love Thai food and have our favorites all over Denver  We got exited as this restaurant is close byt.
But: Never again from Country Thai.

resp.text: Thanks for your feedback, candan! 😭🔥😬

name: Sabrina Miller
text: Finally an authentic Thai restaurant in Thornton! We ordered pad see eew and drunken noodles and both were delicious and had perfect heat levels. Thank you for cooking the heat into the dish instead of smothering the top of the food with dried chili as we've seen others do. We can't wait to try other dishes. We will definitely be back!

resp.text: We're happy to be here! And so glad you enjoyed our food... 😊❤️❤️

name: Ray Meeks
text: Best Asian food I have had in quite awhile! Everything is delicious and will be back probably weekly for more!

resp.text: Thanks so much for your feedback! We hope to see you again soon. :)

name: Jo Lujan
text: The food is super good but when I pay extra for shrimp, I want more than just 3. It's happened 3 different times

resp.text: Thanks for your glowing review of our food! For added protein we need to keep it pretty tight to manage costs. It's like walking a tightrope! We hope to see you again, Jo. 😀😀😀

name: Joshua Erickson
text: I don't know if it was just a bad night or a new recipe or what, but tonight it was not up to standards. We ordered the beef and broccoli and the Rad Na. They were no where close to the description. Beef was not stir fried, broccoli was OK, and it was delivered in water. Rad Na was a soup of noodles, broccoli and black eyed peas not black beans as described. Since this meal was such a deal breaker ($40) I'm hesitant to return. I could make these meals at home.

resp.text: Thank you for your feedback, Joshua.

name: Frederick G
text: This place is amazing!!! It's seriously my favorite Thai food in Denver.

resp.text: Wow! Thank you so much, Frederick. 😀🎉👍🔥

name: Vaughn Townsend
text: Amazon Thai food .. they have a mango Curry that is to die for .. had country pad thai it's was wonderful.. check this place out you won't be sorry!

resp.text: Thank you!!! 👍

name: Elaine Bonnell
text: First time i ordered was Christmas eve. Placed the order online, paid for it online. Went to pick it up and they were closed. Got my money back a couple days later and figured I try again this evening.  Super disappointing. Portions small. Beef and broccoli watery and tasteless. Fried tofu utterly tasteless. Pad Thai was meh.... I'm used to getting peanuts, bean sprouts, cilantro and lime. None of that was included. This was pricey for what it was. Can't say I'll make the same mistake again.

resp.text: Thank you for your feedback, Elaine.

name: Bartek Suchocki
text: Red curry recommended

resp.text: An excellent choice, Bartek! 👍❤️🏅
Thank you for leaving your feedback.

name: Jared Lasko
text: A great little hidden gem. It's tucked away In a "run down" little strip mall but once found you'll love it. Great selection about about 10-12 craft beers on tap from breweries around the US that swap out. Food is absolutely delicious as well! Great spot for a date!

name: Adam Wilkie
text: Always consistent good food. Good service. This provides an overall wonderful dinner spot. One of my favorites.

name: Cyn Cynthia
text: Actually shareable small plates!! And great taste. Not bad price for ecletic either. We share some plates and satisfying. Chill atmosphere

name: chris coughlan
text: Great place for food and drink. Good wine and beer choices. Fun speciality cocktails. Variety of small plates to share and a few entrees.

name: Beth Ellsworth
text: Exquisite. Cozy neighborhood spot with lively energy, top notch service and perfectly executed small plates (and high quality entrées). Very thoughtful wine offerings and full bar. We love the mussels, seared ahi, many creative veg plates and the lemon tart with cherries. Divine!

name: Jim Chesebro
text: Pretty good food and drinks. We'll be back. Loved it the first time...liked it the second...hopefully not a downward trend that continues.

name: Ryan Hoskins
text: Food, drinks, and service are on point. Chef does a great job of keeping the menu fresh and relevant but not pretentious. Get the 'Nduja or the cheeseburger. The chevre tart or the wings. You won't be disappointed. The craft beer selection is diverse and the cocktails are excellent.

name: Jon Roberts
text: Great atmosphere, amazing staff, but expensive.

name: Amy Schmuck
text: Scrumptious food, great staff!

name: Trent Baker
text: Wonderfully unique experience in food.

name: Andrew Goetz
text: Great food great place

name: BA R
text: I am so glad I found this place! No frills, very authentic and extremely kind staff. The food is delicious and reminds me of my trip to Thailand. I've been here 3 times and LOVED every single thing I ordered!! I will continue to return here.

name: Fred Peter
text: This place is incredible. The quality of ingredients and the speed and friendliness of service seems too good to be true. Shockingly above nearby offerings. Pad thai is excellent, not too sweet, chicken is fresh and properly prepared. Samosas are simple and great. Egg rolls, again, have vegetables fresher than you expect from the price point. You should go to this place.

name: Eric Hubler
text: I've been in four or five times now and this has definitely become one of my go-tos. There must be some kind of gift-giving tradition at play because they always give me something I haven't ordered, like a drink or dessert or appetizer. Bonus points: I loved watching the Burmese edition of The Voice while waiting for my order!

name: James Lee Baker
text: The staff is always so friendly. The tea leaf and papaya salads are exceptionally delicious, even when compared to top Thai restaurants in town.

name: Dugan Ewelt-McAuliffe
text:
The restaurant itself is immaculately clean and feels like a nice place to enjoy a meal. The service was fantastic, it felt very personal and helpful. When I entered to order to go, I was immediately giving water and a table to sit while my food was prepared.

The food is fantastic, it is simple, clean and very flavourful. The menu is simple and well organized, however choices of meat is not listed. There is a good mix of Americanized with local, and it is clear that that the food leans toward local.

This is a worth wile place to check out.

name: Brian Flores
text: Very friendly people the food is great but a bit too spicy sometimes so you got to tell them less spice.

name: David XXX
text: Whenever I go into a so called Thai restaurant, I always engage in the Papaya Salad bc a sorry one or Americanized Thai restaurant will not serve that or wont know how to make it. When you see the seafood Papaya Salad on the menu, that is a good sign. The Larb Salad and then the specific Thai and Burmese dishes gives this restaurant away that it's not just any restaurant giving itself the Thai food name for uniqueness.

name: Poppy Seed
text: This restaurant is unlike any other, delicious authentic food, and the best service I have ever had in the United States.

name: shonna nguyen
text: Authentic Burmese food. She reminds me of my momma. Love the food. Tea salad is delicious

name: Hoan Nguyen
text: Fantastic hospitality. Good food. Cozy locale. Helpful for first timers.

text: Everything was fresh and tasty. Owners are wonderful and welcoming. Such a fantastic addition to the neighborhood.

text: amazing food and some amazing people working there.

text: Very good food and they are on doordash

text: Best service ever

name: mike Stettenbenz
text: The service was top notch! I was greeted promptly. The speed of service was very good. I was quoted 15 mins but received quicker. I ordered the Buffalo chicken pizza and I was not disappointed. It was delicious. I also had a side of Buffalo wings. For a pizza place they were very good. Nice flavor, good amount of sauce. And nice sized wings. The Cajun flavored crust was amazing. I can't wait to try the other flavors. One very very minor downside, they forgot my side of ranch.

resp.text: mike Thank you for taking the time and leaving us such a great review. We really appreciate all the support! - Howie's Support Team

name: Christina Kaye
text:
So this was a spur of the moment place to eat!! Looked at past reviews,  nothing bad at all on them!! We decided to try it out and OMG yessssss this pizza 🍕 is absolutely delish!!! We got a deep dish extra cheese 🧀 ham and pineapples 🍍 with butter crust!
The environment was very friendly,  fast and fresh just the way we all love it!!! Also it was a clean atmosphere,  where employees took the time to wash there hands properly!! To say the least my whole family and I were very impressed 👌💯

name: Joseph Evans
text: First time here I know they just open so they're a little slow but that's to be expected with a new business opening up and getting the volume at they're getting and especially with people just learning how good hungry Howie's is out here in the Colorado area but coming from Michigan originally spot on food mix it up I got a deep dish pizza with cage and crust and calzone and three cheese bread and all of it reminded me just like back home A1 job everybody!!!!

resp.text: Joseph Thank you so much for taking the time to leave such a great review!! - Howie's Support Team

name: Jake Rowberry
text: I couldn't help but notice a new restaurant while I went to the store the other day. Wanting to try/support a new local business I decided I would give them a call the next night for dinner. After scouring their menu and choosing what seemed like a solid pizza, I gave them a call to place my order for delivery. The... "Nice gentleman" that answered informed me that despite living within 2.5 miles, less than 6 minutes away, it was just too much for their delivery driver to handle. Apparently hungry Howie isn't hungry enough to earn my business...

name: Justin Thiel
text:
Pizza was pretty good, good selection of toppings, and baked well. Delivery time was pretty good. Might be growing pains but my credit card was double charged for my meal one night. The GM was unwilling to help and kept trying to blame other people instead of just offering me a refund or some pizza to make it up.
Little things like this can decide if a customer ever comes back - in this case thy have lost a potential customer over 30 bucks

resp.text: Justin It breaks our heart to hear that you bad experience at our pizza place. However, we appreciate you bringing this to our attention. Please contact us at https://www.hungryhowies.com/contact-us-0 so that we can get this to the store's owner and have your issue resolved.

name: Aaron Batilo
text: I don't know how much I can emphasize how much I would not recommend someone try this place. If I had the pizza at Chuck E cheese, at least I would also have the games to cheer me up. The chicken wings were so small that I have to assume they came from Chicken Little himself. This one is just going to have to be a no for me, dog.

resp.text: Aaron We teach our employees to always to provide our customers with the best product, service and image. Unfortunately, this wasn't the case with your experience. We will be bringing this to the owner's attention. Please contact us at https://www.hungryhowies.com/contact-us-0  so that we can make this up to you. We apologize for this poor experience but do appreciate you bringing this to our attention.

P.S. Pepperoni + sausage plus garlic herb AND butter cheese flavored crust is where it's at!

text: Went and had the four chicken special for $6.95. The best fried chicken deal in the area. The chicken was moist and crispy, very delicious. Decent portions, fast and friendly service. This place has been open for the last five months and is Green Valley Ranch's best kept secret. $7.00 at the other chicken places only gets you two pieces of chicken, a side, biscuit, and drink. The Chickens was very fresh. The sides are made locally. Thank You for opening a White Fence Farms in Green Valley Ranch! You gotta try it! Located next to domino pizza close to Green valley Ranch Blvd and Tower Road on the SE Corner.

I would probably rate them in a terms of service good job guys. As far as the tasting chicken I am not sure but the chicken smells delicious. The place was dirty, and the staff ALSO screwed up my wife's sandwich, putting in things that weren't on the menu and omitting several vegetables that WERE on the menu.

We joked afterwards that it was like visiting a cafe in a third world country. We only finished the food because we were very hungry. Afterwards, my wife got sick and she's still not feeling well as I write this.

Avoid.

2. Wonton soup
3. They supply University Hospital with sushi on the hour every hour to keep of fresh.

text: Generic Asian food - Chinese, Vietnamese, Japanese - all done to a level where it's OK to eat, but their sushi doesn't even come close, to say Banzai sushi, their Vietnamese is nowhere close to Top Phò... But,it is the closest Asian food restaurant to the campus. If you eat here, you won't remember anything good or bad about the food, and that's the best I can say about it.

name: TD's VloGaming
text: Ordered through delivery!... It arrived fresh, hot, and they even threw in a complimentary Miso soup! Then I tasted the food and fell in love! Overall, this may be my new favorite place period! Hands down, you must try this place!!!

name: Kyle Meador
text: Very good experience for lunch here. They have a huge selection of asian dishes from pad thai, to curry, to sushi. I ordered the vegetable peanut curry and really enjoyed it. Next time I would like to try their sushi and/or some of their traditional Chinese dishes. The prices were good as well. Would like to return sometime soon.

name: Jeff Dedman
text: Blue Lagoon has proficient, if uninspired food at a slightly higher than warranted cost. The dishes wont disappoint terribly, but they will leave you with a vague feeling of being taken advantage of. This is especially true of the sushi. It is hardly better than what you would find at a supermarket and they treat it as if it were gourmet. If they embraced their status as a sub par grub stop and lowered their prices it would be a favorite spot for college students like myself, however I fear they have found a niche for well paid medical professionals jonesing for delivered asian food, and they are exploiting it.

name: Matt Denman
text: This place is incredible! Fast, friendly service in person, plus a high nice online E ordering tool, and of course high quality food. We eat here a few times a month, love it!

text: Mila is a newer restaurant in downtown Denver. Everything about the restaurant is wonderful. The atmosphere is nice, and all the staff are very friendly. The food is an experience. We had two appetizers, two entrees, and dessert, and everything was absolutely amazing. The short rib had a unique combinations of flavors that sound good yet unusual at first, but upon tasting it, you are swept up in a perfect combination of savory, sweet, and acidic. The homemade pasta was also a hit as the dish we tried was just fantastic due to the homemade noodles. You can tell that the effort was put in to design a great menu at this place. I will cwrtcerta be going back for calamari and orange cake as well

The appetizers were great as were the pizzas but the entrees were just barely warm. We had a party of 7 and everyone's meal was just warm. We ordered a few cappuccinos after dinner and they were lukewarm as well. This is a beautiful restaurant with so much potential. name: Miss S.
text: I thought Mila was going to be a fine dining restaurant with excellent service, I was wrong. I was taking my daughter out for a celebration and made a reservation at Mila referred to as a sister restaurant by Limelight supper club. When we arrived I needed to use the bathroom so after we were seated I went and when I came back I asked my daughter if the waiter had been by yet, and she said ya just for some water. So 10 minutes go by and I actually had to get up and ask the hostess where our waiter was (which is a huge pet peeve of mine, especially with fine dining). Then the waiter casually comes up with his arms all tattooed (unprofessional for a high end restaurant in my opinion), and says "I already talked to your daughter about this" I was like "What, now this guy is arguing with me"! this really upset me. Then the food was good but not exceptionally good probably because the service was so bad it ruined it for the food for me.  I had to get up a second time to get our waiter when I had told him we wanted to order dessert and he said ok and never came back! We had a show we needed to be at the performing arts center so we were on a schedule, I did set aside 2 hours for a nice dinner. During the times I was waiting and looking for our waiter, I noticed him dilly dallying most of the time behind the bar with the patrons over there! So as we are leaving the hostess comes up and says " I know the service was sub par but would like to invite you back and give you these coupons for a free cocktail the next time you come in" I said well thats nice of you but we don't drink. So she puts the coupons back in her drawer and says "well I hope you come visit us again anyways" I was like wow they couldn't offer something else like the price of those drinks off the bill we just paid which was over $100 for 2 people no alcohol. When a place is that expensive and fancy I have high standards which Mila failed miserably at. The hostess also was not dressed very nice nor was the waiter, nor were they trained for a fine dining experience, they were more suited to be running a Denny's or the "Denver Diner". My advice, train your staff to give the experience of fine dining that you are charging for and why people come to your restaurant otherwise lower your prices a lot & turn Mila into a diner. There are way better places to go in downtown Denver for a fine dining experience such as Rioja.

I then ordered the food and that process was good enough but the food that came out was in HUGE portions. It seems that White Fence Farm did 0 market research about the neighborhood and thought they could bring family size portions to a part of the city that is young and childless. The food wasn't much better. As many other reviewers have commented the chicken was very oily and my french fries weren't very good. They were soggy with oil I couldn't even eat them. I think KFC has better chicken then what I got tonight. I feel White Fence Farm is pushing quantity over quality and customers are paying a premium price for food that chains do a better job of preparing. I won't be back.

name: Kimberly Schmit
text:
2-20-2017:
I must admit, that I am disappointed in this smaller version of White Fence Farms.
As I had previously written, I grew up going to White Fence Farm in Lakewood. You went for the food, as well as the experience of the entire place: the gift shops, etc. This fast food type version of White Fence Farm just doesn't cut it.

Service was poor, and there were only two parties ahead of us, both of which had ordered, and were waiting for their order. One party had two people, the other party was a single person. There isn't much to any order, as the menu is basic, such as 4 pieces of chicken, two sides, and some corn fritters. The food is already prepared in the kitchen, all they have to do is serve it up, so more like fast food, rather than the table service and experience that you get at the original White Fence Farm. When we were brought our order, it was correct. The only thing is, there was no extra plate or basket type thing for my husband (or I) to use to put our chicken and sides on.  I went up to the counter and asked for a plate or something to put my food on. The girl said, "Oh yeah," and handed me a paper plate. It's not a hard concept, two people, two plates. I don't get it.

Food quality - I will admit that the sides, especially the mac and cheese, as well as the mashed potatoes, are good. The chicken pieces that you get are very small.

Interior - clean, which is nice to see, and open. Lots of windows, so if it's cold outside, bring a sweater to wear inside. There are not a lot of tables / seating. I still believe that management would like people to order for take out, rather than sit inside. It's ok to sit inside, but you would be more comfortable sitting at your own kitchen table.

Noise Level - Quiet, as there are very few customers inside, bummer.

With the popularity of the originality of White Fence Farm, I would expect this smaller version of the original restaurant to be busy. Every time we have walked by, there are only a few people, if any, in the restaurant. The restaurant has been opened since mid November, 2016. I'm not sure if they are going to make it. Another nearby store also serves fried chicken, and it's actually quite good, and I think better than White Fence Farm. Disappointing. Sorry White Fence Farm.

text: Not gonna lie, the place was very clean, cheap, and had excellent food. Service was great, so I'm a bit puzzled why there are so many negative reviews about service. I admit, there are some young children running around, occasionally, but overall I give this place a 5 out of 5.

You could feel the chicken and shrimp squishing under your feet as you say down. When our drinks arrived there was no ice. My wife asked if she could have ice and we were told they ran out. This place is just garbage.

We come outta our way to eat here...and the few times it's been pretty good considering the mixed reviews posted here as I read along about rude customer service to the sketchy food and the price discrepancies...although I could agree somewhat on the pricing comment because I felt our bill was "sketchy" most recent visit...
But hey... I really dig the 🍣 sushi..it's good and fresh....so what if the employee's don't speak much English... And the green tea ice cream is darn tootin' (that means good)

text: Very bad staff/service. Their manager was very rude and did not cared about our opinion. I will definitely not come back.

name: David Torres
text:
I'm going to rate this place for what it is and nothing else: one of the best Asian buffets in town.

I'm big on Asian food, and I love exploring restaurants I haven't been to before, but this place became my go to comfort buffet years ago. The food here is of much higher quality than other buffets, always fresh, and delicious. They also have sushi, and while it doesn't reach "Sushi Restaurant" status, it's not bad, I actually don't even touch the sushi in any other buffets but here. Service has always been good, simple and respectful staff. The establishment is roomy and nicer than most.

If you want a great BUFFET experience, check them out. If you're looking just for Sushi like some of the assholes that left bad reviews on this place, I recommend you to try Sushi YaYa, google it.

name: Greg Gidden
text:
Hit or miss, but usually above average.  I eat here about once a month and have had a variety of experiences.  None have been bad enough to boycott the place, but none have been good enough to rave about it either.  Some items are fresher than others and I would highly recommend going during busy hours, like any buffet.  The service is ok, but they never seem to smile or be happy. Sometimes I wonder if they are forced to work there, like some of the kids that you will often see working.

There are lots of food options, a salad bar, desert/fruit area, a sushi bar, seafood dishes at night, and even some American dishes like pizza and french fries mixed in for the kiddos.  I feel like even though everything isn't super fresh always, there are enough items to choose from that you can find something fresh enough to make a meal out of.  I usually like the chicken and mushroom, jalapeno chicken, cheese wontons, and a spicy all white meat chicken dish that I can't think of the name right now (honey chicken maybe?).

The prices are affordable, too.  Around $10 for lunch and around $15 for dinner. That's what you would pay for a meal anywhere, so I think that's reasonable for an all-you-can eat buffet offering sushi and seafood.

Overall the place is worth stopping when you're craving some Chinese food and don't want to wait, however, don't expect over the top freshness, service or cleanliness.

name: K Sevlag
text: Being the only chinese buffet in my area, this place is reasonable. Lots of food to choose from, and it seems very clean. Quality isn't terrible at the hot wells, and the sushi is kept cold and stocked.

text: Went to try and eat here today and found a sign stating that the place has permanently closed as of September 4th, 2018! Just left a review so people will know.

name: Perky Raskal
text: We have visited this restaurant on over ten occasions and the same story unfolds. The food is enjoyable. I like the fried rice, along with the octopus and many other choice items. One downfalls of this place is the poor service. Apparently the waitresses have not learned to use courtesy words such as "thank you" and "your welcome." I mean come on, I say thank you to the waitress for poring me a drink and she ignores me every time and forget about anyone smiling at you here. It is a wonder that we have come back so many times. If it wasn't for the food and the great price we would go somewhere else.

text: Not even one star the food was terrible very old and dry. I tried a little of everything and left my plate full. When the lady came i told her she could charge the kids plate to my card but i did not eat, my hot tea was not hot, and my fiances iced tea was gross. What did she do? She nodded that she understood so i gave her my card. When she brought the recipt back with a pen to sign i noticed she charged the full amount. I told her no i asked you to take those items off. It was obvious she did not understand. She called someone else over and i explained the same thing to her. She nodded that she understood and told me in english to wait that she was going to get someone. I watched people pass by for about 20mins. I finally asked if someone was coming or not and no one even knew we were waiting! Finally what seemed to be the nanager or owner came out. I explained the same situation to her and she said i can give u 10% off. I said no i would like my price for the buffet off completely. I DID NOT EAT. She said i can take $5.00 off for you we have been waiting for you to leave for an hour. I said excuse me? The sign says you guys are open until 9:30pm (online it says 10pm) and i pointed to the sign. She said our hours changed. I was shocked. I said ok are you going to take this off or not? She said no. I said ok i will call the bank tomorrow and let them know i do not authorize this payment. And she starts yelling at me in her language! Unbelievable! I would not even give this place One star! text: I very much enjoy Hasu Sushi. The fish is usually very good (some I don’t like, but it’s personal preference, not an indictment on quality), and the value is there. The portions are very generous compared to similar restaurants in Denver. We’ve ordered from Hasu many times, and the one thing that keeps me from giving it 5 stars is consistency. I’ve noticed that the variety of their sushi/sashimi combo increases dramatically on weekends. Not necessarily a bad thing, as the floor is still very high. But I find myself ordering mainly on weekends as the quality and selection is just much better. Otherwise, great food, great price, definitely recommended!

name: Kelly Flanagan
text:
Was having trouble deciding what to eat for lunch. Walked with a coworker across the street - and there is was; a Quiznos glistening on the horizon like a long forgotten jewel lost in the flow of time. Sub of the day: Baja chicken. It was sweet with a hint of spice. Each bite more savory than the last. Was the most intimate feelings I’ve felt for a sandwich in a long time (jalapeño cheddar bread, what?). I’m sorry for all those years you were overlooked for Subway. May angels forever whisper echoes of your deliciousness through the winds of time.

~Ode to Quiznos

We were the only ones in there and it look twice as long for him to make our sandwiches because he kept messing up. Since they were so soggy, we wanted to switch them out for something else but instead he was no where to be found. The second we were done paying, he disappeared in the back and didn't come back out. We ended up eating a small portion of our sandwich and threw the rest away. Very disappointed. Won't be going back.

Brennah, We're sorry our toast did not meet your expectations.  We will certainly take a look at the consistency of the toasting, however I can assure you we toast all our bread unless asked not to.   We would love to have you back for an Avocado toast on us.  Let us know when you stop in.

Best

name: Matthew Groves
text: Tried to visit on a sunday morning.  First issue is clear.  4 parking spots, shared with next door neighbor.  Fedex, ANB, Piatti, and Del Frisco all planned for this and reserved spots.  No such luck here.  Inside is clean and colorful, options are solid, but at these prices, i dont see how they last.  Paid a little over 11 for zatar, with 1.79 being the lowest tip option.  Clean juice is a football throw aways. There are two starbucks and an aviano in the neighborhood.

resp.text:
Matthew, I apologize for the parking situation.  You'll be happy to know that there is no charge on Sundays for meters and you are able to take advantage of a front spot if available.  Outside of that, unfortunately parking rarely comes with real estate in the Cherry Creek area and as a small independent business unfortunately that wasn't an option for us.   We do take pride in the local, high quality and abundant product/menu items we provide and are sorry to hear you feel it is pricey.

We would love to have you back for a lunch on us.  Please just let us know when you visit us next and we will be happy to treat you,

Best,

The Corner Beet Cherry Creek

text: Great find!! My boyfriend and I split the chef salad with their house made vinegarette, it was sooo good! Then we got a medium half cheese, half pepperoni pizza. It's better reheated. Unless you like limp, soggy pizza for some disturbing reason, don't eat this. They don't even know how to dice their toppings so get ready to slurp onion & pepper.

Special shout out to the rude employee who expected a tip for pick up after refusing to deliver literally 10 minutes down Colfax. This place is all around trash

name: George Anschutz
text:
I've been an Enzo's customer, either eat-in or delivery perhaps 35 times.  Crust is amazing, perfectly caramelized, perfect char, perfect sweetness every time.  Toppings are fresh, red sauce is full of flavor.

Enzo's service is friendly and fun.  The guys who work at Enzo's look like they time-traveled from Boulder in 1969 .  Staff is professional and polite.

Pizza delivery exactly as expected.

Decor is East Colfax fluorescent with a bizarre assortment of seating that lets you feel every spring.  You'll need to get your beer or wine from PS Lounge, the dive bar connected to Enzo's.  Or, do like we do, order a pizza, then go over to a booth at PS, and Enzo's will deliver your pizza to you.

There's ample street parking in front of Enzo's on Colfax.

Update: 10/31/2020  Another delivery, pizza perfect in every way.

name: Kevin Huckabee
text: Excellent pizza and amazing crust that I actually eat. The toppings all taste very fresh!

name: Jared Kennedy

name: Kernal Ron
text: The best of the best in Colorado. The pizza has always been amazing and the spicy sauce and crust are what set them apart from the pack.  I recommend getting a pie and taking it over to the (connected) PS Lounge for some awesome drink specials!  Because where else do you see a place give the ladies a long stem rose?  Oh yeah, NOWHERE these days except the PS.  Break the "chains" and support your local mom and pop shops.  You won't regret it, trust me.

name: Kimberly Schmit
text:
3.0 star rating 2/18/2017
1 check-in
White Lies is in the same location as Black Eye Cap Hill, a coffee shop.
White Lies is open from 5:00 pm to 2:00 am. Black Eye Cap Hill is open 7:00 am to 5:00 pm.
We thought we would give White Lies a try. We have tried Black Eye Cap Hill.

The facility for both restaurants is in the same location.
This review is for White Lies.

The lights are dimmed, and the music is a soft jazz, very nice. You can actually hear the other people in your party, which I like. There are approximately 6 booths, and several long community tables, with attached stool type backless seats. There is also a bar with seating as well.

The dinner menu is limited. We choose the Hanger Steak, with mashed potatoes and asparagus.
The Hanger Steak was good, cooked to the requested temperature. The asparagus was good, as were the mashed potatoes. The price of the Hanger Steak was $17, a bit pricey, but it was good, nothing to complain about.

Waiter service was good, but the majority of the other tables (with younger patrons) did get better service. When I'm in a restaurant, I like to observe other people, as well as the restaurant employees. The food service was a bit slow. Considering the restaurant was not that crowded, it was a surprise.

Parking - street parking, which isn't that bad, as the location is just east of Lincoln, so that helps. You may still have to park at a parking meter.

There are lots of windows in the facility, so, perhaps bring a sweater, which I noticed several other patrons had on sweaters, or light weight jackets.  Spring isn't here yet in Denver, so you know how that goes.

I'm thinking that both Black Eye Cap Hill, as well as White Lies, are both targeting the younger crowd, and there is nothing wrong with that. Also, I think they are targeting the "come, have a drink, or two, and stay for a while, have an appetizer too," crowd. Both being places "to be seen." This is not my type of thing, as I'm past that stage in my life, and that's ok.

So, all in all, White Lies is not a bad place, it's just not my place.

text: My first experience was not good  but i gave it a second chance and it was 10x better. I got extra cheese and it was delicious.

resp.text:
Hi Zack,
Well i’d like to start by apologizing for the poor pizza you had. Not every pizza we make is perfect, but i promise you we try. Since we use a sourdough crust,  it can sometimes bubble up causing spots where it might seem like there was no sauce or cheese but really it just got cooked extra. I understand if you don’t give us a second chance but i always like to try a place twice to make sure it wasnt just a fluke if i had a bad first experience. But please come by for a pizza on us and hopefully this time you think it’s better than below cafeteria quality. Either way, we hope you have a nice holidays and find some tasty ‘za!

name: Ryan Hicks
text:
I don't really understand the hype about this place. I ordered the Mr. Pink Pizza from uber eats last night and it has salami, red sauce, and mozzarella. While it wasn't the worst pizza I've had in my life it most definitely wasn't worth the $16 bucks and $21.27 total from ordering it off uber eats. It was highly over priced. While the uber eats experience was great the presentation, taste, and experience of this pizza didn't match the uber eats experience nor the other reviews posted here.

As you can see from the images it arrived with a pool of mozzarella and red sauce that wasn't sticking to the crust. It was just floating on it. And as you can also see from the 2nd image all the ingredients were sliding off the crust every time I picked up a piece to eat. The crust is thin and has no flavor to it. It has a strong 5-grain wheat flour taste to it. Unless I get a free pizza I don't see myself trying this place again; every one of their pizzas is either $16 or hovers around that price. I'm not even terribly picky on my pizza. It's just not worth it and I don't understand how they're rated so high. There are so many better pizza options in Denver (especially in this area... like Walters 303).

The pros:
They're open late.
You can order it off uber eats.

resp.text: Hi Ryan. Saw your review from yesterday. Glad you enjoyed using Uber EATS. Sorry your pizza was seemingly (from your photos) underdone. Patrick and I do our best to provide a consistent pizza at a reasonable price @$15-$16 per. I have not yet eaten at Walters 303 but all of the 14" pizzas on their menu cost more than ours. Everybody seems to have a favorite pizza spot in town, glad you have found yours. If you find yourself over in Five Points stop by and we will make you another Mr. Pink. Best- FPP🍕

text: I don't know if this was an Uber Eats issue or a Five Points issue but this was quite possibly the worst pizza I've ever had in my life. We ordered the cheese, a Mr. Black and a Mr. Yellow. My kids would subsist on pizza alone and will eat a whole medium cheese by themselves but my oldest only ate one piece of cheese to be polite and my youngest wouldn't finish a slice. The Mr. Yellow seemingly had some sort of jalapeño paste or purée dumped on it in no apparent order and was insanely spicy. Just overall a really bad experience.

resp.text: Hi Jeremy. Sorry your family did not enjoy the pizzas from us, I'm sure UberEATS has nothing to do with your dissatisfaction. After four years of making pizza in Five Points we have amassed a core, loyal, customer base. I understand that the type of pizza we make here is not everyone's favorite, and a few folks like yourself downright hate it! We do the best we can with the highest quality ingredients available to us, no sugar, or preservatives. Chain pizza shops are great if your taste is specific and there are numerous other pizza options in Denver that conform to a traditional approach. Best wishes, Eden

Even though it was hopping busy, we were able to enjoy our food & drink, make it to the movie on time without a rush, and I have nothing but praise. I look forward to the next time I get to stop in for lunch or dinner. Thanks - you made me look good for suggesting you for dinner.

text:
Very nice place and atmosphere. Was greeted at the door and was asked if we wanted to sit at the high tables or low. Was well taken care of by Sean. Good service good food nice portion size.
Sean had excellent customer service skills, good sense of humor, was quick on getting us what we needed. We were on a time crunch so that my friends could get to the airport he got us in and out. Thanks Sean!

name: Kelsey Shackelford
text:
Food was great but the service was seriously lacking. I was extremely disappointed!
We made reservations for Valentine's evening. Walking in, we weren't even asked if we had a reservation we were just told "you're going to be put on the waiting list."  Once we were able to share that we did in fact have a reservation they seated us at the far end of the restaurant next to a large family with small children, away from the main section of seating that looked quite wonderful!
I think we waited close to 20 minutes before anyone approached us about ordering some wine.
Once our food arrived our waiter forgot about us. We even joked with each other about it as we saw him serving and being diligent with all of the other tables around us but it was as if we were invisible.
Long after we finished dessert he came and asked us if we wanted to stay around for awhile or if we'd like the check. We asked for the check.. It was close to 30 minutes later when he came in to check on us...we just politely asked for the check again and he brought it quickly. We didn't want to be rude. The restaurant was not that busy or full so it was a little strange to us.  I checked for an e-mail address to contact about our experience as I didn't want to leave a public message like this. But, there are no posted contact e-mails on the website. It just wasn't the setting for a Valentine's Day date.

We called tonight to give them another chance. The guy I spoke to had a "couldn't care less" attitude. When we finally got it figured out and I was ready to order the guy was having "phone issues" and the girl in the background was laughing until I was hung up on.  When I called back,  he again couldn't have cared less. I told him they weren't really earning our business back he responded "oh sorry I was having problems with the phone. " and nothing else, not, so sorry what can we get for you? Or anything, just sat silently.  Overall very rude and we decided not to order from rude employees who don't care about their customers.

name: Zorin Dobson
text:
We went to a happy hour at Jonsey’s Eat Bar.  We got street parking and walked through a small park where people were playing a good game of kickball in order to get there.  Jonsey’s had a very good happy hour going on at the time.  We could get much of the good quality craft beers on the menu for half off alongside their selection of fries for $5.  I found this place after a tweet from Alton brown that had a link to the 30 greatest fries in America.  Jonsey’s landed number 28 on that list.  Knowing this I had to try them since I was conveniently in Denver at the time.

We ended up trying three different types of the fries, which was far more than enough food for two people.  Yes I had dinner that day completely of French fries.  The three varieties we went for where the Truffle, which were my favorite and had a truffle aioli and shaved parmesan.  We also had the Green Chili, which was a requirement, being in Denver you have to get as much as you can with green chili and these fries were an example of how the mild flavor of that chili makes Denver’s love affair with the chili completely justified.  Last up on the list were the Asian version that had a tangy sweet and sour sauce.  Before trying them I wouldn’t think that this would work before I tried it, after the fact though the sweet and salty effect that you get with these fries really works.

name: Melanie Shanks (Shanksalot)
text:
Awesome night!
My husband and I are vegan and were surprise at how many options they had for us. The menu is small to begin with, but a good amount of those things could be made vegan. We asked our server to clarify if the vegetarian options were also vegan. At first she wasnt sure but quickly found out all of the answers. She was great! She really went above and beyond to make sure we had plenty of options and to make sure we knew what was vegan.

In the midst of our meal, they actually had to remake the rice, so were going to have to wait for a dish. My husband and I have both served before so we were not put off by this. Things happen and we were fine with waiting. However, they brought out a grilled veggie plate for us to munch on in the mean time, which was yummy and so kind.

Then we got a real treat when the bartender Devin brought us downstairs. Such a cool place. we will be returning to taste all their beers and sake. Thanks guys for a great night!!!

text: A neat place tucked into a hip part of town. The place is clean, minimalist, and very Zen like. Not your typical Ramen places. I had the #1, delicious soup broth, great noodles, and fillers. Decent portion size a little pricey. The Gyoza was great tasty with dipping sauce. Yaki balls were good also. Fast and friendly services. A great place to bring a date.

text: This is the sweetest hidden gem in RiNo! Awesome ramen, and the basement hangout is off the charts cool. Order a pitcher of cocktails which can be saki based and out of this world. Have some food and enjoy the awesome atmosphere. Oh and did I mention that everything on the menu is between $5-$10. Do yourself a favor and go meet the cool staff and let them show you what a great place this off the grid place is.

name: Krista Ashley
text: This was absolutely awful. The people who work here are rotten. After working in the service industry for three years as a waitress, I can honestly say I have never had this awful of an experience ever. After we arrived it took ten minutes for anyone to walk over to our table to even take our drinks. It took another 20 minutes to even receive the appetizers that were ordered. Another 20 minutes later, food was delivered, no one came to ask how anything was. I'm not sure why any of the food took so long, especially because the restaurant was completely empty. We were the only table in there.  The food that was ordered, appetizers and entrees were absolutely awful. The sesame chicken tasted like stale peanut butter, while the rice wasn't even edible. Both bowls of pho were awful as well. No spoons were even given to drunk the broth with. When talking to management about the issues we had with the food to try and get our problems solved, he screamed at us and threatened to call the police. If I could rate this place a complete zero I would. Everything about this place was absolutely atrocious. If you value your taste buds do not go here. The rudeness as well as the food was not worth the hour of my time that I just wasted.

name: Eleanor Cotton
text:
This is such a great additional to Denver's restaurant scene. I went last weekend with a friend, and we were so impressed. The menu is small, but offers more than enough options. She ordered the bowl meal, and I got the naan wrap. We both got chicken with different sauces and a variety of the toppings (which are all at no additional cost!). It took a bit to get our food, but that was mostly due to the fact that they make the naan to order! I watched them roll out the dough and cook it, so it is well worth the few additional minutes! I absolutely loved the wrap (it served like a burrito), it was so flavorful and a great deal. I think you get a bit more food with the bowl, so that is an even better deal

Everyone who worked here was so friendly, and the whole atmosphere is very charming. It is a small restaurant, so I would come here with one or two other people at most. Hoping all the best for Nomaste!!

text: Great flavors and quality food! 10/10 would recommend!

name: Michelle M. (Elevated Awaking)
text: I just had the chicken masala and a hot Chai. 😀👍🙏 Super delicious. The staff was warm and welcoming beautiful smiles. I'll be back it's also very close to home. Thank you Namaste.

name: Mason Traylor
text: Indian curry burritos! Great staff! Spicy!

name: K Wullums
text:
If you have ever thought to yourself "I'd like casual Indian cuisine in wrap or bowl form," get ya buns down to Nomaste. I never knew how much I wanted this in my life.

I first walked in the doors of Nomaste while delivering them a pizza. It smelled so good, I had to come back. When I did, Nicole recommended the Nom-wich with vindaloo. I was lost when it came to toppings but the combo she picked out seemed legit. The tamarind chutney sounded exciting. Tamarinds are the choice hiking snack. While waiting for the nom-wich, I helped myself to some chai tea and that was out of sight. It turns out, another staff member, Emily, had remembered me from before. It's nice eating at a place where they remember your face. I took my order to go, but after taking a bite, I had to rush back in and tell them what a fantastic job they did.

name: Hill Balliet
text: So good! Perfect lunch spot

name: Elena Lugo
text: The food is sooooo yummy!

name: Bailey
text: Good food. Very friendly owner and staff.

name: Siddhesh Deshpande
text: Good fusion restaurant.

name: Ignite
text: For some reason they charged my card a multitude of times until they drained one of my accounts. When I called yesterday they said they didn’t know how to fix it. Then they hung up after swearing they would call back. If I don’t receive my money back and some form of compensation I will file a police report. This is not funny or cool.

name: Shingo S. Ishida
text: Was pleasantly surprised to see a Cold Stone Creamery located here at this location, towards the eastern edge of town (guessing that this location serves a lot of folks who are involved with the airport?) The dessert here was a nice complement to a dinner at a nearby Indian restaurant and we were very pleased by the pleasant staff working at this location. Cold Stone Creamery's products are a bit more expensive when compared to other offerings at similar places like Dai*y Queen and Bask*n Robbins, but the quality at CSC is markedly better, which I think justifies the higher price. Plenty of flavors to choose, as well as those predetermined choices if you like combinations made with chocolate, nuts, etc.  This location also houses a Rocky Mountain Chocolate Factory, so you can also get non-ice cream treats here, as well.

name: Jill Burk
text: We have been here many times, especially on $1/scoop days over the past few years, but today was a major letdown. We went here today (after receiving the photo attached of a text that said today is $1/scoop day at the GVR location) as a celebration/reward for our 6 yr old being really brave in doing something, but I was disappointed to hear the girl behind the counter tell me that the owner of this location also has 2 other locations & that a different location was doing $1/scoop today... she went on to say that this particular location only does that on Wednesdays (today is Thursday). I showed her the screenshot of the text I received today (see attached pic below), but she still maintained that this info was correct & didn’t honor the deal for us. So we left there spending almost $8 on just 1 scoop of ice cream for each of our 2 sons vs $2 and change... I didn’t get anything for myself & my husband because I was so disappointed that they didn’t honor this deal since it was a mistake of some sort on their end. Too bad... we really did like to go there, but now we’ll need to find some place new where the customer comes first instead of the price point.

name: Britney Fuqua
text: This store in general is great. They have very cool flavors like cornbread BlackBerry jam, cotton candy, birthday cake, and really neat waffle cones dipped in chocolate and sprinkles. The only reason I took off a star is because it's in a sketchy part of town and near the airport.

name: Steve Kutcher
text: Always great ice cream!  On the downside, they have gotten a bit too pricey...

name: Lopez_ 5280
text: My first time and definitely coming back.. the girls were fast and helpful in understanding with items. Will return and definitely recommend

name: gilbert rodriguez
text: Obviously the ice cream is above par, however more than a good product is needed to run a company. With that said I have never seen a more immature group of workers. I came in to pick up an order and the girls working took their precious time making it and it seemed that they had never had sanitary training as they were cross contaminating every 2 mins. I'm very disappointed with this location and  not be going back until management cleans up their act.

name: Irene Hernandez
text: Everything was soo good!!

name: Kofi D
text: Great service even on a snowy night when  the other stores had closed. Thru make birthday cakes and all...and at the same time  have smiley faces when one walks in the door. You can sit and enjoy your order or  take it with you. Barely any wait or crowd on this cold night.

Absolutely delicious! We tried it for the first time tonight and were not disappointed!

I’m editing this 2 months later, we just ordered another pizza from here (usually it’s amazing) but tonight I received my pizza and there was NO SAUCE on it. Just cheese and crust. Very disappointed.

resp.text: Thank you kindly for the support and feedback, John. We look forward to serving you again soon!

name: Topher B
text: Through the COVID-19 pandemic I’ve done my best to help, and support local and small business. I had come across the Jersey St Denver Pizza Company location fairly early. I’ve thoroughly enjoyed their offerings, appreciated their safety precautions, and their accurate quote times for pick up. I’ll continue to be a patron of the location for as long as I’m in the area, and I’m craving pizza. Personal menu favourites are ‘The Magnificent 7,’ and ‘Cream Cheesman.’

resp.text: Thank you for your feedback and support, Topher! Your support means more to us now than ever and it makes my day to see that you've enjoyed your DPC experiences. See you soon!

name: Ben Winter
text: Might be my new favorite pizza place! Always busy, so plan ahead on your order. Times aren't crazy for how busy they are.

resp.text: Thank you, Ben! We're so glad you found us and that everything has been awesome. We value your opinion and look forward to serving you again soon.

text: OH WOW!! I have been shockingly surprised in the BEST WAY ever!! Denver Pizza Company has a Pizza called EAST COLFAX and it is one of the BEST PIZZAS MY HUSBAND AND I HAVE EVER HAD!! Today was the first time we tried this place and we cannot wait for tomorrow to come so we can get more for lunch. Anyone looking FOR GREAT Pizza it is a must that you try DPC because they have a great variety of choices for everyone who just loves pizza. FIVE STARS GENTLEMEN AND KEEP UP THE GREAT PIZZA PIES!!

resp.text: Thank you, Tarika! We don't mess around when it comes to great pizza and I'm glad you agree. See you soon!

He brought out the pizza, didn't say thank you, and never looked me in the eye. I would have expected more from the new business on the block.... Might give it another try, but probably not.

resp.text: Jay- I'm happy to see you loved the pizza! Thank you for the feedback, I have discussed it with the staff. We hope to have another opportunity to serve you and earn your stars soon.

name: Casey Bean
text:
Super slow, takes a full hour to get pizza at 8 PM on a Thursday night. The person who takes your order will not write it down correctly, so you will not get the right order. This has happened to 2 people in this apartment in the past 2 weeks, on 2 totally separate orders. Apparently my pizza took so long tonight because it sat in the car while the driver went back and forth from the store to other houses. I voiced that concern to the closing manager Jordan who came back at me with "well you didnt pay for it did you?" I didnt pay for it because I refused it at the door. I asked them to not send me a pizza they had just told me had been in the car so long, and they didn't even get me the right order.

A few weeks later got in touch with the owner who made the situation much better! Thank you!

resp.text: Hi Casey- We appreciate your feedback though it's disappointing to see you didn't have a 5 star experience. We'd love to discuss this with you and see how we can make it right- please give management a call, thank you.

name: Maggie Wilkie
text:
Nice family business! We ordered a pizza to go from here tonight. On the way home, I took a peek in the box and realised it was not what we'd ordered. I went back and told them about the mistake, and they immediately remade the correct pizza and said we could keep the mistake pizza as well. The new one came out quickly and they threw in a free cookie.

I appreciate a business that owns up to and corrects mistakes without a fuss. The pizza was good, too.

resp.text: Thanks for the feedback, Maggie. It's true that we are mere humans and do make mistakes from time to time! If given the opportunity to right any wrongs, we will always do what it takes to make that happen. We hope to earn that last star from you soon!

name: Brandon Shaffer
text: Absolutely loved this place. We were just in town for a little bit and found it based on previous reviews. I love Hawaiian food and this was one of the best I had ever had. The Loco Moco was especially good. My wife had the Chicken barbecue plate and she thoroughly enjoyed it. My one complaint is the Mac salad was a little flavorless. Otherwise, it is a great place to grab a quick plate lunch.

name: Tracey Crosby
text: This place is a total dive, but the food is delicious, the people are nice and the price is right! We had a mini Kalua Pork, Combo  BBQ plate and gravy fries. It was enough to feed 2 adults and 3 little kids. Everything we ordered was hot and fresh. We'll be back, Aloha.

name: Dolores Perea
text: Upon walking into the restaurant my party and I were greeted with a wonderful "Aloha!!" The food was delicious and service was awesome! The place was small but the environment was comfortable. Definitely going back again.

name: Amy Agredano
text: We weren't sure what to expect and were pleasantly surprised! The garlic chicken was delicious. Order the lunch size unless you are starving! They were playing Moana on the TV to create the Hawaiian feel.

name: mike nunya
text: Worst experience ever eating Hawaiian food. This restaurant was very dirty. The staff seemed overwhelmed couldn’t put ice in the drink machine ran out of most everything on the menu.. But the part that hurt the most is my eggs were not cooked correctly on my Loco Moco. Everyone knows that the over easy eggs mixing w the brown gravy makes this dish what it is. The best part of my meal was the rice which is sad. Really wanted to like this place but I would say stay clear. Owner needs to take more pride in the establishment put a little money into it clean it up and get some staff that take pride in their work.

name: Chase Laub
text: What a great find! This place is up there with L&L Hawaiian BBQ. I always go with the BBQ short ribs and it's always good. Fast and friendly staff. Food is great, can't ask for more.

name: Byron Huntington
text: I LOVE this place. Great authentic Hawaiian food, great prices. The Honey Garlic Chicken is AWESOME!

name: Sarena Roy
text: Love This place!! Tried L&Ls after having discovered the mouthgasm that is Aloha Hawaiian BBQ Thornton, and needless to say...... L&Ls DOES NOT COMPARE. This place is amazing, the atmosphere is totally familiar, like coming home and eating with loved ones. The staff is awesome and really friendly. Also I met the owner one time and I must say, he is a tall, tasty mug of hotcoacoa on a cold winters night. Anyways you will regret looking over this joint.

name: Shay Kiel
text: I love this place so much. I saw that the serve kimche do a side and I couldn't be happier. My happy place for sure

name: Amie Roberts
text: I went here a few weeks ago. The kid at the counter was super nice. But they were out of everything and I paid $35 for food that was super disappointing. Kalua Pig had no flavor, honey garlic shrimp drenched with sweet and sour sauce from a jar and the BBQ Beef was burnt, I'm not sure what sauce it was in.

name: Lorin Ball
text: Long waits during lunch hours, most of the food is authentic Hawaiian local food. Seating area could use an upgrade. But, overall worth grabbing a plate lunch if u haven't had local grinds in a while.

name: Anthony Alvior
text:
I really enjoyed this hole in the wall Hawaiian restaurant, and it was a great find after just landing in Colorado.  They have two portion sizes for meals, regular and mini, and to be honest, the mini is the perfect size for being satisfied and not overly full.  I ordered the mini sized portion of the Honey Garlic Chicken which had a scoop of rice and the delicious macaroni salad, and I also added an order of the Spam Musubi.  The food was so good and very inexpensive.  The restaurant is small but has plenty of room for seating.  The restaurant is relatively clean, and when we came for an early lunch (around 10:45ish) there was only one person working the restaurant.  She was doing the cooking and taking the orders both from the phone and walk-ins.  I felt bad for her, and didn't complain that our food took a little time to come out.  We weren't in a hurry anyways, and it was well worth the wait.  Fortunately, right around the start of peak lunch time, two other people came to help her out.

I definitely recommend this place if you're passing through the area and want a taste of Hawaiian food.  It seems like the locals come through here quite often.

name: G W
text: The food taste good and the people working there or nice. But they have a ridiculous rule that you have to pay $10 or more to use a credit card and everything costs under ten bucks.

name: Mike S
text: Lunch was underwhelming.  1st visit. We were really looking forward to some Hawaiian food that day. Katsu musubi had a "small" piece of chicken that was over fried or microwaved. Other items were a bit skimpy. Rice was plenty. There are some good flavors though. We will try this place again.

name: Grace Martin
text: Closest in Thornton. Sweet workers. Good food. Simple hole in the wall with good Hawaiian eats

name: William Sharp
text: Friendly staff,  great food. Order ahead for pickup is a nice option.

name: Stephanie R
text:
I never write bad reviews, but I really don't know HOW this got a 4 star rating. I came here based on other peoples reviews thinking I was going to get some good ethnic hawaiian food. I was pretty surprised what I found. The chicken tasted old, chewy and fatty. Almost everything was fried, and the rice was bland and tasteless, with no seasoning or sauce, just sticky white rice.
The kitchen was questionable.
The Kitchen chefs had no hair nets, didn't use gloves, and were touching other things while touching food.
You have been forewarned .

text: Use to love this place but it seems like every time I come here now they are out of something or they tell me 15 mins i get there in 15 mins just to wait another 15. Hope they can get it together.

text: The Kalua pork here great. The portions are large and worth the money. The only thing not worth the price is their Kimchi.

text: Love this place....spam masubi....mahimahi...oh yeah...plus the Hawaiian soda I miss so much.

text: Was a good amount of food for the price and tasty!

name: Danielle P
text: The atmosphere felt like an old, rundown Chinese takeout place. There was junk scattered around, and everything appeared a little dirty (including the front door and the carpet). As for food, I got a spam Musubi and a chicken katsu Musubi. Somehow, the rice was actually soggy, the seaweed wrap was falling apart, and the chicken katsu was mostly crispy breading. Compared to L&L Barbecue in Aurora or Ohana Island Kitchen in the Highlands, it was subpar. I do not recommend coming here.

text: Great food, Good prices, friendly faces,the place is clean and comfortable,they play Hawaiian music,nice decor,  I think is a great place to eat and have a good time.

text: It is not healthy or fancy. Yet it was very delicious.

name: Clinton Stephens (Kota.Tiger)
text: To start the shrimp was fried with the shell on.  Who in the hell actually does that? On the menu they say they serve Mahi Mahi. That was not Mahi Mahi, nor was it ona which might have been a suitable replacement if someone was being honest about it... That was dry,  flakey and white Talapia. Pre breaded if I didn't know any better! Gross! Nothing was seasoned. Bland, boring, waste of time. I've taken multiple trips to Hawaii and this is nothing even close. Disgusted and to tell you the truth insulted. If a restaurant can't be honest with you about what they're putting in your mouth they really don't deserve to be in business. It was in a run down strip of shops, dirty and gross. I will never go back. Ever. If you want semi decent Hawaiian BBQ drive down to Aurora and get L&L... At least they won't lie to you about what they're feeding you.

I will have to go again since I work near it.

text: Very nice place. Great fire stove pizza. Cozy atmosphere. They occasionally have live music. Staff is friendly and efficient even with large crowds. Drinks are pretty fair price for a down town venue. I really like the spot and the atmosphere. I highly recommend visiting Brik on York. You'll be impressed.
