text: Excellent selections. Great staff and friendly. Pizza is excellent. Highly recommended.

name: Amy Coleman
text: Loved it. Great pizza, great sour beer, great love music. Overall charming atmosphere.

name: Jake Kahn
text:
Yet another tale of me really REALLY wanting to like a place.  And then sorta liking it but not really?

Came in on a Sunday morning for some sweet sweet brunch action.  Made a reservation but really didn't need to in the end.

We came in as a double-date 4-top, and were promptly seated.  That was the first and last "prompt" aspect of our meal.

We ordered a round of drinks.  The fresh-squeezed Granny Smith apple juice was pretty nice, with a bit of whiskey in it, and that made it even nicer.  Unique and tasty!

I ordered a greyhound with vodka, and it seemed to cause some confusion.  Waitress eventually made and brought out a damn-good greyhound with fresh-squeezed grapefruit juice.  Hell yeah.

My Hangover Skiller was tasty, and my girlfriend's hash was solid with big chunks of meat.  All served in piping-hot small cast iron pans, nice.

My only complaint was the delay in everything.  We arrived at 1115am for brunch: we finally left at nearly 1pm.  There was a single waitress for eventually-5 tables, and 2 other employees that I never saw do anything other than be engrossed in their phones.  The waitress was obviously overwhelmed, as she seemed to be the bartender as well as everything on the front-end, and the resulting delays were noticeable.

Another front-end staff member would have turned this brunch into a very pleasant affair, but instead, it left us scrambling to rearrange our schedule after a nearly-2 hour brunch.

Good food, good drinks, but not a fan of 2-hour meals, especially when the blatantly-missing staff is the sole cause for this.

Would be 2 stars, but the food was really good.

name: Holland McKnight
text: We decided to have dinner here New Year’s Eve before going to a nearby event. Our visit started with waiting 15min for the valet which never showed so we ended up parking around the corner. Because of our tardiness our party had already been seated, we arrived to a freezing cold room, everyone was huddled up with their winter coats on trying to stay warm. I thought it was odd that they had one of the front doors propped open during a winter storm only adding to the problem. The waiter at this point began to apologize for the poor service stating that they were extremely under staffed which was apparent when he was in such a rush taking out drink order he forgot someone in our party. The restaurant seemed very empty so I was surprised that being “under staffed” was such a big deal. After a long wait for drinks We were disappointed in the fact that they ran out of martini glasses so the drinks were served in a regular cocktail glass which normally wouldn’t be an issue but when it’s already freezing cold you don’t really want to be holding onto a cold drink. Most of us has decided on a starter of the soup of the day which was potato and leek, this sounded great to warm us up but when we went to order we were told this was now unavailable. After ordering and waiting for a while we noticed that the other tables had bread and since we were starving by this point we asked for some which was brought out with our food. I ordered a well done burger which was delicious but the other two people in our party had ordered their burgers medium which were both very well done. We were definitely disappointed with this experience. I thought the food was decent and good quality but this has to be the worst service I’ve ever experienced in any restaurant.

name: Terry Yarbrough
text:
The food was very good, the service was awful.
of course we went there for the buffet and the breakfast buffet is offered on the menu. And there was no notation in the menu stating that they were not serving the buffet, it was in there like it was be being presented as if it was there.
The girl stated due to remodeling they will not be having the buffet and it would have been also nice, if at the time you walk in, they informed you that there is no buffet, but they do have a full menu.
The waitress was late with the bacon in the orange juice.we saw that talking to another employee was a lot more important than their customer service. Seeing that there was only five tables at the most in the dining room.
I did notice that the interior did need some work the lighting over the table they had taken electrical tape and fixed one of the lights.
The bench padding is fraying. There was some beautiful orientals furniture in the lobby of the hotel and in the restaurant.
Sad that the service was horrible

name: Ashlynn McCarthy
text:
I sat here waiting on a colleague for over 10 minutes without even being offered water. They have an EXTREMELY limited menu. Despite the small, simple menu, the kitchen staff refused to caramelize onions for a customer. This is a simple request when the kitchen already serves onions and uses a cooktop. Given the price of this place, and their utter refusal to accommodate even simple customer requests, I can guarantee I won't be back. Nor will I take business colleagues there for lunch after this. I've had better service at much less expensive eateries. It's an embarrassment to take a business associate to such a nice place only to have approximately 7 menu options, slow service, and completely unaccommodating kitchen staff who already have a ridiculously simple menu to prepare. I have heard nothing good from the guest I took here. I'd have had a better experience for my guest at a Chick-fil-a. Shameful.

The food I did get was not good. I ordered the grilled cheese, pretty hard to mess that up. But boy did they.... The bread was so dry it literally crumbled to the touch and felt like sand in my mouth. I don't think they even used butter to help retain the softness of the bread. I'm no chef, but who makes a grilled cheese so dry it crumbles before you can eat it? I literally threw the whole thing away. Their menu is also scant on food description or side item listing. My food came with fries. Turns out what that means is it comes with a side of black pepper soaked in fry oil with a hint if potato. Who eats peppered fries?! Why wouldn't they tell you about such an unusual preparation of a ubiquitous item?

And before management responds with an invite to email them to discuss it, let me just say don't bother. It'll be a waste of your time. Not even free food would entice me to return to such subpar food and endure such poor service. There are tons of better options in Denver that don't require you to chance a business meeting on bad food, poor service, and unaccommodating kitchen staff who have less to prepare than the average fast food line cook and don't even do as well as a line cook. If you're going to spend $20 per person for lunch, go anywhere else.

name: George Anschutz
text:
We enjoyed our meal at Randolphs.  Randolph's is a large, elegant, airy, well-appointed space, with comfortable seating and lovely views of downtown.  There are cloth towels in the men's room.  I always appreciate a hotel that will go to the time, trouble, and expense to provide this simple luxury.

To start, we were treated to some wonderful ciabatta, hot out of the oven, with a perfect garlic chive butter.  As an appetizer we had the lump crab cake accompanied by a sauce that was a little overbearing for my taste.  My partner, who goes sauce-free, thought the crab was perfect.

We then enjoyed the escarole Caesar salad.  The dressing was a little too lemony for our taste, and we agreed that we would have preferred the standard romaine.  However, the salad was super fresh and well-presented and especially good with a little more of that ciabatta.

Our main courses were outstanding.  My partner loved his scallops, and my pork loin was over the top.  I asked for a substitution in accompaniments, and they cheerfully obliged.  The result was perfect, with a lovely sage flavor just in time for the holidays.

We finished with the deconstructed New York cheesecake, a sweet finish to a great meal.  A strange element was a piece of lettuce which might have been meant to be a green presentation aspect.   Maybe they ran out of mint.

Our server was perfect, but other staff could have been more punctual in removing our leftover plates.

All in all, it was a great meal in a lovely setting.

text: I highly recommend this restaurant. My husband and I enjoyed dinner here a few days ago. The waiter was very nice and attentive. It atmosphere was very calm. The large windows are nice and fill the restaurant with natural light, which was nice. I loved how quiet it was in there. The food was excellent. My husband had the clam chowder followed by the stuffed quail. He thought both of them were very good. They are small portions, which were just the right size for a meal! I has the seared tuna with the Duck L'Orange for a main course. The tuna was very good, the seaweed salad was amazing that came with it. The duck was to die for! Every bite was amazing. It came with brussel sprouts and fingerling potatoes, which were very good as well. I was in the mood for a fruity drink, but I do not drink alcohol. So I asked the waiter if he could talk to the young lady behind the bar and ask her to make me an interesting drink. He brought out a mojito with blueberries in it. I loved it! My husband also ordered the creme brulee for dessert. He very much enjoyed that. A very nice restaurant. Thank you for the wonderful evening.

name: Lauren “Milla” Clack
text:
Our office up in Stapleton got the scam today. I'm not a big pizza fan, so I didn't waste my money but it felt extremely scummy for someone to do that. The few personnel that did pay threw out the pizza after a few bites. They all said it tasted pretty bad and especially when my department was the one who saw the other reviews and figured out it was a scam, everyone was worried it was baked out of some guy's basement and potentially poisoned (I mean, look at the media lately, I think they're being a little overboard but it's definitely not outside the realm of crazy that has been happening lately).

Like the other reviewer, I think it's a creative tactic to sell, and if it works? Okay good for them. But I doubt they would get new business when it seems like a scam. I know everyone at my office is pretty angry. Not only that, looking on their website for prices, it looks like people actually paid the same or more than if it was a legit order. More scummy.

text:

I can't express how good their burgers are except to say that their burgers are probably the best I've had in Denver.. maybe at all.

Their sweet potato fries are some of the best I've had. Truffle parm are solid too, but I'd recommend just getting the regular.
Boozy milkshakes are fun and yummy, when they have them. Mostly a beer bar with basic cocktails if you ask. Lastly, If you like mushrooms, make sure to get the "fun guy" burger!

text: Classic burger joint but not necessarily classic burger prices. I’m a big fan of the standard BBQ burger and highly recommend including parm truffle fries. I’m also a big fan of the salads as I’m not always in the mood for red meat. You can even get a burger on a bed of greens if that’s you’re cup of tea. And online ordering is a breeze so no excuses to not take advantage of right now.

name: Alex Orchilles
text:
Park Burger is a delicious burger spot in the RiNo Arts District of Denver. From what I've tried, this spot has some amazing burgers, truffle fries, and beers.

I've tried out The Royale (1/3 lb. patty, caramelized onions, bleu cheese, & bacon), The Scarpone (1/3 lb. patty, provolone, crispy pancetta, giardiniera, & truffled garlic aioli), The Fun Guy (1/3 lb. patty, sauteed mushrooms, Swiss cheese, haystack onions, & truffle-garlic aioli), and the truffle-parmesan french fries.

Definitely one of my go-to spots for burgers since it is walking distance from my  home!

Update: Stopped by here a few days ago and tried out some new menu items including two pizzas, a caesar salad, the house margaritas, and a cookies and cream milkshake. Everything we ordered was delicious! The two pizzas that I recommend are the Whistle Pig (candied bacon, crispy pancetta, and caramelized onions) as well as this other one which I forgot the name but it had mushrooms and truffle oil - this one was great! Highly recommend this spot - check it out soon!

I'm sorry that you did not get this kind of experience. I'd like to make this up to you so if you don't mind, I'd love to connect with you over email. Please reach out to matt@gastamogroup.com. Parking is definitely a challenge.  There is a Colorado Rockies parking one block north and one block west.

name: Lu X
text: Delicious, very natural tasting with out the lack of flavor. A little pricey so the best time to go is Happy hour with all the deals it’s great

name: Chris R
text:
Would come back to Park Burger for their burgers and the friendly waitstaff. We had no trouble getting a table for 4 on a Friday night and were quickly waited upon. Our food came out 5 minutes after we ordered, which was clutch because all of us were starving.

Speaking of the food, the sprouts and the fries both missed in terms of how well they were cooked. The sprouts were practically charred with no remaining signs of green and the fries were a bit soggy in places - impressive given they're so thinly sliced. Flavor on both of the dishes was superb, so it was not a complete disappointment.

The burger that I had - classic double Park Burger - was the star of the show. The meat had a depth of flavor you don't find in your typical chain-restaurants like Five Guys. It was a simple set of toppings on top of some impressive meat and nothing was insanely expensive, even being in RiNo.

For the price, I would definitely come back to Park Burger. I may give the fries and sprouts another chance; I'd for sure sink my teeth into their other burger offerings.

The service was pretty good a bit too many tv's for my taste but overall a nice place to have a beer and a burger.

I certainly will be back the next time I'm in Rino.

name: Jessica Elizabeth Owens
text: It's ok.  Our service was really really slow, which sucked because we were entertaining international business partners.  Food was tasty, veggie burger was ok, when I asked questions the waitress had an attitude answering.  We ordered appetizers and food and asked for appetizers first.  It all came it together from a different server.  Then our original server came back 20 mins later and asked if we were ready for our burgers and we informed her they came quite a while ago (and cold at that).  I wouldn't go back, but it also could have just been a fluke.

name: Ashley Johnson
text: Food was really good and the environment was fun however, I will not give more than 3 stars because of the snooty attitude my wife and her cousin received from the waitress.

name: Torrey Witte
text: Nice place with outside terrace, where we sat. Good choice of tasty burgers, i had the royal one which is just under 10 usd comes with blue cheese, bacon, tomatoes, pickles and onions as well a sauce. Fits perfectly in your hand, great mix of tastes, perfect meat, enjoyed it very much. We took a basket mix of the sweet potatoe fries and normal fries with garlic / parmesan on top. A lot of different craft beers alone ranging from 4 to 8 usd. Ended it all with a icecream shake for 5 usd. Great service. In total for two with burgers, mix of fries and one dessert and several beers it ended around 75 usd.

text: I can't get enough of this place. You know when your friend is all "where do you want to eat?" and you're all, I don't know but what I do know is that I want to shove food in my mouth and I want every bite to be amazing and I want to be walked through their highly informed and eclectic whiskey selection while you have a fantastic beer and also I want a milkshake and I want the people to be true Denverites, beautiful, funny, and warmly friendly? Yeah. Go here. Best veggie burger EVER.

name: Sydney Valentino
text: When we got there we asked politely if we could sit outside and she told us "well I don't know, it's going to rain." I looked outside and was very confused. It was almost as if we sat outside and it started raining we would have to stay out there. I thought maybe she could see the puzzled look on my face but apparently not. As we sat there for less than an hour she sat group after group outside. Id say at least 10 different parties and we were sitting close to the hostess stand and i could hear her offering "inside or patio?" Um excuse me what? The waitress was very dull. Didn't really seem to care too much about making us happy. She gave us the bill as i was still eating and said no rush. Right after i put my card down she came right over to swipe it in these machines they walk around with. Then she pointed it to the gentleman I was with. I feel like maybe those machines arent the best idea for this reason. We were both embarrassed and even though she felt bad about it I was very uncomfortable and felt bad for the gentleman I was with. The food was ok. There are no chicken sandwhich options for people who don't eat burgers. They have veggie burgers and Turkey burgers but no chicken?? No option to add chicken to the salad? Not too expensive but the salad was tiny for the price. Not impressed. Probably will not go back.

name: Terry Long
text: The burgers aren't the biggest, but they taste pretty good and so do the fries. Not a big fan of the drinks they offer, but I'm not much of a drinker. The building is cool, but its kind of a crowded place, not much space between tables.

name: Nato Francescato
text:
Update: October 2020 - No longer worth the price. Way better quality in the neighborhood, i.e. cherry cricket.

Croque Burger for under ten bucks makes this place a go to lunch in this expensive neighborhood.

resp.text:
Hi Nato,

Thank you for taking the time to give us your feedback. We are so sorry that you had a negative experience! Our goal is the total satisfaction of our customers, and to provide a positive experience. I would love to connect with you further to learn more about your visit, if you'd like to email me directly at megan@gastamogroup.com. I look forward to connecting with you soon.

Kindly, Megan and the Park Burger - RiNo Team

name: chris meth
text: Great atmosphere and awesome burgers. Friendly and attentive wait staff. Great service overall.

name: Dick Foss
text: This place is cool and the food is good. There is a nice beetle-kill wall treatment that I copied for my daughter's mini-remodel. She loves it!

name: Michaela Davidson
text: Good service and friendly management. The food is always wonderful and timely, plus, the environment is always a blast on game day!

name: peter longfield
text:
Rude host - waitress didn't really care either. Soggy burgers, noisy room, uncomfortable seats and tables :(
Serving a burger in a basket lined up with paper is not a good idea. When the waitress lifted it up after my meal, there was an actual puddle of sauce under it - which she saw - but left without cleaning it !
There are many other places around with better burgers and more professional staff.

name: Patrick Gallagher
text: Love this place. They have so many beers on tap, the lemonade is fresh squeezed, and the burgers...Getting figgy with it, is amazing. 1/3lb burger with arugula, bre cheese and fig jam, WOW!

name: Manyi Szabo
text: Would have been 5 stars but our waiter never checked on my beer after asking twice. He was too concerned about a bigger table. Food was hands down the best ever!!!!

name: Jen Tetschner
text: Park Burger serves up some of the best burgers in town, but at a price. And the price will be your time and patience. Most visits to this location include terrible service from a staff that leaves a lot to be desired. Unorganized, aloof, and frustrating are a few words that come to mind when I think about the management. The Park Burger brand has been revered in Denver for years and I love that it’s growing and expanding, but it’s hard to see it compromised by this one bad apple.

text: I love karaoke!!! The staff is very friendly and welcoming, I love the happy hourly and the service industry night specials!!!

text: Needs a more current selection of music.  Especially foreign music.

name: Joshua Wallace
text:
One of my favorite places to go and have a fun night out!
Their weeknight deals are awesome and the staff is usually helpful and friendly. The free valet service is a huge plus!!

Booking a room is very easy but it's a little annoying that you have to wait for a phone call to confirm your reservation.

There are a ton of song options and I love that you can check what's available online and keep a profile. One sad note is that a few of my favorites such as Taylor Swift and Hamilton have recently been removed :(

resp.text: Hi Joshua! Voicebox is hard at work trying to source your favorite songs! Unfortunately, some artists do not prefer that their music be used as a karaoke track. Check back with us again soon as we continue to work toward new arrangements with your favorite artists!

name: sabrina archuleta
text: This was such a fun experience! My first visit for a surprise party and I loved it! Our group of 5 had issues with separate tabs but the staff was PATIENT and helpful and I was glad to see the manager was actively part of the quick resolution. Will visit again😊

text: Love the private rooms and it's fairly nice inside. The service was very good too.

name: Jake Torrison
text: Stoked we finally got some quality karaoke in town. But rooms were super hot with a big group, I don’t know if air conditioning was working or not but got dang we were roasting. Also drink minimum is pricey when we’re all sweating. All in all had a good time with friends, service could have been much better.

name: Marc Kaeden
text: I love karaoke!!! The staff is very friendly and welcoming, I love the happy hourly and the service industry night specials!!!

text: Private rooms are comfy and it’s easy to queue up music as your friends are singing

name: Logan D.R. (LDR)
text: Been here several times and for my birthday and loved it! The service is amazing but not intrusive. The food and drink is also very good. The selection of songs offered is very good. I would recommend this place to anyone looking to spend time with friends! Amazing experience!

resp.text: Thank you Logan for this enthusiastic review! We hope all our guests have this experience! Looking forward to seeing you again soon!

name: s. fisher williams
text: This place reminds me of the movie Logan's Run....if everyone in it were to take turns singing popular songs.....and not exploding when they turn thirty.....you know what? This place doesn't remind me of Logan's run at all! It reminds me of a musical Clockwork Orange........minus the milk.....

resp.text: Ha! We hope to see you again soon!

name: Britinie horvath
text: Everyone there was fun and welcoming.  We were a bit of a rowdy crowd and they rolled with it.  They did a great job with drinks and food and making us feel special.  We will be back for sure!

resp.text: Thanks so much Britinie for your enthusiastic review! This is exactly what we hope all our guests experience. Hope to see you again soon!

name: Mathias Anderson
text: The staff was very professional and quick to serve. The venue worked out wonderfully for our joint bachelor/bachelorette party. The acoustics were a little weird (we do karaoke a lot) and some of the tracks had a weird cadence in spots, but we had a great time. I'd definitely recommend this venue for some karaoke fun with friends.

resp.text: Thanks for your feedback Mathias! This is exactly what we hope our guest experience. We invite you to email our vendor at Lyrical Systems noting the song that was out of rhythm. He can be reached at steve@lyricalsystems.com. We hope to see you all again soon!

name: Lydene Wolf
text: Fun! I just wish i was a good singer

name: Denise Maes
text: Fun place to spend with friends. Didn't like giving my credit card upon entry. Slow service in room, I had to go to outside bar to get drinks and order food. An expensive night. The tech and room set up are high end.

name: Kristi Real
text: Great service. Fantastic song selection. Easy to use interface. Had a blast!!

name: Michael Cummings
text: Karaoke here was awesome! You have your own private room and the cost is really not too bad if you get a good group of people together. Choose what songs you want to play and let it all out! I'd never tried my hand to karaoke before but I think I'm a professional singer now 😅

resp.text: That's awesome Michael! We hope you come back soon!

name: Andrea Joy Studzinski
text: My group bailed on me day-of. My husband and I invited a new group to fill in. The new group bailed right at our appointed check in time. Two hours of karaoke as the only largely empty room in the entire place could have been awkward but they made it work for us. They took care of us, knowing it was how we were celebrating our one-year anniversary. We will likely go back, but hopefully with a proper group.

resp.text: Thanks for the review Andrea! Glad to hear your anniversary was a success!

name: Maxwell Sands
text: It was exactly what it advertises to be. A place you can rent a room, sing and drink with friends. Decent and friendly service. Free valet parking, which in RiNo is amazing.

resp.text: Hi Maxwell! Thanks for your review. We hope to have you and your friends back in soon!

name: Ric C
text:
They close at midnight, last call at 1130 so a waste of drinking time. Over priced drinks. Limited draft selection. Karaoke song selections are very limited compared to other song banks. They don’t take walk ins, you have to make a reservation. There have been More than a few times when they have closed early, so not really midnight at all times. Food options suck and kitchen closes early. And they will not let you order delivery after kitchen has closed.

If you do actually want to show up to this place after all that, just make sure to make your reservation is way ahead time.

And 2, clarify your form of payment at the beginning (before you sing) because it sucks when they charge the whole bill to the one making the reservation or the one that put their card on file. Even if you wanna pay cash they still need a credit card on file, so keep that in mind. The fastest way is to just charge credit on one account because anything outside of that and they will eff it up.

The one plus to this place is that it has private karaoke rooms. The negative is that they have a monopoly.

resp.text: Thank you Richard for your feedback. We are certainly disappointed to see we missed the mark with your experience. Please feel free to send us more information at info@voiceboxkaraoke.com so we can help rectify this.

name: Austin Harris
text: Awesome place with great customer service! Had a blast!! Will be back :)

name: Dan Rutherford
text: Great place to bring together large groups of friends. Not too expensive for food and booze. Find out which friends secretly love nickelback by queuing up the back!

name: Brianna Grimm
text: Super fun place to have a party with all your friends! The service is prompt and hilarious. The song lists are great and the food and drinks are great too! I definitely want to come back and sing my hear out 🎤

resp.text: Thanks Brianna! We hope to see you again soon!

name: rjcass33
text: This place is an absolute blast. One of the best birthday parties I’ve ever had!! 11 outta 10 would recommend!

name: Joel DuBois
text: Went here for the first time Saturday for a friends birthday party.  It was extremely fun and the service and drinks were great!  My only advice would be to see if there is some way to lower the amount of echo noise inside the rooms.  People enjoying the party combined with the music made it hard to hear the signing.  I'm not an expert but maybe commercial carpet and sound deadening material on the ceiling and walls might help?  Regardless, it was very fun and very glad we went!

resp.text: Thanks Joel for the feedback! Hope to see you again soon!

name: Kofi D
text: Very private rooms with soundproofing, party room with just your own crowd, using their website to choose the songs you like; powerful JBL speakers for different frequencies; Compared to other Karaoke places, this is definitely of a different class than I have observed In Denver. Waitress was courteous and frequented the place with food and beverages making sure everyone was ok right to their closing time

resp.text: Hi Kofi! Thanks for the great review!

name: Ruth Poliakon
text: I always have a fun time here! It can be a little pricy but if you go on Tuesdays it's a great deal! Still waiting for them to get fresh jams (if y'all got some more Janelle and Carly Rae I would be so pleased).

resp.text: Thanks Ruth! Yes, the best deals are Magic Mondays and $12 Tuesdays! We are working with a unique supply chain for our music and it is our top priority to get new music as soon as we can. We typically update our library once a quarter. We look forward to seeing you soon at Voicebox!

name: Serena Weber
text: For those of us who don't want to karaok in front of strangers, Voicebox is your place!! First time karaoke for my birthday with a private room with 14 people - super fun! You pick the songs from your phone, 1-2 mics (depending on room size), and your server comes directly to your room.

resp.text: So glad to hear about your first experience Serena! This is exactly what we hope all our guests experience. Hope to see you again soon!

name: Gilbert Lovato
text: So much fun, a little pricy but a lot of fun.

name: Zach Case
text: So much fun! Great venue for a group looking to do an activity different than the normal bar hopping. Can't wait to come back with another group.

resp.text: Thanks Zach! We hope to see you again soon!

name: Amelia Thomas
text: Very fun. Definitely keeping on my list for future parties!

name: Nicolas Holthaus
text: Fun place to do private karaoke parties. Rooms were larger and cleaner than many other similar karaoke venues I've been to. The system had all the songs we wanted and it was easy for the whole party to use with a cell phone app. The bar is weirdly insistent about having a single tab for your whole group, but the drink selection was good.

resp.text: Hi Nicolas! Thank you for your feedback and review. We do hope to see you again soon!

name: Rachel Sobke
text: Even my non-karaoke friends have a good time at Voicebox- having your own private room takes away some of the pressure and the drinks (a little pricey) help, too! Be sure to get reservations in advance because it is popular, though I have had luck occasionally calling the day-of

resp.text: Thanks Rachel! Yes, advanced reservations is certainly recommended! Hope to see you again soon!

name: Jessica
text: Place is tons of fun! Each group gets their own karaoke booth and a server stops be frequently to get drink orders and drop them off. A good night out for sure!

resp.text: Thanks Jessica for the kudos! We hope to see you again soon.

name: Elizabeth
text: The food was delicious and the selection of songs was fantastic. Wish our server had been a little more attentive, but overall we had a great time!

resp.text: Thank you Scarlet for that feedback! We hope to see you again soon and bring our A-game for service!

text: Very friendly, check up on you every few minutes,  great selection of songs

Other than that it was great.

text: I have been here twice now, both times for work outings. So much fun. We had a private room for karoeke. The song list is diverse. The app made things super easy to manage. The apps were tasty. The drinks were excellent and fairly priced. Parking is a little tricky so plan ahead.

text:
I came here with a friend for a celebrity meet and greet that was planned here, so I didn’t have the normal experience of coming with a big group of friends.

That said, it was a great place! You can order food from Parkburger through their waitstaff (and it arrived very quickly), you just have to check out for food separately from any bar orders. The food was good and they had a good bar as well. It wasn’t cheap, but it was more reasonable than I expected for downtown Denver

I liked having the private rooms, the room we had was comfortably large. The wait staff tried not to interrupt too much, but they did check in periodically and brought the orders quickly. The karaoke queue was pretty easy to figure out on your phones (maybe bring a back up charger if you have an older phone though). The song selection was pretty comprehensive as well.

resp.text: Thanks Kelly for your thorough feedback! This is exactly what we hope for our guests to experience! We hope to see you again soon!

We are in the office to assist you between 10:00AM-6:00PM weekdays and 12:00PM- 3:00PM on weekends. If you reach our voicemail while we are assisting another guest, just let us know what a good time to call you back is. We are looking forward to solving this issue for you. Thanks!

name: Krissy Chacon
text:
I don't know where to begin. The place was really clean. The bar was well kept, the floors looked tidy, and the room was very clean (nothing, not the seats or microphones, was sticky, which was a huge surprise to me). The service was amazing. The attendants came in frequently enough to get us more food and drinks and didn't interrupt what we were doing in the meantime - just a quick in and out. They made sure that our water pitcher stayed full and got us anything we needed.
The setup for music was really convenient. You use a website on your phone to select the music with a room code meaning that everyone in the room could choose music whenever they wanted and you didn't have to sit at a machine and take turns.  You can also adjust the lighting via the app. The odds also a lot of space in the room - we had 14 people and it didn't feel too crowded.
All in all it was a clean place with amazing service, good atmosphere and seemed dedicated to convenience.

resp.text: Thank you Krissy! This awesome feedback! This is exactly what we hope all our guests experience! If you would like to share specifics about the day you came in or the suite you were in, please feel free to shoot us a note at info@voiceboxkaraoke.com. We hope to see you again soon!

We do understand that you may not be used to the "grease" on pizza.  Please keep in mind that this comes from the naturally occurring fats in the cheese and meats we use. name: Steve Brightman
text: Absolutely useless restaurant.  1.5 hour delivery time.  Over 1 hour for pick up.  Super easy solution: go somewhere else.

resp.text:
Hi Steve, we are sorry to hear about your wait time.  While it makes us sad to hear that you probably wont be returning to our restaurant, we hope that you keep in mind why we have a long wait time (during peak business hours) in the first place.

At Anthony's Pizza & Pasta we make every one of our pizzas by hand, using fresh, simple ingredients and we have done it this way since 1984.  This takes time and we believe that this is what sets us apart from our competitors and creates a demand for our real, thin crust, pizza that we are so passionate about making every day.  During peak business hours, there is sometimes an increased demand for our pizza. Just as it is with any restaurant that makes amazing food, wait times are inevitably going to increase.

So while we do understand that waiting over an hour for a pizza might not be ideal for you, we would say that you can always plan ahead and order online ahead of time, so you can receive your pizza when you would like it (even during peak business hours).

Thanks for taking the time to provide us with the details of your experience and if there is ever anything that we can do to invite you back into our restaurant, please reach out to us directly at info@anthonyspizzaandpasta.com and we will do our best to win you back.

text: Food and service are both usually so-so.  It is convenient if you are on campus, but it is definitely not something worth making a trip for if you do not happen to already be of the Anschutz Medical Campus.  It is bar food, and that is probably the beat you can say.  It is not great, and it is not terrible.

name: Concerned Citizen
text:
First, the service was amazing. Stephanie was kind and knowledgeable.

I order the triple play slider sliders. The buns were super soggy and gross with the cold slaw liquid and pickle juice. It would have been nice to have been warned about those ingredients and maybe I wouldn’t have gotten them. The pulled pork had a large chuck of gristle in it and, while normal, kind of unappetizing.

Frys were kind of soft as well but better than most places.

name: Nick Magles
text: Service is generally good, food is just okay, would probably be a better hangout spot if it was more affordably priced.

name: David McCollough
text: We had a great lunch on our first visit after a long tiring day at the VA hospital. The burgers were cooked perfectly and the sweet potato fries were awesome! They have a great rotating selection of craft beer on draft as well as many in bottles and cans. Their list of other liquors is impressive too. The waitstaff are very attentive and kind. CCP also owns Ursula Brewery which across the road about 25 yards... we’ll try it next time, because we will be back!

text: Food was good and service was excellent. Atmosphere was comfortable.

name: Kelly Pearce
text: Cedar Pub Creek is a great location for the UC campus employees, students and locals. Decent selection of draft beer and bottled familiars. They have a wide assortment of food choices from a Cubano to Gyros, salads and apps. All their food has been consistently good and service is always spot on. If in the area, I definitely recommend Cedar Creek for a leisurely lunch and a beer.

Would highly recommend, I know we'll be coming back for sure.

We had about 10-12 people. We are all combat veterans, veterans, and people who work with veterans. The server treated us amazing. He was fast with our drinks and kept us up to date on the status of our food.

I will definitely going back.

name: Mig Migs
text:
• Want that hometown pub feel?
• Like a variety of tap beer swapped out regularly?
• Enjoy a versatile selection of comfort food along with salads?

Then try Ceder Creek Pub! The service is great, the staff is aways willing to help. This place draws a majority of its business from the campus.

*Side-note: Students, staff, if your party is over 6, it's a common courtesy to call ahead to the business and give them a heads up you are coming. If you'd like to split checks, tell them up front, and give them your name as you order so that it's easy to tally the split checks by name at the end.

Let's face it, everyone looks the same in blue scrubs ;)

name: Kevin Anderson

name: Dalton Wright
text: Overall this is a pretty nifty little pub to grab a beer and some food around Anschutz campus. The food is good and the beer is cold. Although it won't make you stop what you're doing and write all of your friends to tell them how incredible it is, it's niche enough and cozy enough to feel warm and inviting. And I think that's what the intentions were when designing this place.

text: Food is like any McDonald's, however, I've been here a couple times and they have forgotten to give me our happy meals drinks a few times, they forget to discount after I have given them a coupon but most of them have been friendly. There was only one time when an older lady (manager maybe?) Was extremely rude. We were dining in once and  my husband asked her for ranch and she gave him ONE... it was four of us eating. Then I got up and asked her for more and she said she had already given some to my husband. How dare she?! So I asked ok? Can I get more??? Then she said she would have to charge me (OK?!) That would have been completely fine, it's only a few cents, but her attitude was uncalled for. I have to admit I always very upset at this point but I said OK charge it so she did, she took my money and pretty much threw the change on the counter (literally, the coins were all over the counter) and just as I was about to say something (again, I was not happy at all) she turned around and left me talking. Believe me I do not like to cause problems but I can't stand people being this rude. I understand people have bad days but if you can't do customer service stay in the back. I wish I could remember her name, if I see her again I will be sure to update my review.

text: This is one of the better little Caesars around here, they make great pizzas and don't skimp on toppings. Also, the pizza portal is wonderful. name: Chuck Henry
text:
Little Ceasars Colfax and Havana.
The place advertises "hot & ready" pepperoni pizza. What a crock. 7:45 PM on a weeknight.  Lady behind the counter says 30 minute wait. Place seems very disorganized.  One of the other customers mentioned that she was going to Pizza Hut rather than wait,  while another said he was going to order his online.  I took his advice. I ordered a large 2 topping pizza for pickup at a Pizza Hut only a couple miles away for $7.99. It only took a couple minutes.
End of story: I got a better pizza for nearly the same price and was home eating it in less time than it would have took waiting at this pathetic Little Ceasars. I'll never waste my time there again. I found out that Pizza Hut has much better pizza anyway.

text: Very friendly, staff knows the orders of campus regulars by heart. It's a Subway, so you know what to expect food wise, but from a customer service perspective it's great.

text: The worst quality. Brown lettuce consistently. Tomatoes rarely ripe. Long stems of banana peppers on my sandwich. Sometimes I feel like they have to be joking trying to put that onto a sandwich they expect someone to eat.

The Indian woman at the counter is OUT OF CONTROL RUDE. She has zero tolerance for the customers and questions. When asking what toppings I wanted she rudely stated “slow down, I hear you I’m doing it!”
Really?! I’m just trying to get toppings for my sandwich. She stopped me short of finishing my order and I just took what I could get out of her. I asked her not to be rude. She didn’t say thank you or have a good day.

Will not be going back. The good news is their is a Jimmy John's next door.

text:
The sandwhich tasted good. I liked it. Maybe a little smaller than other subways. But big enough.
I did not like that they do not accept coupons from the newspaper. And they also do not accept coupons that are texted to me from subway themselves.
I get text from corporate Subway all the time. And not all subways accept them. The subway inside Vegas resort, the airport subways,  and this one, do not accept these coupons.. booo!

name: Ken Hipkens
text:
BAD CUSTOMER SERVICE
I am a traveler to the children's hospital. The sandwich was made according to my request but when ask if they could wrap the sandwich in two wrapper I was told NO. I explain it was for a child in the hospital and still wouldn't do it. Then she asked if I wanted a combo and my answer of course was NO. An on campus facility with no heart, I won't return.

text:
Friendly people but terribly trained. Trying to ask for extra tomatoes or extra mayonnaise or extra anything or for more than two napkins is impossible here.
The staff are all trained not give extra anything. Ridiculous.

text: Worst Subway I've ever been in. I ordered a footlong an asked if they could wrap each 6" separate. I wanted to eat half now an the other half later. The Indian woman had the nerve to say it was against policy to wrap my footlong separately. I was in shock! I asked why was this a policy? Her response was because people try to get over and share the footlong instead of buying (2) 6". I felt as if I was being bullied. She was trying to control how I recieved a product that I am paying for. Out of all the Subway shops I have purchased from, they've never said some crazy shyt with a f@#k excuses like this one.

text: I normally go to a taqueria 3 times before a review to be fair. The food here is good and the place is very clean. The staff is friendly and helpful. The only issue I had was the limited menu and limited drinks available, but evaluating them on what they have available for sales I would give them 5 stars.

name: Ben Williams
text:
It's hard to find a truly authentic Mexican restaurant in the area and this place is just that. Everything is homemade, including the horchata. You can just taste that the food was made from fresh ingredients, and trust me, it is delicious!

Friendly serviceand very clean restaurant, I recommend this place to anyone looking for delicious authentic tacos and burritos!

This place is amazing. Just ask and Ana (owner) and Josefina will make your meal just the way you like it. Very kind and they treat you like family.. The food is amazing!! 👏 👏👏
I will definately be back over and over.

text: The service was friendly and inclusive. The food was fresh and tasted great. Notably fresh to say the least. Not the cheapest but worth it for sure. They made a point to state that everything is homemade. You can tell and I would definitely recommend it.

Everything they make is fresh and the quality is consistent. The staff will literally go out of the way for their customers. The prices are not expensive either. This is now one of my favorite places in CO.

name: Cameron Bryant
text: MUST TRY. The atmosphere is wonderful and the music is at the perfect level. Possibly one of the best burritos I've had. Will definitely become a regular.

Locally owned and operated, she also does deals for students being as how it's right across the street from Skyview High School the only gripe is I wish it was open longer :-) it has very reasonable hours, I'm just a night owl 😊

text: Have had their breakfast burritos and they are DELICIOUS! These are giant burritos jam packed with all the good stuff! Chorizo that is perfectly crispy,  nice soft potatoes and eggs that are cooked up nice and fresh for you! The lady that was in there when I went was super friendly and reminded me of my favorite tias!  Stop in for some food when you can and enjoy that home cooked taste!

Peruvian decorated Mexican restaurant?? .. Will NOT BE COMING BACK.

text:
The staff is great but the food needs a little work had breakfast enchiladas and eggs over easy green chili was tasteless and loaded with cheese no spice to it at all real sad after reading all the reviews on how great the Mexican food was. This plate was three corn tortillas smotherd with this so called green chili and lettuce tomato and a glob of sour cream cup of coffee 12 bucks .
Sorry but I won't be able to return to this restaurant.

text: Food was good the place is a little run down they have the seats taped up. It smells like they haven't opened a window or a door to get some fresh air in. Service was good but slow the hostess was helping the waiter and there wasn't even that many people in there. They where all friendly.

name: MotoXMom3
text: TRY THE LEMONADE!!! IT'S AWESOME!! The food is excellent and time after time that I've eaten here I always get the same, high quality, great tasting food and exceptional service. I love Lupita's Resturant. They are one of the few places that make Aurora great.

name: Anne Dann
text: I love Lupita's!  They have a wide variety of food and drinks and the waiter Victor is fantastic!  He's always friendly.

name: Sherri Daily
text: My family has been eating at Lupitas for over 10 years. Not only is the food delicious, but the service is awesome. Every family member or employee we've meet over the years have been great at what they do. Betty (owner) is such a lovely woman, she is kind, generous and a very hard worker. We highly recommend supporting local businesses, especially the kind that care for their community and do what they can to support it.

name: Matt Denman
text:
Delicious food that comes out fast and hot. Always get our to go orders correct too.
Very nice people work here.

name: Sandy Anderson
text: Awesome people, yummy food and a great band. Very enjoyable time. I would definitely recommend this place to anyone.

name: Austin Doby
text: Won't be going back. I was served the wrong meal and they didn't seem to get that I wanted it fixed. They said that this was better. Maybe, but it wasn't wat I wanted. I was offered desert and I though that maybe that was how they were going to make up for it, but I was charged for it. The food was mediocre and not well made. When I paid the bill, the server took 15 min to get me the receipt.

name: crooked truth83
text: I should have listened to the bad reviews. I love Mexican food but I was so disappointed. The beef tasted really funny and was really watery. It was kind of gross. And they charged for sour cream even though we didn't ask for it and the menu said it came with the burritos. I typically don't write food reviews but I was really disappointed. You could get better Mexican anywhere in Denver including Taco Bell.

name: Deirdre M
text: Delicious food, great service, family friendly diner. Wheel chair access, centrally located, well established restaurant, free parking. Weekends offer live classic country.

name: Anne Dann
text: I love Lupita's!  They have a wide variety of food and drinks and the waiter Victor is fantastic!  He's always friendly.

name: Julie Fleiser
text: Simply as good as Mexican food gets! The service is fast and friendly, so no need to eat fast food if you are on your lunch break. Try it all! Not a single bad choice on the menu!

text: Lupitas is the best Mexican restaurant on East Colfax. She's in danger of shutting down. I hope we can all support her and try to keep this place open

text: Great place to eat. Breakfast lunch and diner this place has love music in the weekends. The workers are so pleasant and friendly. The owner Lupita is always working, smiling and conversing with her customers.

text: Family owned restraunt with great food and dedicated service! This is a place where you go for the food and home like feel and mitt for the avaince. Prices are very reasonable for the quality of food provided!  Always a wonderful experience when dining here!

text: Simply as good as Mexican food gets! The service is fast and friendly, so no need to eat fast food if you are on your lunch break. Try it all! Not a single bad choice on the menu!

name: Michael Schneider
text: I mean it's ok I wish I would have taken pic but... had a New York strip torta which I take pride in finding the best around for I got a literally steak on a roll very tough for a strip also had shredded beef burrito smothered green which I liked okay and chicken enchiladas which were packed and pretty decent but the torta can definitely use improvement it was okay  I have family that loves it just tonight was nothing like they were used to but might just have been a bad night or something

text: This is a wonderful little spot 2 eat every once in awhile take my family there the other day the food is consistent the owner is great she takes great care of her customers along with the staff

name: Shaniedia Carroll
text: Betty has the absolute best homemade Mexican food, I hope she keeps this place 🤞🤞🤞 fingers crossed.

name: John McQuaide
text: Nice restaurant. Good food and they have a band on Friday nights.

name: Johnny Nunez
text: It was great love the food and respect the people that work awesome place to go eat.

name: Donna Porter
text: Everyday is a good day to visit Lupita's. Besides the good food and live entertainment on Friday's the have some awesome Margaritas!!!  I'm a repeat customer.

text: This is my favorite Mexican restaurant!  Great food, wonderful service.

name: Alicia Burrough
text: The service was really very good.  We ordered a Smothered Burrito, a Cheese Enchilada, and a Chile Rellano, with a Michelada to drink.  The food was good but not great.  The only thing on the table with any kick to it was the Salsa that came with the chips. When I asked for some hot sauce to spice up my Michelada the easier also brought out the spice mix they use for it which was very kind.  My MIL left some important paperwork behind and they saved it for us to pick up the next day, the waiter recognized me and gave it to me right away.

name: Dorian Harding
text: Great food. Just the salsa is too spicy🤷‍♀️

name: Edward Shumate
text: Very good breakfast Burrito. Spacious dining room. Serves alcohol here too.

name: Julio Dominguez
text: Honestly I ended up in this place by accident. First off the place is "authentic" for its food. I didn't take expect it to be that good, the blue corn tortillas from their enchilada is delicious, the rice is not dry at all and their guacamole is good. The Campechana that they offer is delicious as well. Now there music might not be the typical music they play at Mexican restaurant, but there ambience is warm.

name: Josh Keller
text:
Had Sunday morning breakfast.  Was not crowded but a little busy.  They could have used another server as it did take a while to order.
Had a Bloody Mary and Mimosa to start.  They were good but nothing special.
The chicken fried steak was very good as it was well tenderized and the gravy had good taste.  Home fries could have been crispier.  Garden omlet was very good as well.
Price was ok but thought it was a bit much given it was just breakfast and in the neighborhood it is in.
Overall it was a good experience.

name: TihsreeD Lodge
text: Food was great, service was fast and friendly. Live music band set up on the Friday evening of our visit. We ate, waited for Denver traffic to subside and enjoyed the band.

name: Anthony Bustamante
text:
Lupita excellant service and the food is great.
I come here when I come up from Pueblo  and stop in. Never have been disappointed.
Recommend to everyone.

name: William Chin
text: A great place to get a meal and on Friday nites Rudy Grant and his band play country music.

name: Nikki Nev
text: When the food came out it looked so good! My 3 kids and I came in and had different plates.Ended up throwing up and etc. I ordered a Togo plate as well and my husband got sick.Called the manager today and told her mainly to just warn her to throw away whatever steak or whatever. She sounded like she knew exactly what to say,come on people she did because I'm sure people get food poisoning there all the time.Damn lady didnt even offer to refund the two items that made us sick.Bad business especially when there is a customer who has been going there for nearly 15 yrs.I advise you not to take your kids or family members there.its not worth it.It sucks because there really isn't any good restaurants in aurora.keep your distance from this place.

text: The service was great  & the food was stupendous!

My daughter had a chicken quesadilla and I had Mojarra a la Diabla. Both were very good. We finished with their homemade flan which was delicious.

This is a wonderful departure from the chain restaurants that moved into the area and hurt their business. Shop local, shop small and enjoy some awesome food at Lupita's.

text:
Just moved to Denver and this is one of our new favorite joints! Great food, great whiskey selection, friendly staff and awesome Irish food! I'll keep adding photos as we try new things!

Oh, and home to the Liverpool FC of Denver!

And Tuesday night is our staple with $1 tacos! Y'all they are tasty! Who'da thunk an Irish pub could nail such great tacos?! 😍

name: Amy S
text:
Casual American/Irish pub food, with a big and inexpensive drink menu. The food is good, reliable and tasty. The desserts are a surprise hit, the bread pudding is outstanding and the brownie very chocolatey and delicious.

Service is solid even when they are packed, and with the reasonable prices you could easily hang out all night without spending a fortune. We went for trivia with Geeks Who Drink on Wednesday night, and had a blast.

name: Joey Lynch
text: The Abbey is a lovely neighborhood establishment with an even lovelier staff. Every time we're there, Sara and Raina treat us with the utmost love and a welcoming attitude. Grateful to have such a gem right near our back yard!

text: Sarah was fantastic! Such a great personality! I've never laughed so hard!

name: John Stegman
text: The Abbey Tavern is a great local Irish bar. With its amazing Irish food and drink selections this is a great place to come with friends and family. If you like soccer ‘football’ the atmosphere here during big games is lively and full of fun. My favorite menus item are the scotch eggs but everything I have had here has been good. On tuesdays they have a $1 taco night from 7-10pm this is also a great deal and one of the things I love about this place.

text: Just discovered. Possibly the best AND worst place to watch live European football.

name: Luis Canales
text: Been wanting to check this place out since I moved to Colorado and finally got the chance a couple weeks ago. Been coming to every Liverpool game for the Champions League and it's one of my favorite places in Denver! They'll open 30 mins before every Liverpool match even if they start at 5:30 am! (Premier League times). If you like football, this place carries a friendly and warm atmosphere during games. Their staff works in incredible fashion during games to make everyone's experience the best. It can be hectic but they're all awesome. Reina, is an excellent server with incredible energy and organizational skills! They got booths and pub sitting areas, and the food is awesome. The decor is very classy with rocks, dark woods, and whiskey barrels around. Very casual and friendly.

name: Liz Fox
text: If you're a soccer fan this is the place to be. Beautiful service and real friendly people.  A great time the food is good too!

text: This place doesn't look all that exciting from the outside, but when you walk in it's a whole other story! Decor is updated but still casual, definitely has the casual sports bar theme without being kitschy (separate from all the Irish themed items.) Lots of TVs for watching the game, UK-style beers on tap, and a surprisingly good menu for dinner. Their brunch also looks delicious! We will definitely be back again.

Great atmosphere, too much Liverpool love for my taste (although Love the Steven Gerrard respect), regardless if you are within a mile and need a place to eat or drink, Abbey is your spot with great service and ambiance. Thank you for being authentic.

name: Chris Yenter
text: I'm a Liverpool fan so I'm probably a bit biased.  The experience is great but you better get here early if it's a big game.  We were here for the championship game last year and the United game this year.  We had to wait in line for the first and we were there an hour early.  We got there right after opening for the second game and we had to stand so if you want a seat you may want to pitch a tent the night before.  Other than that the crowd was great and the beer and food were flowing just fine.  YNWA.

text: Great staff, so much fun watching Liverpool games.

name: Ben Schumacher
text: Great atmosphere, great wait staff, and great beer selection. Always a selection of games on many TVs and if soccer is on, it will probably be playing here. This time of year, it seems a lot of basketball is playing, too. About half the food I've had here has been below par, but I keep coming back for the other reasons. Some of the food is good for tavern food, at least.

name: Alex Miller
text: Nice atmosphere, huge patio, far enough off Colfax to enjoy the outside.

name: Chris Mospaw
text:
Great place to hang out for a while and very good food. The menu is a little limited and focuses on Irish-themed or Irish-fused bar foods, with a few items that are outside that theme. Ingredients are fresh and the food is  delicious. Service is excellent and even tolerated me sitting there with friends for 2 or 3 hours while sipping iced tea instead of alcoholic drinks. (I did tip accordingly.)

The patio has some shade and umbrellas. The inside is very dark. Parking can be a bit of a challenge, especially with the ice cream place next door sharing parking. If I lived closer, this would be my hangout.

name: mb mackman
text: Great place to watch a Liverpool game. Awesome atmosphere, people singing Liverpool songs the whole time. Just don't wear the opposing team's jersey like me or you'll get the Who Are You chants.

The only thing that was edible was the dinner salad. My company and i dined about 5 pm so we were the only diners at the time so the service was timely and acceptable, the place was quite however the food left a bad taste in my mouth. I had high hopes for this place but was actually a  complete waste of my money because the food was  undercooked and frankly not edible and I was unable to eat what i ordered and I left the plate mostly uneaten. name: Alan Loo
text:
Went on the recommendation of a friend.  He told me "You will not leave here hungry. My friend was right. A good breakfast, lunch and dinner. This places offers anything from Omelettes, Poached Eggs, Mexican breakfast favorites, Breakfast Burritos, Pancakes, Waffles, Soups, Appitiezers, Greek Platters, Gyros, Salads, Sandwiches, Burgers, Burritos, BBQ Ribs, Beef, Chicken, Tacos, Shrimp, Fish, Desserts, Breakfast, Steak and Eggs, and Skillets. A six page menu of entres. I ordered the Lemon  Butter Fish and Shrimp, it came with a salad, rice, vegatables, fish and shrimp. Also had an Arnold Palmer, and toast. Large portions, friendly service, and delicious food.,  Also a cheesecake for dessert. No complaints here. I have to say this is one of the best diners in Denver with its vast array of food. Thank You for opening your restaurant in Aurora. You're  a destination in Aurora and East Colfax. An awesome place to come to after church or to celebrate . I will come to try the rest of your diverse menu.

Went back there had the BBQ Chicken & Ribs. Delicious. Again I didn't leave this place hungry. Friendly service, great food. The Omelette is a nice restaurant to bring your family or date.

The last few times that I've been to this restaurant food tasted bland.

resp.text: Thank you for the feedback and we are happy that you enjoyed the food. We will continue to maintain and raise our standards and hope to keep earning your business. Also if you decide to come back more often ask any if our waitresses about our rewards program that offers you a free meal after ten visits!

name: Alex Myers
text:
BEST ESPRESSO IN DENVER!!!

I've lived the dream, tried every offering in this city: Starbucks, Ink!, Daz Bog, Peet's, Caribou, Allegro, Dunkin Donuts

and bar none---this espresso, even a solo will wire you for sound, turn the volume up, and keep your subwoofer kicking for at least an 8 hour kick

You can't find more efficiently caffeinated espresso in the city that delivers such a bang for your buck---I've been all over, I've tried!

Finally, I've never had anything at this coffee shop / deli that I didn't like.  But if you're searching for worthy espresso, this is where you get it---no substitutions.

name: Blaine Liming
text: Went to this coffee shop on Friday morning 4/27/18 around 9 am. I was standing there waiting for my friends to pick up their order and was observing the staff.  Coming from a huge customer service background I was disappointed.  None of the staff smiled at all.  A gentleman at the check out counter said..."next please" the next in line was talking with a co-worker and didn't hear...honest mistake.  He only had to repeat himself 1 more time and I hear him say not under his breath...."Jesus Christ pay attention" which the customer did not hear...but I did.  My friend was paying and another lady at the counter asked do you need anything else?  My friend didn't hear her.....she rudely makes her voice louder and says.....DO YOU NEED ANYTHING ELSE?  He said no that is it.  He goes to hand her his card....instead of asking him to use the machine to use the chip...she rudely points to the side as though he should have already known.  The only person to walk by and say hi....the manager or someone in a suit.  I understand....you are a busy coffee shop....but take the time and smile and have fun.  Remember because you work inside a hotel it looks like you are representing both companies.

text: This place is a coffee inside one of the hotels. I actually won a raffle and got a $5 Peet's Coffee card. Although I was pretty psyched about it, I asked myself what in the world will I buy with just 5 bucks. Oh well i said, went in there and looked around and saw some pastries but then I decided to settle for their parfait. It was about $3.85 plux tax. I bought it, taste it and I love it! Happy with my choice, I left the shop smiling. Go check out Peet's Coffee. It's right in Downtown. Great place to grab a quick bite from if you're in a rush.

name: John Victor “JV” Ubana
text: The Peet's coffee, which is franchised by the Sheraton management made mistake on charging us.  We've paid with a $20 gift card and wanted to pay the balance of about $2 using our credit card... Instead they charged $20 on our gift card and another $20 on our credit card.  The UNFRIENDLY and RUDE staff told us that the credit will clear and that they will waive the $2 for the inconveniences.  We didn't sign the receipt just in case.  A month after this event, Sheraton charged our card $8.  Not being petty about the $8, but what Sheraton did was very DISHONEST.  Also they LIED about waiving the $2 and charged something that does not make sense.  If they can't be trusted with the small amount, I will not trust them with anything more. The customers service is way beyond poor and their finance department are THIEVES and will charge you something that is not signed nor agreed upon.

name: Damion Wright
text:
This is my sisters local watering hole, I decided to hang out with her one night and I must say, if you are faint of heart I would suggest you don't go to this place. You definitely have your locals that live in the area that go there, who are there aren't bad at all, however; the service is what you would expect from the likes of the line cooks at your county jail. I went to the bar to buy a couple rounds of drinks and didn't get one "thank you" or one "smile." These things go a long way in an establishment as such.

One positive, the drinks are STRONG AS HELL!!! I can say the $25 I spent there would have been at least double at your local chain restaurant for happy hour.

Will I go back? If my sister blindfolds me and puts handcuffs on me and holds me for ransom. Otherwise, my vehicle will travel just above the speed limit on Montview and zoom right past the Montview Bar and Grill.

name: Chrissy D
text:
Best pizza in Denver. They might have the best gluten-free pizza in the country. I travel a lot, I’m allergic to gluten, and I LOVE pizza. This is the only place I’ve ever been to that has gluten-free crust that doesn’t taste like paper, isn’t gluey, and has a wonderful texture AND flavor. This is also the last restaurant I ate in before lockdown and I hate it that I haven’t been able to dine-in for over a year (due to health reasons). Their order pick-up area is well used by us now! If you’re able to eat inside right now—their bar is awesome, they have great drink specials, and their salads are divine as well. I’m ashamed I don’t have any photos of the food, but the moment our order would land on the table the last thing I thought about was taking a photo. Walter’s is fantastic!

Review Update: Finally am fully vaccinated so we ate inside tonight! Food is still fantastic, beer & cider awesome, and Jonathan was server perfection as always. New photo added!

name: P L
text: Fast, friendly, and quality pizza. Very happy with my Greek thin crust, tasty crust and toppings. Wings were big and juicy. Got the dry rub and wanted them to be crispier so I popped them in the air fryer, then they were perfect.

text: My favorite place. Always a great selection of craft beers. Mostly known for their pizza, which is well deserved. You can also get great sandwiches. But don't overlook their calzones. Fantastic service every time I'm in.

text: This is our favorite local pizza joint, especially if you’re looking for a good gluten-free crust. The Carolina barbecue wings are out of this world and the cocktails and service are great.

text: Delicious pizza, great local craft beer list, good music, and friendly vibe during these weird times. Yeah, those are pickles. This house special is insanely good. I’ll be back soon!

text: We ordered right from their window - the staff was extremely helpful and friendly in assisting with navigating the ordering process considering the COVID set-up. We were able to eat at a few tables outside nearby. The pizza was awesome. Definitely recommend “The Moses”.

text: Amazing food and service! Great tap list. Got the kicking bourbon wings and a deep dish mile high meat pizza. Only complaints- wish the pizza was way more deep dish, felt more like a pan to me (I think it's also just really hard to find legit deep dish out here) and the place was a bit full of kids on a Saturday evening. To be fair, I'm sure that goes down around 9 or 10 and we were there a bit earlier. Will definitely be back, excited for this new local spot!!

text: Keep up the great work at this location! The gluten-free pizza crust is amazing. Amazing! They've got honey for the edges upon request. We've been regulars for the Avalanche games, because they're accommodating to getting the game onto a TV for us. The only tiny downside is they close at 9pm so we're often not able to finish the Avalanche game at their restaurant.

resp.text: Thank you for your review, Christopher! We look forward to rooting for the Avs with you the next time you are in!

resp.text: Hey Christine! Your words are music to my ears. We look forward to serving you again soon. Cheers!

name: Barb Riley
text: Every. Single. Dish. Contains chili  flakes. Even the veggie lasagna (I avoided the spicy sausage in the meat lasagna.) For old grandmas or young grandkids who don't do spice, this isn't the place to go.

resp.text: Hi Barb,  thank you for letting us know your thoughts.  While we certainly like a little kick in our homemade marinara. We have multiple sauce options that have no chili flakes. I would try our Garlic Olive Oil sauce, or Garlic Ranch Sauce.  Also we have a Pesto Marinara sauce that is very mild.  One of my favorite pizzas is The Greek - Garlic Olive Oil sauce, Mozzarella, Spinach, Sun-Dried Tomatoes, Artichoke, Fresh Garlic and Feta Cheese... It's absolutely delicious and not a Chili Flake in Sight.

Their sausage is SPICY, so watch out for that if you don’t do heat.

text: This pho is simply the best. I have been to a lot of them and by far this is the best. The broth is to die for and there is no one in this neighborhood that i would got to. And the price is screaming good.

text: Broth was good not great, same with the dumplings on special. The tripe in my pho was perfectly cooked, and the mango jelly smoothie was pretty awesome. Spent $20 on just myself so everything should have been as good as the tripe and the smoothie.

text: Omg...This is by far the best burgur I've ever had. I hardly speak english let alone Spanish (Correctly) but the menu said (best I could translate) Warez Style hamburger. I wouldn't buy a hamburger from any place but tacos menny, unless it was after hours, for the rest of my days. It was a flavor filled burger. At least one bite contained the best flavor of the best hotdog. Let alone the best burger, I have ever tasted in my life. As a single guy that works, lives on the road. I prommise...you can live off this resturaunts burger. Order the hamburgerosa esrilla warez /w papas ( I think I spelled that wrong) and you won't be dissapointed. That being said...no Trucker parking, but right off I-25. You can make it with a left and a right without a jacknife. I'25.and 84th. They have a laundry mat, convienence store and retraunt in the same parking lot. Omg...try thier hamburgers. And there tommales. And steak smotheresd burritos.

name: Buster Douglas
text: I walked in at 4pm on a tuesday to get pastor tacos. The only person there was a woman sitting in the dining area watching tv who didnt acknowledge me, but definitely worked there. No problem. I said hi and tried to order. She looked up at me and said "no ingles". I said "quatro pastor tacos" and she just looked at me. I said it again with the same result. So I said "tu no comprende quatro pastor tacos?" and she looked at me, clearly just not wanting to take my order. It was a really bizarre interaction and I could tell she knew exactly what I was saying... Im just a regular guy in khakis and a sweatshirt, I dont understand why she would refuse me service.  Their tacos are good, but not great. Not worth that level of insult. I wont be back.

name: Justin Neustadter
text:
Great little dessert/cupcake spot that's very reasonably priced! The staff is really friendly and welcoming.

I went for the three.mini cupcakes (red velvet, nutella, and peanut butter chocolate). Red velvet is my recommendation!

resp.text: Justin! Thank you so much for the sweet note. We appreciate you and your business.

name: Emily Neal
text: I ordered a cake for my sister’s birthday that turned out even better than I expected! The cake and the icing were both perfect! I got their chocolate covered Oreos for a holiday event that went over so well! They were so good! And lastly my other favorite are the sandwich cookies! They are always delicious and every combo of cookie and icing is better than the last! 10/10 would come here for any baking needs 🥰

resp.text: Emily! We are so honored to have been chosen to bake for your sister's bday! When we exceed expectations we do a little dance! Thank  you!

name: Karly Porter
text:
Yummmmmm!!!!! The cupcakes here are almost too cute to eat, but well worth it!! I'm not usually a cupcake person but these are amazing!! The flavors are really good, and because they are mini, you can justify trying all of them! Red Velvet needs to be at the top of your list! As a red velvet cake connoisseur (because it's literally the best cake ever), this flavor cupcake is incredible!! Plus they have other cute treats which are perfect for last minute gifts!
And you're supporting a small woman owned business! Treat yo' self!

name: Valerie G
text: We were so thrilled with the dessert spread that Yours Truly Cupcake put together for our wedding! Everything was delicious, but the boozy mini cupcakes were an especially big hit with our guests. The vegan and gluten-free options made feeding everyone a breeze. Chloe was so wonderful to work with, from the initial tasting and ordering to the final set up. I would recommend Yours Truly Cupcake to anyone looking for dessert catering or simply a quick cupcake or cookie in RiNo!

name: Erin Slattery
text: Got cake pops from here, they were ok (funfetti and chocolate raspberry) but the banana were honestly one of the worst things I’ve ever tasted in my life. I don’t want to be rude but something seriously has to be changed about the recipe, it was horrible

resp.text: Erin - I am so sorry to hear this. We are going to review this immediately. If you email me at cupcake@yourstrulycupcake.com I will issue you a refund or provide some free desserts. Thank you for letting us know. Truly we can't improve if we don't hear when everything is not right and clearly we missed the mark.

resp.text: Thanks so much for the sweet note, Lisa! We hope you try everything on the menu!

MY ABSOLUTE FAVORITE DESSERT PLACE!!!!
The cakes,cupcakes,cake pops,cookie sandwichs,macaroons etc.They are beyond delicious and they are made fresh along with the buttercream they make in house man🤤🤤🤤If you order from here,whatever the occasion it will be the highlight of the special day.

resp.text: Rayesha! Thank you so much for the sweet note. We are here for you!

resp.text: Cole, darling! You got US though COVID. We appreciate you. xo

resp.text: Lauren, Thanks so much for your sweet review. We are here for you, your friends and families birthday! Boozy cupcakes alllll day long :)

name: brianna archibong
text: Food is mediocre on the best day.  I've been twice and have learned me lesson.  The service was so rude it almost seemed like a joke.  We only came in because the sign outside said on game days ( rockies baseball) its all day happy hour. We then order and at the end we are told we need to show tickets to the game to get the all day game prices.  We say the only reason we came in to eat this half hazard food was bacause of the false ad out front.  The waiter seemed to think it was funny we fell for their trick and was almost mocking that we didn't know better ahead of time.  The best part of the night was this cute little boy walked randomly up to our table and gave us two old tickets from earlier that day and said that he and his mom wernt going back in if we wanted it.  We obviously didn't want the tickets for the game but with that I waived back over our waiter. We showed him our new tickets and he RIPPED  them out of my hands and ran to the back. Never got the tickets that little boy gave to me back and after 30 MORE MIN we got the check with the 8 f-ing dollars off for happy hour and we finally got the hell out of there.

name: Jem Cannu
text:
I go here regularly for lunch as it is across the street from my work. Once I get to the counter, they already know, "half kale ceasar, tossed dressing, no tomatoes and sub cucumbers instead." They always include a random grab of two half slices of their signature breads they make in store. The raisin and jalapeno cheddar are my favorite and am always delighted when I find them with my salad. I love it here because I know they make their foods with the best ingredients, and there are plenty of healthy choices on their menu for whatever mood you are in.

The line moves quickly, I am always greeted with a smile, and depending on how busy they are my order takes anywhere from 3 minutes to 10. For those not wanting to wait, they have a quick grab and go cooler for daily made salads and sandwiches. They also have some freshly baked goodies if you are so inclined. The space is modern and clean, and in the summer months a lot of folks sit outside in the patio area.

text: Last week I needed to do an Amazon return and found this location near my office and did the return.  Very convenient though I had to ask for directions because the hotel lobby is 2 levels and the store is on the lower lobby level.  Today I went there at 7am to do an overnight delivery but the store wasn't open.  I left went to my office and found a FedEx and went there and made the shipment.  I left a VM with the ups store to please call me when they opened so I could go back. It's now 245pm and there has been no call from them.  I'm glad I didn't wait and went to FedEx sooner than later.  So I'm splitting my review between and 1 and 5 and giving them a 3.
