name: David S
text: Fantastic food. Really friendly owners. If you haven’t tried Ethiopian before do yourself a favor and try it today! If you already know you like it then add this place to your list! Delicious and huge portions. Just remember it’s cash only and service can be slow... enjoy the atmosphere and company!

name: Gonzalo Lerner
text: Awesome restaurant run by its owners. The food is amazing! Also, try the honey ethiopian wine. Jut keep in mind that they take only cash and the food takes a while. We waited for 40min.

name: Kingsley Thomas
text: My favorite Ethiopian spot in Denver.  It's starting to get too much recognition though. Great food. Hole in the wall place. Eat with your hands.

name: Jordan
text: This was my first time eating at this location and trying this style of cuisine. I was thoroughly impressed! Everything tasted really good! The only downside was the wait time to get our food (about an hour or so), but it was well worth the wait. I would absolutely come back to this place in the future.

name: Michael Alfaro
text: This place is a little gem owned by the coolest couple.  They are so funny and enjoy talking to you about the food.  I was really impressed since it was my first time eating this food.  Honestly could have completely ordered all the vegan options.  The food is so flavorful and it is definitely made from scratch.  Will have some spices and hints of tart.  So worth it!!

name: Lisa Henkel
text: Absolutely the best Ethiopian food in the Denver metro area. A little "hole-in-the-wall" place; get there when they open, or be prepared to wait-& each table's order is prepared and served in the order it was received. A small (but excellent) kitchen.

name: Rebecca Wahl
text: I recommend the combo plates, this is the vegan one. I also recommend bringing TWO people with you, not one. It’s a huge amount of food. Come with a monstrous appetite. Smoke some cannabis first as an appetite stimulant for bonus points haha!

name: Gabriela Isturiz
text: Fantastic food. The lamb was out of this world. Our food did take 1:15 to come out. We did walk in on a Friday at 7 pm, and the room about 3/4 full, but it was still the longest I’ve ever waited for my food. I would say worth it, but wish I knew how long it was going to take because I was so hungry!

name: Rebecca Green
text: Love the food here. Super delicious Ethiopian. The Wot stew is probably my favorite dish.

name: Sam Ang
text:
Oct 18, 2020 update:
After closing for 3 months, they are back! And as good as ever. Check their facebook for temporary phone#.

OMG. 2 years in Denver and I finally found you. Truly best Ethiopian in town we have tried so far. There other good ones, but not good enough to stick with. At The Ethiopian Restaurant, i would say we can stop looking. This is the place.

Wot stew is spicy. The sides are all delicious, both gomen’s, mesir wot was also really nice.
Injera is tart and soft.

Thank you for being around so long. Since 1985 and going strong because they are the best!!!

As for negative reviews due to slow service. Tell me which Ethiopian place in town doesnt have a long wait. Enjoy your Meta or coffee and your companions. This is worth waiting for.

name: Corey Bangs
text: YASSSS This place is absolutely amazing!!  Looks kind of sketchy, but the food is incredible and reasonably priced.

name: Timmi Lasley
text: I love this place. Don't let the humble decor fool you! The staff is friendly, the food is incredibly good. Heads up, they don't take cards so bring cash!

name: Lee Carroll
text: The best

name: Taryn Olivera
text:
We have eaten at quite a few Ethiopian places in demver, but this is becoming our favorite for a few reasons. 1. The food is excellent. 2. The owner is adorable. He makes all of the food himself when you order it. 3. The restaurant itself is a hole in the wall type place that makes you feel comfortable and welcome.

It is cash only, so be prepared for that, but totally worth it and worth the wait for the food!!

name: tina c
text: Delicious food, very simple setup. A sweet pair of elderly folks ran the whole place. I recommend it to anyone who likes this type of food.

name: Sara Jayne
text: So yummy!! Cash only, so worth it! The owner pours his heart into his food. Tried Ethiopian beer! Food comes in a huge bowl/dish and you eat without hands. Sop up the food between thin pancakes.

name: Sunny Jenkins
text: The best Ethiopian in Denver! Family run restaurant and they are so warm and welcoming. I would recommend this to everyone I know!

name: Brianna Krauser
text: Delicious authentic Ethiopian food, felt like a real homely place. Love eating family style. We shared a 2 veg plates and 2 chicken plates among 3 people and had leftovers.

name: Carrie P
text: Delicious and unique cuisine. Feels very authentic. A great meal for people looking to try something new. We got the shared platter, the chile powder was strong but not overbearing. The lamb was definitely the best. Bring cash because credit cards are not accepted.

name: j a
text: Food is rich, delicious, authentic and modestly-priced. Two things, however (not negatives, you just need to know ahead of time): #1, they are CASH ONLY, and #2, it is not a fast meal. Expect 45 minutes between you order and delivery of the food to your table. Have a beer, relax and anticipate the meal to come.

name: Scott Reed
text: Me and my kids have been coming here for years. They love it, the owner Naguzi (sp?) is so wonderful and nice. The food is very tasty, served family-style. We keep coming back

name: Vikki B
text: I love this place!  The food quality is fantastic.   The wait is worth it!

name: J Brown
text: Dont judge a book by its cover.  Unassuming from the outside (and the inside too), this place has fantastic food and ridiculous portions.  Yes, it will take a while to get your dish in the same way it is the case at most other Ethiopian restaurants, BUT the wait is worth it.  I have tried a few Ethiopian places in town and for my money this is the best one by FAR!!

name: Andee Becker
text:
The food here is amazing. I have been coming here for 20 years.
Be prepared to wait for your food, everything is made to order. Don't show up starving, the wonderful smells of food cooking will make you hangry 😊. This is truly a Mom and Pop restaurant. Pop waits on tables and helps Mom in the kitchen. The Key Wot and Vegetarian special is my favorite!

name: Sid Pink
text: Consistently amazing for 25 years; take your time, soak it all in. Rich savory dishes, some spicy options, good vegetarians and carnivores alike.

name: Akzorz
text:
I had never had anything like this, but I finished it all.  The bread is like sourdough crepes.  Interesting... The food was delicious and the service was good.  The atmosphere was the only thing off, as there was no music and it was very quiet.

Great place to try if you want something different. 🤑

name: Ryan Bocchino
text: 10/10 delicious. Meals cooked to order so be ready to wait, but totally worth it!

name: Ryan Dean Roberson
text: Authentic food, no frills but decent food. The dining area seats 20 or so. The same guy who takes your order also cooks your food. All of our party enjoyed the family style service of this ancient food. This place is worth a stop for anyone willing to try new things.

name: Heeru Chari
text:
Don't go in here- horrible old man who owns the place is just not meant for the hospitality industry.I went in there jonesing for some injera- the prices were really high, the portions very scant and there was a complete lack of seasoning.
The injera was made from a mixture of Teff and wheat flour- not entirely authentic.
The food arrived in 40 minutes- the lentils were just boiled-with some salt- no seasoning, the so called vegetables were boiled within and inch of their lives- ever eaten mushy cabbage?
To add insult to injury, the old man told me that he would charge me for a glass of tap water!
I don't know how this horrible place stays in business- go to any other Ethiopian restaurant and they are good, unfailingly nice and hospitable. This one tho', is a blight. Don't waste your money like I did.

name: Chris Irick
text: Great food, and very good service. We did the “dinner for two people” option, and the red lentils were absolutely delicious. My only grief is the cash-only rule, but there’s plenty of warning here and at the store. A couple ATMs are within walking distance of you need cash.

name: Kalon deLuise
text: We've been coming here since we lived down the street. We don't get back as much as I'd like, but it's always a treat when we do. Friendly staff and always great food.

name: Richard Rew
text: Tasty, simple meals including many Vegetarian selections

name: Andrea Kevin
text: LOVE this place. Family owned for about 50+ years. Best Ethiopian food we have tried (I literally think we have tried them all) in Denver. Don't go here unless you just want good food. Service is at their pace. That is okay by me because it is friendly and right on par with all the other Ethiopian food on that side of town. The atmosphere is authentic, bare bones. Try it!

name: Ben Hernandez
text: Best injera and red spicy lentils. Fantastic vegetarian options as well as meat dishes.  Be ready to wait for your food,  no-one is in a hurry, and it can take close to one hour,  but well worth it.

name: Desiree Marye
text: Been going here for decades.  My parents ate here when I was a child,  and they used to bring a happy meal in for me to eat.  Now 30 years later,  I love the food. The owner is a special guy,  he may seem a little dry but he is simply amazing.  Thank you for all these years Negusi, I hope I came close with the spelling.

name: Christopher Najar
text: This place is amazing. Everything is cooked fresh and with flavorful spices. I'd recommend going with 2 or 3 people since the combination platters let you try a lot of different dishes. If you go alone that is fine too because the entrees are fantastic.

name: Miki Tamura
text: Absolutely delicious! Loved the cubed beef and vegetarian platter! It was extremely tasty and big portions. Plus lots of bread. Couldn't stop eating! Service is great and friendly.

name: Orri Jonsson
text: Food was delicious. Every dish is made to order, so it takes forever to get food here, but if you have the time, it's worth the wait. The personal service really adds to the atmosphere.

name: Russ Schleicher
text: This place was not busy at all. The same guy was there from about ten years ago, last time I went. Food is amazing. Berbere spice for days! Can't wait to go back!

name: Nora Beal
text:
WOW!! Where do I even start?
I order the Oaxaca drink! Delicious!!!!!!!!!!!!
As appetizer we order Maryland crab cakes, and 1/2 dozen oysters!! OUTSTANDING!!!!!!
We split a Caesar salad!

name: Kara Grosse
text: The food was great and they are very sweet but it took over an hour and 45 minutes to get our food and about 45 minutes for drinks, even when we called ahead and made a reservation :/

name: Abigail F
text: Amazing food! Went on a Saturday night and didn't have to wait too long. The portions are big and perfect.

name: Nora Beal
text:
WOW!! Where do I even start?
I order the Oaxaca drink! Delicious!!!!!!!!!!!!
As appetizer we order Maryland crab cakes, and 1/2 dozen oysters!! OUTSTANDING!!!!!!
We split a Caesar salad!

name: Michele “Lady” Ducharme
text:
be prepared to wait...
its worth it. have been coming here for years and we love it Josef is an excellent host and every dish is prepared upon your order.  have never been disappointed with the food.

name: Cat Hindman
text: Excellent food.  Not fast, be prepared to wait for your food. Simple setting, clean.

name: Skyler C
text:
I would give 5 stars but it's cash only and I didn't realize it. Had to go to an ATM and return to pay and got charged $3 for the withdrawal and $5 by my bank. So yeah, there's that to make note of.

But the food is absolutely excellent and I'll say as much.

I'll say this too, I honestly suggest coming when the weather is much cooler than now (posting this in July) bc they do not run the a/c and it's literally cooler outside at that point. Kinda makes it hard to enjoy food when you're eating at 88 degrees + even at 6:30pm. But... Again, I'd come back for the food. Just can't really provide 5 stars bc of the lack of plastic payment and literally not even some fans running to cool the air a tiny bit.

name: Kamel Alboaouh
text: The restaurant looks creepy from outside but once you get inside you feel it is a comfortable place. I think this place would be good to someone who wants to get a break of life and have a new experience other than the conventional restaurants.

name: Nate Waldmann
text: Best Ethiopian in Denver. The combos to share with others are great, but individual dishes are just as delicious. Just remember to bring cash as it's cash only.

name: Isaac Griffin
text: Best Ethiopian food in Denver. Family owned business with a home cooked feel

name: Colleen Bement
text: Wonderful food that is super fun to eat. We were welcomed like friends

name: Nate Waldmann

text: Good food, when it is open. More than once I have tried to meet people there for lunch, and found it closed. There were no hours posted either. It is too bad, because I would love to support them if they could keep regular hours.

name: Isaac Griffin
text: Best Ethiopian food in Denver. Family owned business with a home cooked feel

name: AE MULLIN
text: I think I met Negusie in 1987 or somewhere way back then. When everybody always used to joke about the Ethiopians starving.. well you won't starve here....YUMMY.

name: Nathan Curry
text: Fantastic place. Really nice guy, great food.

name: Shannon Dickey
text: The best Ethiopian food in Denver. The best. All food is made fresh. Very good. Can you can drink here.

name: Kevin O'Hare
text: Literally the BEST tasting Ethiopian food around. The service is kinda slow but totes worth your time!

name: Nathan Curry
text: Fantastic place. Really nice guy, great food.

name: Carmen Toure Lorenzo
text: Best Ethiopian food EVER....I've been going for over 20 years....have had a lot of this fits grin other restaurants but none compare

name: Loomy Bunny
text: This was by far the best Ethiopian restaurant I've ever been to.  Service was a little slow but the quality and quantity of food made up for that 10 times over.

name: William Thompson
text: My family has been coming to this pragmatically-titled restaurant for 30 years. Never once has the food been anything but fantastic and never once has the slightly curmudgeonly owner of this establishment shows any sign of becoming any less curmudgeonly. One can not find better Ethiopian food in Colorado

name: Colin Kleinmann
text: Delish. Bring your friends who will enjoy eating with their hands!!

name: Greer Brown
text: Hands down the best Ethiopian food in Denver!

name: Bess Scully
text: Kind of a hole in the wall serving copious amounts of the best Ethiopian food Denver has to offer. Just amazingly good.

name: veronica broslawik
text: Came in on New Year's Eve, really early around 6pm.. We were not greeted, the waitress seemed quite visibly annoyed that we had walked in. Didn't say much, we sat and waited while she said she was taking care of other tables for about 20 minutes without any communication. She ignored us to the point of awkward. My husband went to the restroom and told us there were no other people in the restaurant. He sat down, 5 minutes later his cousin went to the restroom and they still didn't have any other people or tables or make a move to seat us. Maybe I missed something? I was stoked to try it but I guess I'll find a different place to explore Ethiopian cuisine. Bummer!

name: Jason Cox
text: Tasty hole in the wall with friendly service and good vegan options.

name: IDon'tWannaBeMe1231234
text: Really delicious and really unique! I would Deffently recommend trying!

name: Daniel Preston
text: great food, well priced, and a nice part of the neighborhood. One time we had to leave before our food arrived (our mistake) and they quickly packed everything into a box to take with us.

name: Ethan Bair
text: Ordered take out YEBEG WOT (deliciously and uniquely seasoned lamb). We paid $18 for the dish, but the portion was enough for doing dutch and/or tomorrow's lonely leftovers. All entrees include a side of YATES ALICHA  (yellow split peas), a side of TIMOR GOMEN, (collard green-like cabbage and potatoes), and a large dollop of BERBERE, a surprisingly succulent sauce that compliments the rest of the fare beautifully in tangent with the customary ENJERA, a spongy flatbread that resembles naan. The shop seating is pizza parlor size, 10-20. No delivery.  Saved a little of each food for the next day and everything was still tasty with the exception of the ENJERA, which didn't maintain its initial luster. Food appearance fresh isn't the best, and leftover is worse, but I'll reiterate the splendid savoriness. The only drawback I could discern was that the place is cash only, but I'm sure that will change sometime. Will return.

name: D. Barnette
text: Wonderful food, just remember it's cash only and it's worth the wait

name: john koelling
text: Great food. Friendly service. Good value.

name: Gareth Forshaw
text: Looks a great place, planned our visit on Sunday, was supposed to open at 4:30 but at 5 the sign was still off and door was locked so not sure really, bit disappointing.

name: Traci
text: Honestly, the first time I tried it, I wasn't a fan, but my boyfriend likes it so I went back, and by golly, I really got hooked on the flavors and textures. I don't love eating with my hands (I'm sure they'd give a fork if I asked) but it is fun and different.

name: Graham Molinaro
text: Great food, tried all the lentil varieties, great food on its own. Family owned, great service.

name: Burp Reynolds
text: I'll be honest. It takes a long time to get your food. That said, I will wait two hours for that food, any day of the week.

name: SkAr Brjs
text:
(Translated by Google) It is a quiet, discreet place. The attention of the staff is good, they are attentive and friendly. The food as they say, takes time to be served. The cleanliness of the place is good. The quality of the food, Doro Wot is tested. The dish has mostly acid notes, except for the accompaniment that is based on cabbage and chickpea. Flavors are rare, so you should come prepared for new flavors. The price is moderate, but I think it's worth the experience. Consider an average of $ 20 plus tip per person.

(Original)
Es un lugar tranquilo, discreto. La atención del personal es buena, son atentos y amables. La comida como lo comentan, tarda en ser servida. La limpieza del lugar es buena. La calidad de la comida, se prueba el Doro Wot. El platillo cuenta con notas ácidas en su mayoría, salvo el acompañamiento que es a base de col y garbanzo. Los sabores son poco comunes, por lo que debes venir preparado para sabores nuevos. El precio es moderado, pero creo que vale la pena la experiencia. Considerar un promedio de 20 dólares más propina por persona.

We ordered the nachos as an appetizer and when they were brought out, there were exactly 10 chips with some dry beans and cheese on top arranged on the plate. Who does that? We had to cancel the rest of our order. We didn’t want to see what else was in store for us here.

resp.text: I'm very sorry you had a bad experience. We could have replaced your soda with a bottled soda. We could have made you a fresh lime juice margarita and replaced you appetizer with another item. The food is really good we are on our 4th generation of feeding families. Last thing I want is for someone to leave my establishment unhappy. If you ever give us another try look for the big grey haired guy me. I will make sure your satisfied. Thanks for writing us.

text:
Been going off and on for many years, ever since I was a child and Norma was still alive.  Up until last night the food had been wonderfull and the shreaded beef was the best, never had I been able to find any thing comparable.  Well last night was quite subpar,  the taco I had was ground beef and not the marinated shreaded beef I was costumed to.  My wifez stake was gristally and overshadowed by the Verdi sauce, not green chilli,  the guacamole was also uninspired.
And the prices were alot higher then they should have been.

Norma would not have been pleased with the quality. As it stands that is probibally the last time I return.

Sadly this quality change had to have happened within the last 1 to 1.5 years ago, since I was there a while ago with some co-workers.

resp.text: I'm sorry you did not enjoy your food last night. All recipes are the same as they have been since 1974.  Norma & Nabor have not been in the kitchen for about 20 years now. I know Alfonso would have done anything to make you happy. He was there and regrets not knowing your table was not satisfied. He remains involved in all aspects of the restaurant.

name: Julie Russell
text: Chose the Inn as a place to stay for a Menlo College class reunion on advice of friends. And, were they ever right! Let's start with Krystle who took my phone reservation which involved some specific requests. She was friendly, knowledgeable, and businesslike... including a cell message to me on day of arrival that room was ready for occupancy (which really helped with logistics). The place itself is a standard old El Camino motel that has been very creatively updated. While my room was smallish, it was more loaded with amenities than many five star hotels - microwave, Keurig coffeemaker (with Starbucks pods), refrigerator, iron and board, cool décor, great bed (pillowcases designating soft and firm) and even a welcome from management in the form of a paper airplane. Everything including hot water worked like a charm. Nice complimentary lite breakfast in pleasant facility. The staff were all great, genuinely happy to be there, and pleasantly helpful. It's a small place, priced well and run impeccably... one that I wish could be cloned in all my travels. You can find some more lavish places nearby but not better ones!

name: Eileen Lawrence
text: I was very disappointed because the quality of the bread has gone down.  I bought the blue corn sourdough bread today noticed it looked like something else.  The manager on duty Jeff said the bread was blue cornmeal.  I took it home and sliced the bread open to see no blue cornmeal.   I took a picture of the bread will bring back tomorrow for refund.

resp.text: Hey Eileen, this is Ismael (Owner/Baker). I'm sorry you feel the quality is going down. Believe me when I say we truly work really hard so it is the oposite. My guess is that the guys confused your bread and they just gave you a plain country bread, it can get easily confused. Please bring come back and we'll happily give you another loaf. Again please receive my most sincere apologies for the inconvenience, hopefully we'll make it up to you, and if we do, please consider changing your review, they do really mean a lot these times when everything is online. Hope seeing you soon. Ismael

text: Awesome staff and AMAZING scratch made baked goods. The pastries are delicous and love the international inspiration for all the items. The breads are just as tasty and if you can keep from eating a whole loaf on the way home make awesome toast and sandwiches.

name: Krista Wojciechowski
text:
Reunion is the best bakery in the state of Colorado, hands down. This bread is the only thing keeping me sane during quarantine. They always have a wonderful variety of delicious breads, but recently on the weekends, they've been offering bundles that are so much fun and a welcomed break in the monotony of a covid world.
Recently I purchased a bread and butter flight (!!!! I know!) And they had a memorial weekend package with meat from a local butcher, veggies, pickles and aioli from acorn. I don't care that I can't go anywhere for the holiday, I'm taken away by reunion!  Plus they had brioche buns in the package, which I'm making lobster roll (buns?) with!
Their staff is wonderful and help out in any way they can. They now offer local deliveries too!  I want to be selfish and keep them a secret, but they're too amazing not to share.

resp.text: Krista, thank you so much for taking the time to do this! It has also been a crazy ride for us, so reading this just made our day! Really really grateful!!

name: J Rob
text: My wife and I were enjoying cocktails at the bar right outside he bakery. When all the sudden Ismael shows up the a tray of left over bread/ pastries he was giving away as they closed up shop for the night. My wife picked a piece of sticky bun, and I as I looked over the tray he suggested I try the almond croissant. Oh my goodness, it is by far the best croissant I have ever tasted. Every bite silenced everything around me. It was just me and the croissant. Even minutes after my last bite I was still savoring the flavors hanging on my palate. I immediately jumped up and walked over to the bakery where they were cleaning up for the night,m. I declared to Ismael how amazing it was. His response was short and simple, “I know”, reflecting a man who knows well, with confidence, the craft he brings to the table. Thank you sir for the treat!

name: Collin M
text: I have bought so much bread from this place now. The reason: why would I buy bread anywhere else? This place has the most friendly bakers and the best bread by a mile (no Colorado elevation-based baking pun intended, I swear!). And if you like baked sweets they have so many wonderful and delicious creations. I almost didn't want to write this review because I want all the delicious bread for myself. You're welcome.

This place made me smile and remember where I came from and where I am now. It also made my taste buds very, very happy.

Congrats to the owner! Sigue adelante pana.

name: Jamie Alary
text:
I made an order online but none of the coupon codes I had were working. I placed the order anyways, thinking the store would be able to adjust things on pickup. When got to the store, I asked who appeared to be the manager if   I could use a coupon code because it wouldn't let me online. Before I could finish my sentence, he rudely interrupted me saying, no. When he handed me the pizza's, the code I had been trying to use was on a flyer on top of the pizza. I showed him the flyer and told him it was the same as I had been trying to use, but in a rude tone, he again said no and told me there was nothing he could do.

When placing an online order, it tells you any issues with your order are handled through the store. I received and completed a survey which asked if I wanted to be contacted regarding my rating. I have yet to hear anything after over two weeks. I was hoping someone would have reached out to me so I didn't have to leave a negative review.

name: Daran Thach
text:
New American bistro.  Went for a brunch and three person drag show Saturday.

Service/decor- excellent atmosphere and decorated dining space. Hostess was very congenial.  Brandon at the bar was attentive and welcoming.  5/5

Drink- My friends had the $15 bottomless Mimosa, but I just had the bottomless black coffee.  5/5

Food- I tried a breakfast burger (fresh beef, pimento cheese, over easy egg, and sweet onion) with tater tots.  Although the quantity was conservative, the taste was marvelous and juicy. 5/5

name: Matt Strauch
text: Spectacular food in the Golden Triangle by a family-owned restaurant in a open-kitchen concept work with exceptional Chefs at work.

resp.text: Thank you for the wonderful review!

name: Sterling Greni
text: Great food!  Friendly staff! Chef Catie is the best!

resp.text: Thank you so much for joining us! We are glad you enjoyed the food and atmosphere set by our wonderful staff. We love Chef Catie too! We hope you can come back and join us soon!

name: Alex Wiley
text: Some the best tasting food I have had in Denver. It's really a spectacular place. The menu rotates and there's new things to try which are always delicious. The staff are welcoming and friendly. We like to check out new places all over Denver but this is one of our new regular spots now.

resp.text: Thank you so much!

name: Kirk Patrick
text: Ok, this place was way too fancy for a redneck like me. The staff was great, but did I mention that it was way too fancy for me? I was actually there on a date. We were going to eat somewhere else beforehand, but we decided to hit this place up randomly. It's more formal than what I'm used to, but the staff probably got a good laugh looking at me trying to arrange little spoons and little forks. My date also got a good laugh as well. I guess they weren't expecting a dude to show up in cowboy boots, blue jeans and a polo. Anyways, it was a great new experience.

name: Molly Robinson
text: What a great spot! The service was fantastic, and we loved the food. Overall a wonderful dinner and I'd love to go back!

name: Paula Mery
text: The service was amazing our server was very attentive and thorough.  The rebel farm salad was phenomenal so fresh and the vinaigrette was perfect. The wings were equally good, my only suggestion is to offer wet naps or a moist towel with them lol they're messy!! We had some of sterling sausages that were so delicious and obviously made with love. The wine was so yummy and was refreshing as we sat on the patio and enjoyed the ambiance. We will be back soon cheers to the chefs and owners keep up the good work!!!

resp.text: Hi Paula, thank you for the wonderful review and the great suggestion! We are so glad that you were able to try some of our house favorites, and hope to see you again soon to try more!

name: John Michels
text: Varied and eclectic menu of American style dishes prepared perfectly. This is a relatively new restaurant in Denver, but is staffed with a number of long-term professionals from other Denver landmarks. Service was impeccable, and the food uniformly excellent. I highly recommend Ad Hominem.

resp.text:
Hi John,

Thanks for stopping by for a meal and for your recommendation! We hope to see you back at Ad Hominem soon!

name: Jeff Sunderman
text: So delicious. Such a different type of selection on the menu. Its unique but homestyle a bit too. You gotta try the fried green tomatoes and leave room for desert. The best staff too, they want to make sure you enjoy everything.

resp.text: Hi Jeff, Thanks for stopping by for a meal! We appreciate your kind words and hope that you will be back to visit us soon!

name: GJ Cordeniz
text:
My experience was underwhelming. There would not be a review at all. When Google suggested a review I would have ignored it if it hadn't been for the restroom.
Based off the state of the urinal it hadn't been cleaned in 2 weeks. The was a ring at the bottom of the basin and the top had a layer of dust.
I ordered the chicken. For a $28 plate with a chicken breast and finger potatoes I was underwhelmed by the flavor and presentation.
Being greated by the host felt like our party was more inconvenient. Our server was attentive and polite but not friendly. There was no suggestions or pairing options offered.
Finally the bill came, the waitress offered to split off only one person's tab. The rest was manually split having to calculate tax and forced gratuity manually. Would have been easier to do with split checks.
Overall not impressed and not in a hurry to return anytime soon.

name: Josh & Margaret Weiss
text: What a great addition to the Denver restaurant scene.  The interior is a bit austere, but clean and comfortable.  The service was perfect, attentive without being  overbearing.  The staff has all worked together in the past, and followed the chef to this spot.  And the chef is really the star of the show.  The flavors are bright, the vegetables are just-picked fresh and each component compliments the other.  The recommended wines were both wonderful as well.  I can't recommend this restaurant highly enough.

resp.text: Hi Weiss Family! Thank you so much for your kind words! We are so glad to hear that you enjoyed your food and drinks. Happy to hear that you also got to learn a bit about our staff during your visit as well. We look forward to seeing you again soon!

name: Alex Philipson
text: We had delicious scallops and salmon for dinner, but we're disappointed by the charcuterie board. The salmon was in a delicious coconut milk sauce and the scallops had a great blueberry glaze with them. Overall a great menu.

name: Lisa Foster
text: My family received super -outstanding service on our visit today. We also had the best brunch I've ever had in this state. And that's coming from a Denver native. 😄

resp.text: Hi Lisa, thanks so much for joining us for brunch! We are so glad to hear that we have topped your brunch list! We hope you’ll join us for lunch, dinner, or happy hour one day soon so that you can try some more of our culinary offerings!

name: Beth barta
text: Excellent food. Great service. Good atmosphere. Wish them tremendous success!!

name: Karl Chwe
text: Fancy place, but reasonable prices. My friend and I had dinner, desert and two drinks each for about $90 total. Great service.

resp.text: Hi Karl, Thank you so much for joining us for a meal! One of the aims of Ad Hominem is to maintain a reasonable price point for a meal and drinks, and we are happy that you were able to use that to your advantage! We are glad our staff took such great care of you, and we hope to see you again soon!

name: Peter R.
text: Personable service and good food, with a decent happy hour menu to boot. Great neighborhood restaurant that's a little on the higher end than most in the area.

resp.text: Hi there, Peter. Thanks for dining with us, and of course, for your honest feedback. We're working to lower those prices to make it a more approachable neighborhood haunt. Stop again soon (like, next week) for a new taste!

name: Taryn Olivera
text:
At the end of the day, very underwhelming for a 45 dollar steak. There were parts I couldn’t chew through. I had high hopes for this restaurant. The person I was with ordered a lamb shank which was very delicious. The waitress was adorable and sweet, but we could hear the kitchen staff complaining about customers arriving late although we are very sensitive about staying after close at a restaurant and made sure to leave before close. There were other customers there past close (which is totally rude) but I just sorta wish the kitchen staff would have complained quieter haha.

The restaurant itself is absolutely adorable! I’m just so sad that I spent 45 dollars on an under seasoned steak that was tough and had parts I couldn’t chew through.

resp.text:
Hi Taryn,

We are so sorry to hear that the steak that you ordered was not prepared correctly. We do hope though that your husband enjoyed his lamb! Additionally, we are very sorry that our staff was behaving in that way, as it is not an acceptable standard at Ad Hominem. The Executive Chef has been made aware of both issues and will be looking into them. We do hope that you will come back for another meal soon and give us another chance to elevate your dining experience to what it should have been the first time. Thank you for joining us for this meal, and we hope to see you again soon!

name: Martin Lopez
text: Soup, Entrees were delicious. Service by Ilona was excellent!  Was a little dissapointed in the dessert being the last taste as souffle was surprisingly salty and a little chard on edges.  But will definitely go back.

resp.text: Your feedback means a lot to us, Martin. The souffle remains a work in progress and we strive to get it right the next time you're in. Thanks again for dining with us!

name: Martha Martinez
text: I love heat health food.

name: neil ballensky
text: Justine was great working by herself on a mildly busy sunday night. Good food like normal and great pricing.

name: Zachary Christian
text:
It's Subway-- when I'm needing a quick bite that can just as easily be eaten on site or carried as takeout, this is the location closest to home and that which I frequent the most.

I can't say there's a lot that stands out above any other location, but there are a couple of things; both are rather significant-- though, admittedly, one may apply only to myself...

1.) Employees... The folks here seem to be at least one notch above some of the other locations nearest this one. They're attentive, prompt, and friendly!
2.) As of last week, they once again began carrying Honey Oat bread! This alone will definitely have me stopping by at least twice as often-- guaranteed!

All in all, it's Subway...better than most fast-food; still, however, fast-food.
Solid!

name: Jason Sedillo
text: When you go to Subway you already know what kind if food you are about to get. What makes this location so wonderful is the two workers that always brighten up my day. JoJo and Justine are always so warm and welcoming. These two young ladies always excell in customer service! If it were not for these two spectacular employees I would go to the Subway closer to my house. Thank you Justine and JoJo! Oh yea, and the pesto chibata sandwich was tasty!

name: Michael Rael
text: Stopped in with my daughter for dinner tonight. To my surprise the store was empty. Walked up to the counter, business as usual. Matthew was my "sandwich artist". Well needless to say, Matthew needs lessons in customer service. We were not greeted as we entered the store. When we approached the counter Matthew seemed upset. He did not ask what we would like. He was not asking what kinds of bread.  Slamming things around while refilling product. I went ahead  and started my order. I asked him if he was okay to which he replied in a very argumentative tone, "im fine, why?" I told him he seemed upset and we weren't greeted when we walked in the door. So he decided to argue with me in front of my daughter about not being very friendly. I will not be disrespected by somebody in a service position. We walked out while he was cutting our bread. Bad day or not,  you are not allowed to treat people like that.

name: Neal Rigga TV
text: I've visited this JJ's at least once a week over the last 3 years and 80% of the time I bring my dog since we live a block away and this store is in route of our dog walk. On my most previous visit, I was rudely greeted by a man who shouted "We don't serve dogs here" while standing at the register. I explained as I did above that this was the first time my business was turned away and I explained that my dog is my emotional support animal. The rude employee and his manager Vincentus said if I show them my psychiatrist letter/prescription for my dog which would prove to them that my dog is registered as an emotional support animal, then I'd be able to visit the store with my dog. I returned home to get the document, but something about having to show my private medical records to a sandwich artist just didn't feel right. I recorded the video and captured images to post as proof that this bizarre scenario unfolded in order for me to get a sandwich. Ultimately I had to return a 3rd time that day, due to finding out once I returned home that I was given the wrong sandwich. This was a huge hassle for a sandwich.

name: Jarrod J. Perrott
text:
"Freaky Fast Delivery?!"

Lately it's "Freaky Slow Delivery!"

We've been loyal patrons of this Jimmy Johns location for years. The sandwich quality is always good and fresh. In the past, they have been "freaky fast" when it came to delivery time. We would order and they would literally be delivering our order within 10 minutes.

Unfortunately, as of late it's taken over 30 minutes to receive our orders. It's not a horrible wait time, but if you advertise "freaky fast" it should probably be here within 15 minutes at least. Also, when you order online and pre-pay tip for the delivery person, it's disappointing when it takes 30+ minutes to receive your order.

Just some constructive criticism. Aside from the recent delivery issues we've been happy. Hopefully I can update this review in a positive way in the near future.

resp.text: Please let us know the specifics of your experience so we can look into this. http://bit.ly/JJsFeedback

name: Jake Allen
text: Very flexible. Ordered two Little John's (their cheapest sandwich) with a ton of additions and customizations, then paid with five low-balance gift cards I was trying to get rid of. Thanks for being patient with me, guys!

name: Cole Greenway
text:
Went in 20 mins before close to be told they only had sliced wheat bread left, which I accepted due to it being close to closing time. I gave the cash person very clear instructions that I wanted just meat and cheese on my sandwich. When I got my sandwich, there was mayo on it which I specifically told them to leave off. After I told them about the mix up, they couldn’t even make me the correct sandwich because they had no more bread. I wasn’t offered anything in the future to make up for it, so I practically wasted $11. Wouldn’t recommend going here within an hour before closing because they seemed like they could only focus on shutting the store down.

At least I got to give the sandwich to some homeless guys, so it didn’t completely go to waste.

name: Reed Kremer
text: I got very sick from a sandwich at this location, let them know, and wasn’t even offered an apology. Dangerous place to eat.

text:
**Update: The store manager reached out to me personally and not only assured me that we would discuss the issues with his team, but then sent me a free lunch. Very impressed with how fast I received a response and what he did to make sure I was satisfied.**

Tried to order online but their website does not have an option to use cash and that is all I had on this particular day.  No big deal, I called the store.  The phone rang for about 3 minutes without anyone picking up so I hung up and called back.  I was asked to wait on hold.  I was on hold for 8-10 minutes before I hung up and called back.  The phone once more rang for 3 minutes without anyone answering.  A friend at work offered to use her card.  Placed the order online and have now been waiting for 20 minutes to receive my sandwich with no communication from the store.   As a person who has worked in customer service for for 15+ years, this is completely unacceptable.

name: Ben Ross
text: Great place to enjoy Colfax. The cool evening air on the open and inviting patio reminds me of summertime city-life. The food is really good and the menu is quite eccelectic. Smoked Spanish Octopus to Lamb Burger.

text: The fondue was awesome. They had a good selection of wine and cocktails, but the beer list was limited.

name: Rachel Rosebrook
text: I have never had worse service in my life!  I went there with my boyfriend, we were seated near the bar and after 45 minutes of absolutely *no* service -- we were told our waiter would be with us any moment several times, but never were asked for as much as a drink order -- we walked out.  The place wasn't particularly busy and frequently there was a gaggle of wait staff just lounging around at the bar completely oblivious to the fact that we'd been sitting there forever and hadn't ordered a thing.

name: Maggie Wilkie
text:
This place is great! We've been twice now and really enjoyed our dinner. Both times, it was a lovely summer evening and the patio was fabulous, and we wondered why it wasn't more busy. I really hope this place catches on.

They do upgraded takes on classic dishes. So while you might not be blown away by what you read on the menu, you'll probably be impressed by the quality once you try it. You can tell that a lot of thought has been put into each dish. I think this place will become a regular spot for us, especially in the summer. Their patio is definitely one of the best on Colfax.

name: Daniel Shannon
text: We really, really like Urban Chow. The staff is friendly and helpful,the food is very good, prices are fair and the service is great. Nice people! The food has gotten better and better since they first opened, and their happy hour offerings are great. In particular, the salads are very well made and interesting, and the lamb burger and prime burger are incredible. The prime burger is the best burger in Denver, hands down. Portions are good too. We go to Urban Chow when we want great food in a comfortable, attractive setting. If it's warm outside, the patio is a great place to sit!

text: Amazingly good food from eclectic menu. Upscale casual atmosphere.  Lovely patio. Friendly staff. Excellent craft cocktails. Great selection wine & beer. A must try & you'll be hooked!

I went for brunch with some friends and we sat out on the patio which was really nice and open.

Their brunch menu does seem kind of small and expensive but you get a lot of food and it's really good (as previously mentioned).

text: Food is top notch and delicious. Enough options for even the picky. Service is good (even if those water glasses get ignored occasionally). A little pricy for the instep, but great location and darn good food. I recommend for a date night or a casual night with buddies. The couches are a nice touch! Totally hope this place is around for years.

name: Lauren Flippin
text: We got the lamb burger and one of the flatbreads and both were delicious! Our food came out quickly and their cocktails were amazing! The patio was beautiful!! I will definitely keep coming back!

name: Everett Lennon
text: Over the years the local dining scene along Colfax has greatly improved, but there were still a few boxes left to be checked: urban chic ambiance, elegant yet comfortable outdoor space, unique but approachable menu, and truly exceptional service. I expected the neighborhood to gain dining concepts offering maybe one or two of these things over the coming years, but then Chow popped up out of nowhere and left nothing to be desired. I've been in twice and it's plainly apparent that their chef takes great pride in his work and their management and servers really care about the service they're providing. After dining at many restaurants during their opening weeks, I have to say the lack of 'hiccups' during my visits really does say a lot about the team that they assembled. Hopefully(for locals) Chow remains a hidden gem where you can just walk in, but I wouldn't be surprised if, once word gets out, it becomes a 'reservations encouraged' kind of place.

text: Such a great place! The food is incredible, definitely "comfort food" and typical diner fare, they have created something really unique for the Denver food scene. The food is all vegan which is awesome. Everyone I have taken there, regardless of dietary preferences, have absolutely loved it. The staff is so kind and welcoming and you really feel like a part of a big family when you're there. Just be aware, the place is rather small and the dining room can fill up sometimes during peak hours. Definitely a must-try local spot in Denver!

text: A little hole in the wall restaurant that will surprise you with flavour. I'm not a vegan, but went with a vegan friend and found the food fantastic. And carrot bacon? yeah, good stuff! If you have vegan friends or are vegan, or even just don't mind a non animal eating meal, don't let the look of the place put you off, it's excellent.

name: Steve Replogle
text:
When I was in my twenties, a day trip by bus to Boulder was a fun experience. My friends and I didn't go with any specific goals in mind, just hanging out on the 16th Street Mall, perhaps visiting a bookstore or record shop. I can't imagine spending a day so aimlessly now, and sometimes that’s a shame.

In those old days, there were one or two reliable places for lunch or dinner, and Falafel King was one of them. Such good Mediterranean food - no wonder their hummus is now featured at Whole Foods, Alfalfa's, and similar outlets. Times may have changed for me, but Falafel King is still around, and I enjoy visiting the Colorado Boulevard location. It brings a little bit of Boulder to Denver, and has a bit of the feeling of those older, younger days, too.

For another review of this establishment, see "Falafel King Rules the Plant-based Falafel Empire" by Amber Taufen in the March 6, 2012  issue of Westword.

name: Judith Mattoon
text: This little restaurant is a favorite of ours whenever we are nearby in Denver. Food is always tasty... Yesterday's meal was outstanding! No one flavor dominates, and many different textures and colors enhance the plate. The restaurant is clean, with safely socially distant seating and an Airy feel. The restaurant staff is patient and efficient. If we lived closer, Falafel King would be a weekly dining spot for us!

name: Eric Dornbush
text:
For those times you wish you could write a review without any stars. The menu is a bit strange because they do not make it clear what you are ordering or what you will get. When you ask someone what the difference is they think about it too. But that certainly does not warrant one or no stars. What does is the hygiene practices at this establishment. I watched the worker take the pita bread and put it on the working surface with his hand, open the pita holder and put it in. The pita holder is a barrier between the employee who for some reason does not wear gloves or a hat but works with fresh food that will be served uncooked. I was one of three people in line (not a peak time), it seemed like everyone was confused as to what to prepare and who ordered what. The gyro meat is shaved off the stake as normal, but they do this ahead of time and put it in a storage bin and heat it on the grill when you order it. This is definitely not the way this is supposed to be done. Falafel balls were mediocre at best just like the service and attention of the staff.

Save your time, choose another spot. When I brought these issues to light, again, they just looked confused and sought no immediate fix or offer to remake the food. I'd rather give my 22.00 to someone outside and skip dinner.

name: Cesar Ita
text: Garbanzo Mediterranean Grill sets the standard for falafel pitas. I decided to give Falafel King a try as I've never been to one before. I was looking forward to getting a dank pita falafel loaded with the usual stuff I get from Garbanzo. Well, I was sordidly disappointed simply over the fact that they charge extra for tabbouleh and baba ganoush which Garbanzo doesn't do. Sure, the green chili hummus was intersting. However, it doesn't redeem the over-priced pita I got. Garbanzo is cheaper and has better options that don't cost "extra." Not to mention, the staff was not wearing gloves when they were stocking the food counter which almost prompted me to ditch the place, but I was kind enough to over-look that part for the time  being. Also, the falafel doesn't taste as good as Garbanzo's falafels. And then the pita wasn't an actual "pocket" as the menu suggested it would be. Instead, they just slopped all the toppings on top of the pita like a taco so guess what? The toppings fell out. Yeah, I should've saw that one coming, huh? Garbanzo actually puts everything INSIDE the pita like an actual pocket. Again, I am not mildly disappointed. I am sordidly disappointed. Never again, Falafel King. Long live Garbanzo Mediterranean Grill. I am annoyed as hell right now.

name: Lisa Rial
text:
We just ordered the family deal for delivery from Falafel King, expecting a hot meal that we could eat right then - isn’t that what ordering food from a restaurant is supposed to be? What we got looks like it came from a grocery store— prepackaged hummus, cold bags of prepackaged pita, and cold prepackaged bags of falafel. If this is what I wanted, I would have gone to a grocery store.

Even the baklava is disappointing and soggy.

name: John Buckle
text: I have fabulous food my friend Clifford had excellent food as well service was wonderful food was unbelievable and the prices were very good!

name: Echo Matthews
text: I would die for falafel king

name: Sam Edwards
text: Great food, friendly service, and good prices. Yum

name: Ann Lewis
text: the food is spectacular and the service is wonderful. I love we love going there

name: Darren Hopkins
text: Refreshing and great healthy food. Parking is a tad ruff but neighborhood parking is good.

name: Armando Gonzalez-Mijares
text: Original taste well done and friendly service!

name: Jayme Theis
text: Being originally from the mid-michigan area growing up outside East Lansing and an hour from Detroit, I definitely know good Mediterranean/middle-eastern food. The fact that this is a chain should not dissuade you. The people who run this particular location do a REALLY good job. The ingredients are always fresh, the portion sizes are great and it always leaves me feeling good. Great place to grab a healthy, filling lunch or lite dinner.

name: Michael Manos
text: Delicious falafel.

name: kendall cheek
text: Best falafel, ever!!!! Amazing!!! The staff is extremely kind, my order can be difficult bc I like extra things a certain way, and they give what i ask for every time! The food is awesome!!!!! So refreshing and delicious flavor. Been coming here for years and will continue to do so! Great job you all, thank you so much for a great experience everytime!

name: kendall cheek
text: Best falafel, ever!!!! Amazing!!! The staff is extremely kind, my order can be difficult bc I like extra things a certain way, and they give what i ask for every time! The food is awesome!!!!! So refreshing and delicious flavor. Been coming here for years and will continue to do so! Great job you all, thank you so much for a great experience everytime!

name: Christina Pelloni
text: Gyros meat is a little salty, but that is easily overlooked when faced with so many deliciously fresh flavors. The pita bread is soft and grilled to order. Veggies are crisp and sauces are wonderful. Hummus, especially, was delicious on the pita. The staff are courteous and quick. Great place!

name: Amanda
text: Great little shop in my neighborhood. Healthy and fresh. I really like the meat and pita grilled to order. And the sauces are great. Falafel is tasty and not dried out.

name: Devin Hieb
text: This place crushes. If you are a fan of falafels or gyros, then you must go here for the food. It is the best I have found in Denver. Even though it's a little far from my stomping ground I always try to stop by when I can to get a delicious meal.

name: Alex Palmer
text: Great gyros,  they actually filled it full of meat unlike most places. The meat was nice and crispy, the pita bread had a nice crunch on the edges, and it was full of flavor in general.  This was my first time trying the place and it's definitely worth trying out if you haven't yet.

name: Tony Grabczyk
text: It was delicious fast and affordable

name: Jenna Khivka Pratt
text: menu and ordering process is not obvious And the staff seemed a very annoyed that I it wasn't up to speed on how they wanted things done. Good food though

name: Stephanie Beaver
text: Not good anymore. I have been a faithful customer for 16 years. I will not go back after last nights food. I don't know what happened but everything tasted different and I did not feel well afterwards and for the next 24 hours. Sad. I will miss this place.

name: Ed Ski
text: I haven't had a good falafel in over 30 years. We found this place the other day and tried it. Will definitely go back again and again. They do it right. Excellent flavor and service. Good prices too.

name: Jacob Fletcher
text: Great restaurant. They also supported our local school. I highly recommend them!

name: Nick The Denver Dirt Jumper
text:
Falafel King is the fast-casual of Mediterranean cuisine if you're looking for a delicious plate shawarma or a pita this is the place to go reasonably priced and delicious.
They have their own parking on the side of the building

name: Daniele Ciccone
text: This place is great!! Friendly staff really good fresh food!! I actually ate garbanzo beans chick peas whatever they are! Not bad in this guise!  Eat here very often now!😃

name: First Last
text: It is a Denver staple. It isnt the beat falafel in Denver but its quick, easy and pretty good. Ambiance of the dining area is hip. Its definitely a place to bring your friends from out of town fir a quick bite, or a good place to grab some food on your lunch break.

name: John Buckle
text: A group of us from church went to Falafel King on Colorado Boulevard prices were low food was excellent we'll probably make it a regular place for us service was terrific will be back

name: Paul Merritt
text: Such delicious fresh and healthy food

name: John Buckle
text: A group of us from church went to Falafel King on Colorado Boulevard prices were low food was excellent we'll probably make it a regular place for us service was terrific will be back

name: Dmz Mari
text: Criminally underrated. The food was extremely good and probably the healthiest thing Ive had in weeks...maybe months. My personal suggestion is the sampler platter, as you get a nice helping of a little of it all. Their falafel is good as you might expect, but their hummus and tzatziki are some unsung heroes.

name: Jayan Manol
text: Great salads and shawarma, we enjoyed the lunch..

name: Karlett Eguiluz
text: Kind of expensive for less food than I was expecting. Falafel was good but small pieces.

name: Che Timas
text: Just found out they keep the raw gyro meat out at room temperature for several days. Great place to go if you want to get sick.

name: Duncan Palmer
text: Food was okay, place smelled kind of strange though

name: Sandra Brooks
text: Stopped in last night after work, was ignored by the 2 people working the counter. No eye contact, no greeting from the employee's. Wanted to order some dinner. Went down the street and got some dinner elsewhere. Won't be back.

name: Robert Taurchini
text: Best walk in Mediterranean in Denver.    Excellent!!!

name: Daniel Young
text: Great gyros, falafel, hummus and topped it all off with baclava!

name: Matt Tait
text: Excellent food at a very reasonable price. Eat 24 mistakenly lists them open 30 minutes later than they are. I ordered online and the staff waited 15 minutes after closing for me to pick up my food.

name: Nicole Meyri
text: Delicious! Very healthy and tasty!!

name: Bri S
text: I am a big fan of this type of food. It tasted very flavorful to me,in a good way.  The mint lemonade and the tea are not worth the money though.

name: Cleb Bleezy
text: Just so you are aware this place will use food past its expiration date. They are supposed to keep the gyro meat for around 4 hours and log the time. They do not follow health code and will in fact fudge the little white board. If they even do that much. The workers here are incredibly lazy. I once saw the old white lady who works here drop a set of tongs onto the floor and then dunk them into the falafel fryer, then use same tongs to get the gyro meat... The owner is a bad person as well he holds checks hostage from workers and will tell them to sue him as he hangs up hiding behind his telephone. If you eat here and feel sick after you were warned.

name: Demetrius Minos
text: This place serves pretty decent Mediterranean food for a reasonable price. It's definitely better than Garbonzo.

name: Patrick Smith
text: Mediterranean and middle East food

name: Mike Muniz
text: Slooooooooooow . I came in during off-peak hours on a Saturday (2-4pm) and they were clearly overwhelmed. Food was good but the chaos of the staff wasn't

name: Brad Sampson
text: Delicious!

name: Justin Case

name: Alexis Chavez
text: Falafels are delicious, even kingly. I personally love the baba ganoush. Reasonable amount of food for the price, cooked quickly to order. I've made a point to go back.

name: Marci H
text: The atmosphere leaves much to be desired. It just doesn't make me feel happy.

name: Mark Willis
text: Had the falafel, and it was very tasty. They have a tahini sauce and humus that were both good. The only caution is there falafel are small, the size of a big grape.  But other than that,  i highly recommend.

name: Shane Williamson
text: I LOVE this place.  Cheap, delicious, semi-healthy. What more could you ask for?

name: Whitney Iacovetta

name: Christine Caldwell

text: The closing times online do not reflect the new/actual closing time which is 8:30 pm. I came by at 8:00 pm on a Thursday, and the doors are locked. The employee came out and looked at me, then just turned straight around to go to the back. It'd be one thing if it was 8:15 pm, but 8:00?

name: Brian Hartman
text: The food is okay. But it goes for prices much higher than you might expect for the product. Wouldn't go back because of the lack of value.

name: shawna quezada

Yes, I will try out the chocolate baklava upon returning!

text: My first time trying Ethiopian food. That red sauce is a littler spicy, but very delicious. I highly recommend the sambusas appetizer which comes with the sauce.

name: Joy Elizabeth
text: Best Ethiopian I’ve had since I can remember. I had the vegetarian combo and everything was perfectly seasoned and delicious. The injera was outstanding; just the right texture. It was all gluten free and vegan, too!

name: Henok Teketay
text: I love the food specially the dry stake. If you get the chance to go to this place you should definitely have to try it.

name: Fishin' In Scrubs
text: First time having Ethiopian cuisine... Don't know if authentic or not, but certainly good... The service took a long time, and that may be a turn off for many... The one lady behind the counter was the hostess, waitress, bartender, basically everything...

name: Jennifer Torrez
text: Good food, calm environment around lunch on a Sunday. Good prices.

name: Luismiguel Lopez
text: This food is delicious. The woman is so nice and helpful. I like it better than most Ethiopian restaurant in the area

name: First Last
text: Very authentic but still approachable for people who may be new to Ethiopian food. Relaxed atmosphere, very quiet on the Wednesday night we went. Food was excellent, waitress was polite and helpful. Unfortunately it took quite a long time to get our food despite there being only 2 other tables seated at the time.

name: Gigi Solo
text: I have to give this place a one star due to the couple times I was served food that tasted like it’s been sitting out for days. It seems as if your taking your chances whenever you walk into this restaurant because some days you might get lucky and be served fresh food and other days you could very well be served something that could have you sitting on your toilet for days. I just don’t understand why they think they can get away with this. I’m not sure if it’s to save money, but they need to understand that customers can very well taste the difference between something that’s been freshly made vs something that’s been sitting out. I ordered their green Gomen (cooked spinach) the other day and it tasted like I was eating someone’s leftover. It was overcooked and it tasted like something that had been left out for some days. Similar thing happened when I picked up Gored, Gored (marinated med-rare beef) for my friend last night and when I tasted it, I have to say it was horrible. Quality of the meat was poor as it was very chewy and rubbery. Again, I’m not sure if this is their way of making money/profiting, but they need to understand they are losing customers as they continue to do this. This is unacceptable.

name: Cole Schmitt
text:
As much as you want to try different Ethiopian food. It's a good restaurant, though some items just mix their bread in with the dish. You feel like you get more but just filled with bread.
The combos at Queen of Sheba offer more of a rounded menu with different flavors. Lucy's is more diverse. Defiantly a try but not something you want to come back to too much.

name: Sabrina Akina
text: My first Ethiopian experience and it was delicious. It was extremely quiet when we ate there with our 2 sons. The gal whom served us was very nice and helpful as this was our first experience. I believe her two daughters also worked there and they were sweet. I wasn't able to try their coffee but I can assume it was as delicious as their food.

name: Ryan M (nize2beme)
text: Delicious Ethiopian, we'll be back!

name: Benjamin D’Innocenzo
text: One of my favorite Ethiopian places in Denver. Sometimes he service can be a bit slow, but only because they are making some serious food magic in the kitchen. My girlfriend and I always opt for he vegetarian platter. Plenty of food, super nutritious and delicious. Haven’t tried the coffee ceremony, but have heard it is 👌🏼

name: Rick Beethe
text:
Back again for Mother's Day 2018. Amazing food!
The gal that waited on us was very helpful in answering our questions about how much to order. We ordered what we thought was probably not enough but found we had more than enough! The experience this time and last makes this my go to place for Ethiopian food. I want to go there tonight now that I wrote this!

name: Coco Jo
text: I thought the food had delicious flavor. The meat was definitely tough though which I did not enjoy. It smelled of cigarettes inside which was a bit bothersome.

name: Joshua Sanders
text: Scrumptious

name: Tracy Ray
text: Food here some of the best I have had in a long time! Coffee is fantastic, as well.  If your in the area, and do it mind rough exterior, THIS IS YOUR PLACE. The cook is out of sight

name: Brendan Hodgens
text: great food, nice atmosphere, last time I went they were also doing a great job hosting a private event.

name: Isaiah Chatman
text: Very delicious, very friendly, nice ambience, DELICIOUS coffee and I will definitely be returning often!

name: Jason Stevens
text:
So I have to start off by saying that I am a bit of a foodie and this was the most stressful dining experience I've had in years.  I actually had to drive around in my convertible with the top down for an hour after just to de-stress and feel back to normal.  My fiance took hours after to feel calm again.

Okay, so where to begin?  Perhaps the best place to start is I showed up around 1pm, 2 hours after they opened at 11am.  I saw the person who showed up right before me (perhaps the owner?) unlocking the front entrance, so my fiance and I were the first to get in (I'm guessing they opened 2 hours late?).

So now, we go to sit down.  The table is wobbly, as well as my chair.  Not a big deal, right?  Well, right after that, we notice a child of one of the employees at the other end of the restaurant.  He's watching a kid's video on something with the volume turned up to the max.  You could hear it louder than the music everywhere in the restaurant.  It had a volume that just pierced any conversation and even your inner thoughts.

Oh, and wait, there's more!  While waiting for our food, the waitress was sitting on the floor working on some type of project, then took the mop, moved it around, and never washed her hands between that and serving us food.  My fiance noticed that one and didn't let me know until after, so I hope we don't get sick from food poisoning...

The food actually tasted good (not great, but good).  Such a shame, as we might have come back if it weren't a nightmare!

name: Francis Handley
text: The staff was super friendly and the food is delicious. Very chill spot.

name: Deepu Devassy
text: Best Ethiopian Food. Best Service. Period

name: Jamie Indigo
text: Great service. Delicious food.  Highly recommend

name: Leah Charleson
text: The food is delicious. We shared the vegetarian dish.  We had to wait a while for the bill, even when it wasn't busy.

name: Brandon Bearden
text: Great food, nice atmosphere.

name: Yemane Habtezgi
text: Amazing Ethiopian food and with cultural coffee ceremony with spectacular service.

name: iggirex
text: Amazing food and very well priced.

name: Dean Myron
text: Standard Ethiopian fare. The food is a bit under-salted and bland. If you're looking for flavor, head up the street to Queen of Sheba.

name: Guillermo Gallagher
text: The food is great and the staff is extremely friendly. The dealbreaker is the cabbies who start filling up the place after 9pm and think it's a club. No one should consider living within a two block radius of Mesob unless they're enthusiastic about being routinely woken up by arguments in Amharic at 3:30am on a Tuesday.

name: Nathan Schmitt
text: SUCH good food. The ribs are totally out of this world, and everything spicy is great here. They can do gluten free injera if you call a day or so in advance! Mela-Nation E. hosts open mic with a DJ here every 2nd/4th Thursday, and it's legit.

name: Nick Massie
text: The food is a step above other options nearby.  Did a great job with the decor. Staff is friendly.

name: Dionne Washington
text: Try it it's great good and nice people

text: Meh. Chicken tibs were good. It's just there was too much of the injera (bread), and not enough other ingredients. I couldn't eat all of the injera because it was too much. Was still hungry afterwards. A bit expensive ($16 with tip). Staff was very nice though.

text: I've been avoiding this place due to the more recent reviews, but a co-worker recommended it. It is literally 1/2 a block from my yoga studio, so I tried it today. It's surprisingly pretty inside and I'll probably dine in next time instead of take-out. I had some soup and summer rolls, and they were both very good and filling. Service was fast and friendly. I'll definitely be back - soon. :)

name: Stephen Holst
text: This is a pretty good Thai restaurant. I've been for lunch a few times. It's never too busy but it's not empty either. I still like Thai Basil better but they're not in the downtown area. This place will work in a pinch when I need my Thai fill.

name: Dan Stern
text: Favorite Asian food in downtown area.  Consistent flavor, good flavor, generally the hotness matches what you ask for.  VERY inexpensive for lunch.  Frequently quieter than other area restaurants since it's slightly hidden away.  Overall very good.

name: Damian Jonsson
text: Waitress had a bad attitiude, didn't serve drinks till we had been there for 15 minutes (5 other people in the restaurant). My food was dry and overcooked, Thai iced tea was terrible, and my green tea was brought out not even steeped for a minute. I would have figured that I it takes 10 MINUTES to bring out tea then it would have been PREPARED. Atmosphere was pretty good though.

name: Cobun Zweifel-Keegan
text: Decor is fun but the food was incredibly bland. Watery soup.  Sad pad thai.

name: Min Ma
text: It's super oily and salty. The server only dropped out good off and never even refill my water I ate all the ice. Worst place now it was better the last time I came

name: Kraig Kaiser
text: I tried eating here and was turned away.  Their hours are until 11 pm.  It's Saturday night and their doors were locked at 10:20.  Locked with people inside.  Illegal!  We came across town for them.  They lost our business.  Go somewhere else that honors their hours.

name: Paul Caraballo
text: This place has reasonably price Thai food. Isn’t the best Thai I’ve ever eaten but not terrible. Service was horrible! There was only one waitress covering the entire place.

name: Adrian Rodriguez
text: went for 5280 week. Very good food and the atmosphere was great.

name: Kyle Jones
text: We went on a Thursday at noon and they were closed. No sign or anything about why they werent open.

name: Jolene Santos Lozow
text: Good for lunch.

name: Greyson Bankson
text: Bad service, bad selection of alcohol, every beer on the menu I asked for they no longer had, I asked for hot curry, it barely had any spice.

name: Matthew Walter
text: Bland, not worth a visit

name: J P
text: The store remodel is beautiful!  I loved when it was Whole Foods and love it now (I think it was a Wild Oats back in the day, too).  They have a great selection and nice outdoor seating.  Will definitely be back!!

resp.text: We're glad to hear that you're pleased with our store and selections, J P. Thanks for coming in!

name: Justin Case
text:
This is my new favorite place !
It's laid back ..
Fab finds ..
Deliciousness everywhere you look !
Get your wallet and your a$$ over there ...but don't crowd the isles .

name: Robert Hubbard
text: Easy to use. Serves its neighborhood well. Very popular.

name: Ryan Farrell
text: The absolute best market in the state. Shouts out Sean for being super helpful, friendly and knowledgeable. I always look forward to going here!

resp.text: Thanks for the review, Ryan!

name: Amy Alleman
text: So happy to have this neighborhood market back!  Staff is very helpful and always positive.  We find everything we need and more each time we visit.  Thank you!

name: Brendan Bassett
text: Wonderful selection! Love the emphasis on produce and local food. Great prices on the basics, with plenty of quick and easy dinners too. A much better fit for for Cap Hill than the previous Whole Foods I think.

resp.text: Thanks for the love, Brendan!

name: Alexander Novosad
text: The IDEAL market provides an IDEAL consumer experience! I swear to you, kind reader, the store is set up to put customers on an adventure to the supermarket of the future, that is if humanity takes the IDEAL route (learning sustainability is necessary so we don't all die, choosing to eat organically, et cetera). They didn't pull the name "the IDEAL Market" from nowhere! It's all about IDEALism here. The prices here are even inflation adjusted for the future! It's crazy how they did that. Jeff Bezos knows no bounds. It's truly like stepping into a time machine, not to the past, but forwards, to the IDEAL future humanity hopefully chooses. It's much better than getting stuck in our hedonistic, unsustainable, overall subpar present by going to effing Walmart. Thankfully, you have to drive out to the suburbs for that. The Ideal Market is right here ;)

name: Cynthia Nodland
text: Easy in and out. Helpful staff. Fairly good distancing. As always a great selection of just about everything including organic fruits and veggies.

name: Ar1iee Ari B
text: Very much appreciate the convenience of location to cap-hill & has a fresh and clean feel. Didn’t realize it was basically a whole foods / same company! Well w/out the fish market smell. Organically focused is great (although prices for sure are reflective of that!!). Food bar is good (although the pizza was kinda stale last few times i was in, my only issue lol) .. Overall THANKs for the service!!!...

name: Kettering
text: Clean, great selection, friendly staff, decent prices.

resp.text: Thanks for the review on our store, products, and team. We appreciate you shopping with us!

name: J H
text: The cutest little whole foods you've ever seen

resp.text: We're glad to hear you liked the store, J H. Thanks for coming in!

name: Robert Blauvelt
text: Nice scaled down version of Whole Foods

name: Michael Alfaro
text: Very clean, modern, small and cool bar.  This is how all Whole Foods should open in small communities.  Prefer Ideal Market over any of  the other whole foods.  Selection is smaller so you don’t have to choose a million things.

name: Spencer
text: It’s amazing to have a luxury supermarket back in the neighborhood. Awesome prepared foods and the brand matched the area perfectly. The inside is like walking into my OCD dream, each aisle is perfectly organized with every label and item facing out, the sections are well categorized for look and efficiency. I have never seen a larger section of mineral waters in my life. I don’t mind paying 30% more for a better product and shopping experience. It is truly a magical place. Can I just move in?!

name: Kevin Christensen
text: Friendly staff, great layout. Love having a WF option that isn’t too crowded, yet has all of the things we need.

name: Linda Madigan
text: My favorite place.  Great food and lots of great specialties.  The customer service is flawless.

name: Joe Patierno
text: Whole Foods Market is finally open again in Capitol Hill!  The Ideal Market is awesome!  The prepared foods is expanded compared to regular Whole Foods stores, but it is more expensive at $13-15 per meal.  The food was awesome!  There is a small seating area and bar selling beer and wine for onsite consumption.  Love this place and will probably be back at least once or twice a week.

name: Scott Rickert

You have to give this place a taste test EVERYDAY of the week the lunch special hits the spot and saves the cash flow. Highly recommend! Just Do It!!!!

text: A pleasant surprise found this restaurant as I was waiting for my girlfriend's surgery on her hand to be completed. I was not expecting much but when I received the food I was pleasantly surprised more than ample food for even the heartiest of appetites. Prices are very reasonable and the staff was very friendly. I would have given 5 stars however seating is limited and a little maintenance would definitely increase the appeal. This resturant is definitely  a must try.

It's just good food, at a low price and its local! I will always come here! They have good breakfast burrito specials and student special which is cool too! The people running it are super nice, especially the lady that runs the register!!!

Hope this forwarns people so they end up getting the right type of Mexican food according to their current craving! Very important, I know!
