text:
Michael was super helpful after I’d had a terrible experience at another UPS Store.

Best experience I’ve had a UPS, and he was just very friendly and nice to chat with while I was printing out shipping labels! Thanks so much!

resp.text:
Hi Laura,

I'm Douglas, the Manager of the Store.  Thank you for the great feedback. We try really hard to provide a good experience at The UPS Store here in Thornton and are really happy to hear that you enjoyed it.  Michael and the rest of the associates read your positive feedback.

Thanks,

Douglas.

name: Kalyn Peter
text: Once again we need more help. Sat in line for 5 minutes nobody there at the desk had actually call twice to get the guy to come up front.

name: Keely Garcia
text: Never have had a good experience here.  The employees seem over worked, under staffed and grumpy.  I returned a package that weighed 60 pounds - the employee wouldn’t help me retrieve it from my car, it was large and awkward. Luckily a Good Samaritan customer was there and helped me out, thank you kind stranger!

name: Amy Hoffman
text: Awful customer service this is the closest store to us and our Safeway but we will drive anywhere rather than go here. My husband was bringing in a heavy package after all day at his own job and Mamoj was a rude, less than helpful, piece. When asked why he was being so rude and short (yelling at my husband to move the package not once but twice after he specifically followed instructions from another worker) Mamoj told him , “it’s because he was counting his drawer” and “closing up” which is a poor excuse for such an awful attitude and snappy verbal tone with customers but IT WAS A HALF AN HOUR UNTIL CLOSING! If I could have any influence on your decision to support this store I would suggest you take your business elsewhere as will we.

name: Jesus Medina
text: Hey where's my replacement key. It has been about 2 or 3 weeks now?!?

name: K Sevlag
text: I’ve never had a problem at this location since I have been using UPS, all of the staff are great! Sometimes, they struggle with a line during the weekends and peak hours (understaffed?), but the service has always been excellent. They are very polite, and today I was helped carry out a large, heavy package. These guys deserve every bit of patience, holidays or not.

name: Kara Highfill
text: Manoj Thapa was the highlight of my week during the pandemic. He was so friendly, and I really appreciated his offer to continue running the fax and making sure that it went through. He went above and beyond the requirements of his position, saving me a lot of time and frustration. He was fabulous and I would recommend coming to this store any time you had a need.

name: Mrs. Sandra Mosley III MOSLEY
text: GREAT SERVICE, I GOT TO KNOW MANY ASSOC'S IN THIS BRANCH' THE PEOPLE WERE GREAT, THEY REALLY CARE ABOUT THE CUSTOMER BASE. 80229 THORNTON, CO HAS MANY "LAZY" WORKERS IN ALOT OF COMPANIES AS IF THIS IS THE PLACE TO BE TO ALLOW ANY TYPE IF SERVICE. SO SPEAK UP WHEN THINGS ARE WRONG' LETS KEEP THORNTON A PLACE WE ALL WANT TO SHOP!

text: They advertise they are open at 8:00. 8:15 still no one in store. Lights out door locked. Line extremely long!

name: Sasha Cordova
text: Store opened 10 mins late and there were several of us waiting outside at that point. Employee didn't say a word to anyone. Waited another 10 minutes for the person in front of me to email documents to the store, meanwhile the employee doesn't offer to help anyone else. I was 2nd in line and just had to drop off a pre-labeled package and this took more than 20 minutes

name: Zander Woolley
text: There is absolutely no reason scanning to a flash drive should cost 50¢ a page. And even if there were, there is no reason the associate should wait until AFTER he's helped you scan a large document to warn you of the outrageous price. Will not be visiting UPS stores again if they keep up these insane prices.

text: They charged me one dollar for the little piece of tape necessary to attach a printed label to my package... wow.  Hope those 100 pennies were worth it, I won’t be coming back to this UPS store.

text: I only went here to drop-off a package 📦 and it took a minute at most. Thanks for the fast service. 👍🏻👍🏻

name: Davie G6309
text: Very helpful and courteous staff. I was in and out of there in no time. No waiting and I was in a hurry so it worked out great! Needed some help with the computer and printing and they walked me through it without hesitation. Highly recommend this store!!!!

name: Audra Montoya
text: Went for passport photo and notary. Online says just stop in. Came in and oh they don't have the passport white background for photos and notary is not in. Asked if they knew another UPS I could go to. They said no. Welp Google was more help. Don't waste your time here!!

name: Laurel Lalicker
text: Understaffed for Friday afternoon, but it was clean, in a decent area with quick access to I-25, and had good customer service.

name: Timothy Cordova
text: Store opened late. Employee gave zero F's. Poor customer service.

name: Les McDaniel
text: I have been a customer here for the better part of ten years. The last month they have turned form great to terrible! Packages being delivered and signed for then they say there not there, arguing over tracking numbers they say were picked up, and they were not. Even going as far as telling my wife to go in the back and look for herself for packages that they misplaced, while just standing around. We called prior to driving down there to be sure packages arrived, they said they were there then when we got there they could not find them. They need to change all the staff for people that are going to do the job right!!!!! Pitiful

name: David S
text: Fast and good prices. Rupesh was very helpful and polite. Sent my Amazon return on its way in a matter of minutes, which included buying boxes and printing labels in the store!

name: Jerry Hollingsworth
text: I've conducted business here numerous times, shipping packages and making copies and have never had a problem. I've always been greeted by friendly and helpful staff. Depending on where I'm at, this is one of a few UPS Stores I conduct business at in colorado.

name: Mac Mcrae
text:
IMO... GO Elsewhere.We won’t patronize These 2 places.
1/2 good reviews from some time again.
1/2 Bad reviews of recent.
High Turnover of Employees, Extremely high!
Employee are Not Trained.
Employees are Not happy here and quit often. Because They are not taught much They are Thrown  in and it creates Jams here. Ie. when it takes them an hour to figure out how to Scan & Email.
Owner has an Un-Professional Attitude, as well, about almost any issue brought to His attention. Money... Money..type
FYI, He, the ‘Owner’ has the UPS @ 120th and Colorado, also.

name: Debbie nivens
text: I am very disappointed with the lack of good business ethics at this ups store as well as the one on 120th and colorado.  The other day I needed a notary and to fax some documents.  I went to the Thornton parkway location and they didnt have a notary on duty even though it is advertised.  My additional issue is im disabled and it is super hard every step i take. Nevertheless I went from the Thornton parkway location to the 120th location.  I proceeded to get my notary and faxes to 2 separate locations all costing almost$30. I got the verification papers and went on my way only to find out one of the faxes never made it. So I go back to the thornton location and explained to them the verification papers show both faxes were sent to thr same number.  The workers at thornton parkway have a tone in their voice that seems like a chip on their shoulders.  They told me the verification papers were not in the same form as ups has so they refused to refax. Having all of the previous issues I would think they should bend over backwards to satisfy a customer..no way! Not a budge even after I told them im going to write this up they both laughed and said go ahead!  So here it is.  I have decided to change my fax and notary to fed ex!

name: Z O
text:
At times they have employees who are simply lazy, talk to much, lack a sense of urgency, etcetera, especially given when the line is long.

**HOWEVER, the young man they recently hired, ISAIAH, is extremely talented and such is refreshing. The speed and accuracy In which he 'Moods-into,' especially during High traffic times is short of amazing. His demeanor, light heartedness, professionalism, and willingness to assist in so many ways is again amazing!
I.e. Jumps the counter to quickly help a senior, Then Quickly sends off a customers fax, Then rings out a customers package, Then runs to the back and grabs a dolly to help the next customer put her numerous packages in a car. Then He explains the Mail box prices and procedures for another. Then it's our turn to send off a UPS package and it only took about 3-4 min for Him to get to us.
DYNAMIC WORK ETHIC!
Awesome Personality!
If Isaiah could be cloned, there isn't a business, IMO, that wouldn't crave to hire such cloned off-spring!
Keep Him and like minded employees and we will continue to patronize this location.
Great hire, such has had a very Positive impact on your business!

name: Travis T
text:
Edit: I called last night to make sure they had services for me to come down and use the computer and scanner.  A girl answered and said yes they did and i said id be down soon.  I get there and the computer doesnt connect to any websites at all.  The kid behind the counter told me "yeah it wasnt working for a while but has been better lately but i guess this is an off day and then went back down to looking at his phone.  He wasnt gonna try to assess the problem or help me he was waiting me out till i left.  So i did.  Thanks for allowing me to call ahead to make sure services worked there then i get there and they dont.

name: Joshua Sinnott
text: Great foods

name: M Victoria
text:
I came back from Mexico a couple of weeks ago and was craving Mexican food.  Ajuua hit the spot.  I had the smothered burrito with rice and black beans, my boyfriend had the pick three combo with enchiladas.  The prices were very reasonable, the food was good, and the portions were quite large.  We easily had enough left over for a 2nd meal.  Add to that a really pleasant and helpful staff and you've got yourself a willing combination.  We'll definitely be back.

Tip: We weren't drinking this trip but we were really impressed with their drink menu and tequila selection.  They had a whole page of different margaritas and tequilas that I had never heard of.  They also had great happy hour specials.

name: Alma Flores
text: My family and I went in for the first time yesterday. We have seen it but never actually got our attention to eat there, we only went in because it was late and the other Mexican restaurants we frequent are pretty far from home. We were sat down pretty fast. The place was fairly empty. The waitress was really nice not at all rude. BUT THE FOOD!! When it arrived I can honestly say it looked gross. The rice looked like plastic. I mean I have trouble cooking rice but what I do looked better than what was there. It was so chewy not good at all. The green Chile was so sour I was only able to eat the meat. I tried my kids French fries and they looked like they had been deep fried more than once. Once we left I told my husband I didn't like it and he said "me neither". Late at night my stomach started hurting and I had to miss work. My baby girl told me in the morning that she does NOT want to return to that place again her stomach was also hurting. And believe me we won't!! I don't like writing reviews (this is my first) but because I haven't been able to leave the restroom I said to myself "Hey why not" hopefully it would be a heads up for someone that would like to eat there.

name: David Erickson
text: Our food was great they have a really good Mexican breakfast which is rare to find. Our server was super friendly and our drinks never went empty. Food came fast will be back

name: Tim Schmidt
text: I've been here a few times and the atmosphere is nice. The food and drinks are decent, but nothing to write home about. On my last visit, it felt like the staff was a little short for a Friday night.

name: Sarah Wilkerson
text: We were seated and placed our order for over 20 minutes we waited for food to be told they had no eggs (11am) . It took over an hour before we recieved lunch. So much for breakfast. Lunch was good despite the hang up over breakfast. The food tasted savory and spicy.

text: Always have a great experience here!!! Nice wait staff...good food....reasonable prices!!! Great vegetarian options as well! TRY THE SPINACH RELLENOS!!!

Shredded beef taquitos were bland with utterly killed (burnt) meat, and were oddly sweet. Fish tacos were very greasy, and their sauce was the consistency of pink, opaque water. Not recommended.

text:

very nice people and services.

20% off with La Quinta hotel key

text:
Pretty meh-tastic for having the slogan: "Bringing the taste of Mexico to you". We went for endless taco Tuesdays, and they were dry, yet dripping with grease. Taco Bell does a better job seasoning meat. The tacos we had were 8 parts meat, 1 part vegetable (lettuce and tomatoes), and there was not enough cheese to affect flavor.
The chips for the table were pretty good.

name: Michele Ducharme
text:
So, first time happened to be attending a meeting at the hotel, and decided to pop in for a bite. Now, we were a tad disappointed that they did not have their full menu, but they were just getting started back up after covid. So, we did understand that. Jack the bartender also apologized that they were getting slammed with room orders, but we must have hit just the right time, because our order did not take long at all.
The wine he picked for my wife's dinner was extremely tasty and went very well with her fillet which was fantastic. You could tell it was aged extremely well and the demi-glaze was so good, she asked for a little more and the waiter/kitchen was kind enough to bring her extra, extra. Super yummy.
I am extremely picky about my ricotta, and the fried ravioli did not disappoint. As far as I'm concerned a good ricotta can make or break a resteruant, I was very pleased to see it was very good quality and fresh.
Jack went out of his way to brew me some great iced earl grey tea ☕, and even sent me out the door with a to go cup.
My shrimp linguini hit the spot. The shrimp was fresh, cooked well, Not overdone, and the sauce tasted heavenly.
We will be back hopefully to try the Colorado lamb in the future

name: Chris Missy O'Brien Christensen
text: Great smoked old fashioned and serves food late. Friendly staff that you want to come back to see time and time again. Something that gives hospital that neighborhood feeling.

name: Hilary Nieberg Baskin
text: We come here at least once a year when my husband's family is in for the snow show. The staff is usually attentive the food hot and delicious. Last night we experienced a much different restaurant. They were rolling out a new menu and decided to do it on one of their busiest weeks of the year. Between the first person on our table and the last person on our table being served there was a half an hour wait time. Drinks were overcharged allegedly because of a slipped finger from our server however it was not corrected until we brought it to her attention. I like spicy food and this was at my higher limit. The vegetarian bowl was 90% rice with a few pieces of broccoli and tofu thrown in for good luck. The falafel is mediocre at best. The brie however was delicious but served with too few pieces of bread. Service was slow, our water bottle consistently empty, and I was never asked if I would like an adult beverage. I understand that it's a new menu and a new chef. This makes me sad as it used to be a five-star establishment. Although the staff was apologetic. We did not learn that one of our dishes did not get sent to the kitchen because of a computer snafu until the end of the meal- thus the long spread between dishes being served. Compensation of that last meal was given however a new menu should not be rolled out  on paying customers. Apologies were not made until the end of the meal when the manager saw that we were not happy and brought the drink error to his attention.

The charcuterie board was tasty and ample. Scallops were very good, but a little too well-done for my taste, so 4 stars instead of 5.  Sorbet at the end of the meal was delightful.

The hotel is a little weird, with no lobby.  At first I thought the restaurant was going to be loud, but as happy hour went away, so did the noise.  Hotel operator told me I could catch a cab out the door to go home, but ended up having to call for a taxi  Would that I could live in a city where you can hail a cab.

text: Was going to wax and lash when I first moved here last year because it was closed to where I lived. The girls at the front desk are always sweet and helpful. The people who I had for waxing were all awesome but all three quit, then the two girls who I had doing my lashes both quit. If I had 5 people performing two different tasks and they all quit that’s saying something. Sad too because I liked this place but if it can’t hold it’s employees and the turn over rate is so high it’s not for me. They do validate parking at the Larimer square location so that’s cool.

resp.text:
Thanks for sharing Kyra,

Staff turnover is one of the hardest parts in the beauty industry and we feel your pain as well. It is bittersweet for us as well considering most people who leave do so to open their own businesses. We take pride that we provide an environment where people can grow and eventually feel confident to open their own businesses. The part we don’t love is we lose great people and our guests are then asked to see another esthetician.

Some guests prefer to see solo providers and we encourage them to find a private studio so they don’t experience the staff changes. That sounds like it may be a better option for you.

We wish you all the best,
Tawnya

text: Wow! So happy I found this place, I live 3 hours away and was hoping this was a nice place. I got my brows and face done, and it was fantastic. I will definitely be going back!

name: Alex Thomas
text: Love this place - I'm a regular and see Amanda. I dreaded the thought of going downtown, but they comp parking in the Larimer Square garage which makes it sooo easy! The studio is adorable, smells great and very clean. I like that they give you an eye mask and make you comfortable. Online booking makes scheduling very simple and the staff is always friendly.

name: Cheyenne Koch
text: Melissa is amazing! I will be coming back soon.

resp.text: Thank you!

text: There’s a reason this place has five stars and almost a hundred reviews...see for yourself!! Their space is beautiful, everyone who works there is so friendly and welcoming, and their services are seriously top-notch!!

name: Rachel Saltzman
text: High quality service. Friendly staff all around, very clean and Anna did a great job!

name: Nicolas Barreto
text: Kati is the best, professional, attentive and kind. I absolutely love the space as well! I didn’t want to leave, great ambiance, great smell, very relaxing. You need to go! ^_^

name: Marie Smith
text:
Christine is the best !super cute spa
Easy parking , great prices  - highly recommend

name: Jyll Overton
text:
Wow!! Great service from Stephanie! I will for sure be going back to her!!
Stephanie was awesome as always! She is personable and truly genuine.

resp.text: Thank you for the love!

name: Yaroslava Andrijauskas
text: Always great service! Been going here for over 2 years. I'm so happy that they expanded! Everyone who works here is very professional & nice. Been seeing Jamie, she is absolutely wonderful.

name: Terra Walker
text: Got the best brow wax from Mikayla. Great conversation, comparable, warm, and inviting space. Will definitely be back.

name: Geraldine D
text: Danitra was amazing.  Love her. She makes me feel comfortable. She’s the best. Took her time. Was very thorough

name: Breanna Maloney
text: This was my first time at wax and I will definitely be going back! Cristina L was very professional and made me feel super comfortable. The salon is clean and the atmosphere is very relaxing. My wax came out perfect:) Wax is now my go to salon for all my waxing needs!

name: Christina Robison
text: Joy is the best! So friendly and helpful, she always remembers me and makes a personal connection. And her waxing skills are on point! Wax & Lash is a great little studio. I highly recommend!

name: Christy Zollar
text: Professional, clean and good products. Their specals are great too!

name: Claudia Leal
text: Sarah was great!

resp.text: Thank you!

name: Angela Clodfelter
text: I do not recommend coming here, when there are so many options in Denver. I’ve been coming here for three years and this last trip was beyond disappointing. I went in for a brow wax and tint, lash tint and facial. When the esthetician was tinting my lashes she dropped quite a bit of the tint into my eye. I really didn’t think anything of it at the time. However, almost immediately after walking out of their store my eyes started to itch. I thought it was just allergies. The next day I woke up and my eyes were crusted shut, I had to leave town so I couldn’t do anything. Saturday and Sunday became almost impossible to open my eyes without a searing burn. I was able to get into the doctor on Monday and she had suggested it was an eye infection. The next two days I went to eye doctors and they concluded my cornea was burnt from some chemical that fell into..... hmmm maybe the eye lash tint that was basically dumped into my eye. I’ve been talking to the owner and she has no empathy and no customer service skills. Had I not gone to the eye doctor my cornea would have kept being chemically burned. I spent close to $300 at her salon and close to $700 trying to fix my eye. I’m very upset this visit turned into a nightmare. I’ll be going elsewhere from here on out. Currently my eyelashes are falling out and I’m taking steroid eye drops and eye creams. She is willing to give me $25 back as a “courtesy”....... more like joke. I wouldn’t be surprised if they get their supplies from Amazon and have no quality control of what is in them or where they come from. I asked for a list of ingredients and she sent me a product list. Basic message: go somewhere else. Attached are some pictures of what I paid almost $300 for.

name: Liz McNaney
text: Rebecca is very thorough and does an amazing job, I have had quite a few appointments with all the girls but Rebecca is definitely my favorite.

name: Whitney Pruitt
text: Sara is great! Professional and knowledgeable. Such a great experience!

name: Andrew
text: Joy was probably the best esthetician I have had. She made the entire experience comfortable and had great conversation to keep you distracted.  Location was great and convenient . Free mimosas!

name: Larissa K Quirk
text:
Visiting Wax & Lash always has and I hope will continue to always be a wonderful experience! The energy of the salon is great, everyone is friendly and the service is bar none! After Tonya stepped out of the waxing room years ago to focus on growing the business, I've had a hard time finding someone to replace her, but I finally found her! Livia did my very first lash extensions and I was her very first client...match made in heaven. hahaha Anyways, more than a year later, when I returned for lash extensions, I found out she also started waxed and I'm so happy! Wax & Lash has once again become by go-to for when I want to pamper myself.
I highly recommend this gem in the heart of Larimer Square for both waxing and lash extensions....especially is you see Livia! :)

name: Jenifer Graham
text: Love this place.. so clean and the staff was very professional and friendly.

name: Brandy Beasley
text: Haylee made my experience very nice.  She's a sweetie and I'll be back!

name: Mia Voss
text:
Wax and lash is still amazing! I haven't had a treatment since covid hit so getting to the salon finally after 6 months was delightful. I had a facial and dermaplane treatment which was like a mini spa experience!

The location is fabulous. Don't let the busy intersection location fool you. It's secluded and quiet, with a large patio right outside the front door which will be wonderful in warm weather. the front rooms are light and airy with high ceilings. The treatment rooms are great and the decor in the new space is classic and well done.

One of the things I love about this business is how great their services are and how well trained the staff is - Ashley and Mikayla are two of my faves with owner Tawnya leading the pack so the Queen of Treatment.

My fave treatments in addition to #eyelash #extensions : #facials, #dermaplaning, waxing (including nose waxing..it's the shiz and not near as painful as you would think it would be)

Oh... And #mimosas / wine served anytime of day! 🥂

resp.text: Thank you lady!!! Love having you back!!

resp.text: Thank you Jessica!

name: Molly Habby

resp.text: Thank you Molly!

text: I love Wax and Lash! Incredible friendly staff in a calm and inviting environment. So relaxing and peaceful - and they validate parking!!

name: Mike Flanigan
text: Great place. Great people. Aimee made me feel as comfortable as I could be. Fast.  2nd time not as painful as 1st. Will be going back again.

Are you sure you have the correct Wax & Lash? There are others with a similar name. We have no record of you visiting our shop.

If you have a different name that it may be under and have been in we would love to know what happened.

What do you mean by trash quality?

Thanks,
Tawnya

The technician had a very hard time, rushed, and hardly did a competent job. I don't blame her but her boss could have made an exception. I'll never be back to Wax or Lash and will be sure to warn my friends and colleagues.

text: I ordered at 9:37, it was delivered at 9:54( I live close). Was excited how fast it arrived until I took the first and last bite it's half raw dough, severely unprofessional and down right a public health and safety concern, I would love to hear their excuse as to why this happened

name: Kat Williams
text: 88th always on time and hot & delicious the BEST.

name: Andrea Maez
text: Great subs good service sign up for points to earn free pizzas  Thumbs up

name: Shanna Olivarez
text: I was so disappointed in my last order. This has been my "go-to" Domino's for the last 6 years. They delivered my thin crust Philly Cheese Steak Pizza and it was BURNT! Like burnt, burnt. Normally I don't mind anything that is a little crispy or toasty and ill overlook it. However this was so burnt that that was the only thing we could taste so we ended up tossing it out. So bummed that they would decide to serve that pizza to us.

name: CoolingSoda2000
text:
One of the best places I've been to. They have one of the best reliable services as well as timing, not to mention how nice they are to people ordering and how much of a great help they are in relations.

Would eat from there again.

text: Rude delivery driver and I called they hung up the phone before I could talk

name: Amanda Lynn
text: My FAVORITE

name: Nathan Lambert
text: Made a carry out order for 1 med pizza and 1 cheesy bread. It took 50 minutes for them to make this. 50 minutes for a 2 item carry out order!! ? Get outta here. Will definitely take my business else where.

name: Jared Saindon
text: Domino's is a chain and not one of the better ones. The pizza was not great but I've had worse from here before. Just be aware that there is a better pizza place right across the street

name: Deanna Bruno
text: We had a very large order, over 60 dollars. It was mixed with pizza, sandwiches, wings, ect.  A little bit of everything on the menu. They had the order complete when I got there. So they were very fast. Everything was kind of sloppy and greasy. Also. I had to check and recheck to make sure it was all there, because they forgot 2 items and almost have us someone else's order. They seemed very irritated that we had such a large order and that I had caught their mistake. A bit short and almost rude. I left a large tip, but wish I hadn't.

name: Nails_by_ashley95
text: Dont really care if you have a problem with your order

name: Helen
text: Great prices and pizza

name: Michelle Ewing
text:
I had a cheesy bread on credit. Because the one i had ordered came to me burnt. So when i used my credit. I got the same results. My friend with me said their pizza just days earlier was same'.
They need. New ovens or cooks

name: Melissa Lynn
text: Wings are soggy even when you ask nicely, ON THE PHONE, to please make them extra crispy. They are a soggy, nasty mess. Our pizza was dry and didn't have double cheese. Never again.

name: Danny Neufeld
text: We call Domino's alot

name: Paul Davis (RustyPilot)
text: These guys are quick and the pizzas were very good. The store is nicely laid out with places inside to eat and there is plenty of parking available.  Due to the location,  getting in and out is a little bit of a problem if you need to go West at certain times of the day but not to bad mostly.  When picking up an order placed online my name didn't show up on the ready screen a couple times but everything was hot sand ready to go.

name: Gregory Lee
text: Good and inexpensive!

name: Phi Nguyen
text: It was Easter Sunday and we needed a quick lunch, ordered two xl pizzas and some chicken bites, came to pick up, made eye contact with an employee assuming they knew we were there but was ignored for a good five minutes before we even got a "someone will be with you". Once someone finally came to the register the total was nearly $60! Asked for an itemized receipt and got a receipt with just the total on it. Pizza was scarce on toppings, way too small to be considered XL, and the chicken bites we're overly dry. $60 at any other pizza joint would have been a smorgasbord of food, needless to say I am never again going to be a Domino's patron again.

name: Ayo Gonzo
text: Service at this place is horrible

name: Josh Gunn
text: Pizza is good. I would give it 5 out of 5 but they made us wait over an hour for pizza because they did not let us know it was ready for pick up.

name: Gabrielle schultz
text:
If I could give negative stars I would !!! I have ordered from a couple different dominos .... this is by far the worst pizza/customer service I have ever encountered!!! The boy who took my order was completely incompetent and rude. He clearly hates his job! The delivery driver was exceptional, I hope he finds a job with people who are good people.
My pizza was cold
I asked for extra cheese I barely got any cheese at all!
I asked for ranch ... it did not show up!
I called and asked to speak with a manager and was told that he was too busy too speak with me. For the sake of his job he better pray this location is a franchise and not corporate.... because corporate is my next call!!!!

name: Sasha Lah
text: Always have a great pizza and great service. If a mistake is made it is quickly rectified. The crew is a great bunch.

name: Dragon Berry2020
text: Tried to order from one lactation , told this was our location ordered the pizza not what we wanted because the guy couldnt understand so my husband ordered less ...called 20 min later to tell us the couldnt deliver after we had ordered so we called Black Jacks then another 20 mins went by and they tried to call to get our adress again....no thanks!

name: Michael Martinez
text: Service has gotten WAY better and the pizza has ALWAYS BEEN HOT! and FRESH!

name: Daniel Gray
text: Solid overall. Quality of food is a little inconsistent but mostly good.

name: billy bob
text: 1 star because I have to. Ordered online and watched the "pizza tracker" go through its steps. At 511pm it says driver has left the store. YAY FOODS ON THE WAY. Waiting..... check the tracker, we hope you are enjoying your food. Wait what? No food and it's about 530pm. Call the store and get told the driver left about 530pm. But the thing says I have my food. I get told the driver will be there any minute, which in domino time is 30 minutes. I ordered at 445pm and got it a 6pm. Not the first time I have had a bad time here but will be the last.

name: Mary Obrien
text: Good food good service

name: Roberto Rangel
text: It was super tasty.  I loved the Hawaiian pizza.  Prices a little bit higher

name: eddie cee
text: Waited 2.5 hours for the pizza to never get here. Never again will I order from this location.

name: Gary Nielsen
text: Loved the food, doesn't honor T.V. add pricing

name: Rochelle
text: Horrible pizza had Anchovies on it the pizza is untouched I just wanted a replacement for the correct order guess customer service is not their forte I paid $30 to be told what I ordered and  I dont care who's fault it is just fix it never again

name: Meg
text: This location is terrible. The order is consistently incorrect or the delivery driver forgets to give me some of my items. Delivery takes way longer than estimated regardless of day or time, and the food is always cold by the time it arrives. The boxes and containers are generally absolutely soaked with grease, more than would naturally come from the items themselves. Pickup orders may be a little easier, but this is not a good location to order delivery.

name: Erin McConnell
text: Fantastic they went above and beyond right b4 closing

name: Samantha Schobitz
text: They don't deliver to my trailer park. They deliver to every address adjacent to the trailer park on all directions, but not into the park.

name: Jerry Hollingsworth
text: It's a shame that Domino's never get's the credit it deserves from pizza connoisseurs, other pizza chains just don't surpass their menu items, options, value and taste. I had a great experience at this location and will be returning, the staff was excellent and a pleasure to deal with, they were so friendly and helpful. I ordered the ultimate pepperoni and Wisconsin 6 cheese on handmade pan and not only did it look and smell great but tasted fantastic. Additionally, the marbled cookie brownie was delicious but you have to eat it while it's fresh, within 30-45 minutes because it starts to harden, even in the box. Domino's has never disappointed me and has always been my favorite pizza spot. Their sandwiches and pastas are really good if you're looking to change things up.

name: Dillion McWhite
text: Delicious food and some of the best staff I've seen in any restaurant.

name: Oliver Tiger
text: Most incompetent employees ever. Ordered at 5 pm and 4 hours later pizza arrives and the driver demanding payment after 5 year old manager said I wouldn’t be charged. Never order from this store.

name: Jordan Hunter
text: Good quality. Fast service, good prices

name: Mike Smith
text: In and out with a quickness

name: Ali Norris
text: It shouldn't take 2 hours to get a pizza that I ordered from a location 6 minutes away from my house. The pizza was luke-warm at best. I tipped while placing the order. I wish I could take my tip back, ya'll dont evem deserve a 1% tip.

name: Maria Zuniga
text: I ordered delivery and had a really ride delivery guy come to my home never again will order delivery from this place

name: Nelly JO
text: Always super fast and delivery is great but lately on the weekends their delivery time is 2 hours or more. WTH?

name: Nicole A Pelletier
text: I always love how fast and delicious the food is!!

name: Joe Treacy
text: After an hour and a half I called about my delivery, the guy said it should be there in another hour. His Mgr was nor available. When I ordered they said up to an hour. This is the worst place to ever order from. Call Pizza hut!!!!! Whom ever gave this store a good review is working there. Has never been a victim of thier horrible service!!!!!?????.......

name: Mica Rodriguez
text: This store has been getting worse and worse. I ordered online at 6:06pm with a delivery time of 75-85mins, it’s now 8:24 and we’ve yet to see our food. The boy who I talked to at the store wouldn’t or couldn’t put James, the manager on the phone when I called at 7:45. All he could tell me was “it says it’s being delivered, call us back if it doesn’t.” This service has discouraged me from ordering from this Domino’s ever again. I just called to get my money back and they told me my order was cancelled by me due to some kind of emergency. Bulls***!

name: Miss Chelle Vigil
text:
Has a great deal for 7.99 carry out pizzas. Large 3 topping.  I usually love their pizzas........Now with that said.
Make sure to check out the pizza before u leave. Last time my pizzas came out with bubbles and basically no cheese or toppings..
When I called a RUDE lady continued to tell me that they cannot help that; bubbles come from the fresh dough.. etc. Please tell me why i dont get pizza from Anywhere (including them) thats mostly bubbles that have no sauce cheese or toppings on them? And what kind of employee argues with the customer when they are unhappy with their service or product? Well i got them to give me a credit for 2 of the 4 pizzas they messed up. 👎☹  apparently I somehow
Ordered one of the pizzas with no sauce online. How and why is that even an option? So long story long. I had a whole pizza of breadsticks........ ugh! Yay

name: Mart Ladd
text: Friendly staff especially after the last big winter storm. They were working 12 hour+ shifts and still had a smile despite irate customers on the phone when they couldn't deliver because of the roads. Pizza is usually good but they lose a star for charging more for the N.Y. style crust.

name: Victoria Mitchell
text: This dominoes used to deliver to my home and without noticed stopped delivering to this area I no longer can order from dominoes and it’s the only pizza place I order from

name: Marco Reyes
text: I would have rated higher if my pasta bread bowl came with actual pasta in it. It had none at all, it just came with the toppings. I also asked for extra alfredo sauce, there was barely any in it. The only reason it's higher than one star is because the driver who delivered it to me was super nice. Get it together dominos! 😡

name: Edeltraud Fedder
text: They use to be fantastic but now they are.sliding  down ward. Have had some issues but not concerning the food.

name: Stephen Petrock
text: 2 hour delivery wait!! I ordered online to pick up and it said my order was being prepared. I go in to pick it up. After I paid, I had to wait an additional 45 mins!! This place is horrible. Not to mention the inside of the store smells like super glue. It must be the bread but, it was awful.

name: Mallory Foughty
text: Helped out one of their drivers with a flat tire, Still don't know the girl's name but she was amazing thank you so much. Kudos

name: steve l
text: 70-80 Minute wait time for a carryout order is long but somewhat understandable for a cold Saturday night... Being told that it's going to be another half hour after you show up in that timeframe is unacceptable. This place will not be getting my business again. I like Domino's Pizza too 🤷🏼‍♂️

name: donre darden
text: Pizza was great!! Wings are horrible! Like is it even chicken?! Don't make my mistake! Stay away from the wings!!

name: Kenneth Howlett
text: Use the online ordering and pick up, quick and convenient, plus you can earn free pizzas. The new store is larger and better, with an area the young kids can watch them make the pizzas.

name: Katey Kaczar
text:
Domino's has been my very least liked pizza place for a long time now. I saw that a 50% coupon was being advertised, so I thought I'd give Domino's a chance to redeem itself.

The nearest Domino's to me is only a couple of miles down the road, on the same road I live on. The pizza took 30 mins to get here, after being out of the oven. Thanks to the pizza tracker, I could see just how long my pizza sat on a shelf. 30-40 mins for the pizza to get here, out of the oven??

The delivery time wasn't bad in itself, just that the manager didn't have the foresight to wait to cook the pizza if they knew no drivers were going to be back for a bit. I've worked in pizza joints on and off for years, it's not that hard of a job, people.

Moral of the story: my pizza was cold, crappy and reinforced my dislike for Domino's. Will not be wasting my money again.

name: Jose Olivas
text: Love dominos ,best cheese sticks ever

name: Jerika Stanley
text: Cookie brownie was great. Pizza crust was gross

name: Brit G
text: Went into this Dominos purchased my order and checked it and we noticed the toppings were missing so we took it back in and asked if they could fix and they flat out said no there's nothing we could do. My family and I won't be returning to this location even though it's closer to home.

name: Brian Nelson
text: I just ordered a pizza and a sandwich for my family. I was told 30 to 45 mins. I have patients and it went 1.5 hrs. I call in to check status and Jazmine the manager who took my order made a mistake and put it as carry out. I was offered to have the food that has been sitting waiting to be delivered in 30 more mins. I will never eat at this dominos. They always mess my order up. They turn and burn the staff. Avoid at all costs.

name: Eric Merrifield
text: Food from this location is always made right and cooked to perfection. My only complaint is that once my food is cooked and checked to make sure is made right and ready to go out for delivery it always ends up sitting at store waiting for no less than 10 but sometimes up to as much as 25 minutes before its finally sent out to be delivered to me. Stop letting my food get soggy in its packaging waiting for u to bring it. Plz and ty!

name: Justin Willhite
text: Ordered my food and an hr later called asking where my food was. Was told they had the delivery driver delivering 7 other orders in the commerce city. After we voiced our concern that the food would possibly be cold, CSR rep began to get grumpy with us. After an hr and 15 mins food finally showed. Driver did apologize, but our concerns about the food was justified. The pizza was barely warm, like it had been sitting around for an hour and our soda was Luke warm. At least they actually remembered the sauce this time. Bravo you remember the sauce this time but were slower than molasses. Can never win with this domino.

name: Adam Aberle
text: I really like the customer service they have as well as the fast hot delivery service. Also, love their food.

name: Damion Cole
text: I really like this dominos, they always get my order right, and the one time they did get it wrong they immediately fixed the problem and I still thank them for that. I am very picky and they always fit my needs.

name: JatOvia NayMot
text: After having been a loyal customer to this location alone for over 5 years, and Dominos as a whole for more than a decade; I can honestly say i experienced the absolute worst customer service/conflict resolution EVER at this location in particular last night and carrying over into today!! They are theives! After inadvertently over paying for my order on a carryout I tried to resolve the issue w/ the register attendant (Devin) serving me. When that didnt work and i asked to speak to a manager(Brandon). The manager advised me ther was no way to check the drawer amounts for appropriate tallies at that time. With my kids' pizza getting cold and still need ing to be transported, i resolved to allow Brandon to contact me at the number provided after shift hours, once the drawers could be tallied and cashed out. While enroute home i realized there are cameras facing the register drawers and called back the store. I asked to speak to Brandon and formally requested that the surveillance be stopped from cycling over until i have the opportunity to view said surveillance with the franchises' owner. He assured me he would make note of my request. I received no communication after shift, which i diligently stayed up for (the store/shift closes at 2 so i waited until 4am). I then called the storw back this morning at 10:30 and again asked to speak to a manager. The female (Mary or Marie) stated she was one of the managers. I then reiterated the details of the incident along with the names of the individuals involved and their lack of following thru with their assurance. She asked for additional info such as order number, my name and number, and approximate time of the said occurance. All of which i complied. I again requested i be given the opportunity to view the surveillance of the register afer she confirmed their surveillance cycles over ever 24 hours. I requested also  that i might be put in contact with the franchise owner to resolve the issue. She informed me she would get back to me after ther viewed their records and the video footage but it might be a while as they were "very busy" (really? At 10:30 in the morning?!) Despite my suspicion i gave her the benefit of the doubt and waited patiently to be contacted. At 5pm i had yet to hear back so again called the store and asked to speak to a manager when Devin answered my call. This time i spoke to Dillion whom had now knowledge of the incident. He advise me the only way to speak to the owner was to call 1800dominos.. I did this and only got an automated recording advising me to contact the store directly with any discrepancies. To avoid physical conflict that would most likely result in an assult charge, ive brought my discrepancy here. This location has turnd me off to Dominos completely. I hope they know Karma is a b!%@#. Do unto others as you would have done on to you! I am a single mom of two kids on a limited income. Where it was nice to get them pizza once a week on a regular basis, i will no longer subject my income to the dishonest thievery of this establishment. This incident shall plague this location in one form or another, heed my words.

name: Scott Rovner
text:
Having lived in San Francisco for 20 years I have sampled some superb Thai restaurants.   Since moving to Denver I have been searching for an authentic Thai eatery that uses only fresh ingredients and offers an incredible menu.  I am happy to report my search is over!  I am writing now to express how pleased I have been with Lucky Noodles!  I have visited it twice in the last two weeks and cannot say enough good things about this quaint, cute, relaxing spot.  The dining area is immaculate, parking out front is easy, and and the food superb.   It is the epitome of a neighborhood gem of a restaurant.

When I walked in I was immediately greeted by Ploy, one of the owners.  Ploy was so friendly, caring, and clearly focused on my satisfaction.  I had a few questions about several dishes which she patiently addressed.   I cannot say I routinely have experienced that kind of greeting.

My first visit I ordered the Mango Sticky rice and Spicy Chicken Pad Thai.  Just perfect!  So flavorful, fresh, and perfectly prepared.   I cannot say enough good about the food.

My second trip I tried the Tom Yum Soup and Red Curry.  Both were awesome!  Uber flavorful.

I am thrilled to have discovered this little jewel of a place.  I urge you to give it a try.  I am certain you will be as pleased as I have been.

Scott R.
Golden

name: E G
text: This is a charming location with great curb appeal. The owner or woman i spoke with over the phone while ordering was a delight to speak with and very helpful in choosing things both on and off menu..  There-in-lies the extent of my interest. I am no food critic but found the food to be ridiculously overpriced and portions very small.  G-mas soup,  which I'm sure is great as morning starter has the flavor of cinnamon toast being sweet and filled with cinnamon... with the price being about $13.00 for a small cup with my palette a bit perplexed. My main entre was again $13.00 and a miniscule amount that was a small lunch portion.  I counted 9 pieces of thinly sliced chicken, some green beans and a ton of rice... The soup was Made with chicken wings, which I have no issue but the meat closer to the bone was bloody and I could not get past the flavor and will more than likely dispose of it.  Not sure i buy the excuse given that she charges by the once,  everything being fresh which adds to the cost (but shouldn't food you cook be fresh anyway) and the imported items from ocean pacific on Alameda Street. Huh?

i legit would give them 10 stars if i could.
someone recommended me this spot, specifically for their “chile” type of beer, right before the bars shut down and i just had the opportunity to give it a go last Friday. sooo glad i did! it’s become my fave brewery in town from that very day on - i even went there twice in a row and brought more people with.
their beers are something else. for real. and i tried a couple. loved literally all of them.
the place is wide open on the outside and very cozy on the inside. great for gatherings and social distancing at the same time during ‘Rona era.
and on top of all that, the customer service is absolutely amazing. Jess took care of us amazingly on Friday, and the other bartenders remembered me the next day.
definitely going back a million times and recommending to my fellas.
