name: Kiefer Thomas
text:
I've had a couple of 14er beers in the past and really like them. So when I saw they finally opened a can taproom I was excited to get down there and see it and try more of their beers.
I ordered a flight and sadly, I didn't care for anything I had. The beers I ordered were milkshake IPA's and a regular IPA. The flavours were weird or off. I don't think they added enough lactose in some instances and one beer, a strawberry spice rhubarb had so many things going on, it was confusing. Flavours weren't pronounced and seemed...weak.

The place itself felt empty. And by that, I mean the taproom wasn't inviting or "warm." There were almost zero pictures of mountains on the brick walls let alone any actual 14er pictures. With a name such as they have in a state known for its high peaks, you'd think they would have this aspect dialed in.
And lastly, that music....Jesus. Please lose that stuff. Dance/techno (Die Antwoord) isn't for everyone. That's actually the main reason why I left after four tasters.

You guys have some work to do.

name: Sarah N
text: Got the Groupon.  Great beer selection.  Bar tender was very friendly.

name: J Holmes
text: Their beer slushie is on point. Stopped by for a beer and ended up staying for two because that frozen concoction is blissful.

name: Andrew Cashen
text: Cool atmosphere, but the beers were not good.

name: Chelsi Hornbaker
text: One of my favorite breweries! The silver tray flight is the best and the beerslingers are always super friendly and will answer any questions you have. They also have seltzers for those who aren't feeling the craft beers.

name: madhu mathew
text: For a fantastic option of beers this brewery leaves much to desire. Hard to spot from the street given no real sign. Few games to play inside. Much potential however. Apparel but very overpriced in general.

name: Nato Francescato
text: 31 taps all made in house... Are you kidding me. Mecca for beer!!!!

name: real303 Steve
text: This is honestly a wonderful find in this neighborhood. The beers are delicious. Your bar staff is knowledgeable and amazing. Nato will recommend the best brews.

name: Chris Lombardi
text: I finally had a chance to check this place out. I had their beer at GABF and loved and and love their concept. The venue is a great old warehouse, my favorite beer was the mount massive IPA but all are good. Staff is also very friendly, and how can you beat the fact that some proceeds go to the Colorado Fourteeners Initiative, which is a non profit that maintains trails along Colorado's great 14ers. Absolutely check this place out.

name: Josh Gibson
text: Flagship beers are consistently great!!! These guys are innovative and always trying to come up with new ideas. Been a fan since they first started canning. Great outdoor dog friendly patio area. CHECK THEM OUT!!

name: Ryan Veidt
text: Blended beer slush is phenomenal!

name: Kate Kidwell
text: Love this place and their beer slushies!

name: Tom Hennessey
text: Great beer

name: Ethan Ruhland
text: Awesome staff and great beer! Neat dog-friendly patio out front as well. Will definitely be coming back with my dog. Loved the music!

name: Brian Ulrich
text: This was a great brewery. They have a great space in Rino, with a big open area behind the bar and a "patio" area. The "patio" has a large garage style door that opens to the outside. They have a good selection of there own beers, but also have a few guest beers on tap. This is also one of the only places I have seen that sells Little Man ice cream.

name: Simon Carlson
text: This place was great! Really enjoyed my experience here from the atmosphere, service and the beer that I had. I wear my 14er Brewing t-shirt proudly back in Michigan!

name: knisely sautel
text: Beer was great but saw several mice running across the floor in the hour I was there 😷

resp.text: Knisely, thanks for visiting. Unfortunately, we saw them yesterday too and the exterminator is on his way today. Cold weather with the proximity to the train tracks make this a neighborhood problem. Hope to see you again. -Nato

name: Jason Capp
text: Been great watching this place grow for the past few years. Nato and Andrew have done a great job making this a go to spot. Phenomenal beer selection, great music and inviting atmosphere! Very excited for the food truck this summer.

name: Linda S
text: Great atmosphere and brews! Had Groupon to try, will definitely be back!

name: Ric Rini
text:
Average beer and small variety (10 on tap). The space is big, open and airy. Decent ambiance. It makes for a cool local hangout but not so much for a craft beer lover, as for my palate I good not find any beers that I would make the habit of drinking.

Despite that it's worth checking out as they had had some unique breed just not for me.

name: Jacob Hansen
text: Consistently good beer! You can tell these guys pride themselves on quality.  I enjoy stopping here when I am in the neighborhood. They do some barrel aged beers that are blended quite well. The trivia on Sundays is serious business if you are interested in that.

name: Dana meldgaard
text: The beer is really good. Place is a bit sparse, they're just getting started, but the few beers they have available so far were surprisingly delicious. Especially love the coffee IPA- hop forward flavor, coffee after flavors. The lime cream ale and hibiscus guava ale both sound like things I wouldn't enjoy, but there's no candy artificial sweetness and they were surprise hits. Highly recommend, glad they're here, will be back!

name: Joshua Gilbert
text: love there beer

name: S A
text: Stand out brewery in a sea of breweries.

name: Cassie Day
text:
My husband and I went to 3 of the breweries in this neighborhood before stumbling upon the barely moved in 14er brewery. But I tell ya, they had the BEST variety of beer BY FAR. They aren't scared to brew something unique and full of flavor. We instantly fell in love with the charm of the building that will soon be amazing, as well as one of the owners.
Its definitely worth a try. DO NOT WALK BY THIS PLACE WITHOUT STOPPING IN FOR A SAMPLE!

name: Scott Thomas
text: This was my first time here. It's a smaller place but still plenty of beer selections. I tried an ipa and a lager. Both were good. The staff was friendly and my friend was allowed to bring his dog.

name: Ryan Koseski
text: Really good beer, and a tasting room you'd expect from a brewery that does beer not food and flash.

name: Emily Lowe
text:
Awesome atmosphere, beers, and service.
Dog friendly!

name: Matt little
text: Very good barrel aged beer. I bought the "Ginny Girl", so good, so complex. Love it on a rainy day like today. I will definitely come back at some point to try some other beers.

name: Robert Willson
text: Although I'm not always a big fan of the regular beers in rotation, I am a huge fan of the barrel aged beers. Spacious tap room and patio with corn hole. Be sure to visit on Sunday and play trivia hosted by 831 Trivia.

name: Greg Johnson
text: Lots of potential.   We'll see when we come back next year.

name: Kevin Mudrak
text: Nice space. Good beer. How they can get their permits in order to make it even better!

name: Cassidy Strode
text: Good beer. Great location in RiNo. Easy walk from a lot of restaurants. Good place to stop and grab a beer. Decent sized tap room with plenty of tables. Big tap list with a good variety.

name: Curt Hunnewell
text: On point for unique beer options only available here, in an amazing location, with staff that are meant to be leaders

name: Leon Stamatis
text: Went to Beryl's for the first time last night with my wife and friends. For a new brewery, these guys have some excellent beer. Great atmosphere as well. Highly recommended!

name: Alex B
text: Firstly, the beer is great. They are one of my favorite 6 packs to pick up locally. However... The taproom is small and under staffed. The bar tenders we're quick, rude, and stoned. The place had only 2 pinics tables in the back and they were charging for stickers.

name: Stephen Yanchuk
text: Cool spot. Good beer, eclectic taste in some...but by and large awesome

name: Robert Bostdorf
text: Awesome place with very friendly and knowledgeable staff, also, AWESOME BEER!

name: Thomas Arias
text:
Not too bad for a small place. The beer is really good here and the names are something else. Fun place overall. They have shelf full of games so clearly you have to play Uno and fake Jenga.

Beware though! The lighting is pretty dim so the Uno green and blue cards looked very alike... makes it challenging for those hard core Uno players.

name: Xavier Orozco
text: Fantastic service, great beer selection, you can't be disappointed. Friendly neighborhood with plenty to offer. Up and coming place I'd love to take friends to.

name: Matt Parke
text: Their brandy barrel aged beer is one of the best I've had.  Seriously, it's amazing.  The tasting room is large and the parking is easy (for cars and bikes).  The staff was very friendly.

name: Eno Hypatia
text: Colorado craft beer at its finest. Great location near other various micro brew and cider houses. Inviting interior and welcoming staff. Rocky Mtn saison is a must.

name: Jacob Schmidt
text: Cool spot with bar games and plenty of room.  The beer was good but I only tried the specialty stuff.

name: Jeff Delgadillo
text: Great groupon! Good beer and fun atmosphere!

name: Michael Bergman
text: Very nice little brewery, cool building.  Beer selection is very limited for a craft brewery.

name: Jake Hunter
text: If you like the taste of green and the feeling of awesome, this place is right upi your alley

name: Steven
text: Great beers- always experimenting with creative recipes!

name: Ben Troy
text: Great beer.  Looking forward to seeing this place after the remodel.

name: Brandon O
text: RiNo breweries are good.  Beryl's is great.  Enjoy everything from the basic 1864 to the barrel aged deliciousness they have to offer.

name: Carl Truong
text: What a joke. Went here last Thursday with my co-workers, we work 2 blocks up. Asked the bartender if it was happy hour and he looked at me like I was nuts and answered condescendingly, No... awkward silence. Then a few of us had BoGo coupons and when I asked if I could use it, the dude made it real difficult and it was super uncomfortable. Inside was cold and unimpressive. Literally like 10 other breweries within the same block, go to those instead and save yourself the trouble.

name: Jeremy Olson
text: They have great beer and a good deal when you get the flight. Six 6oz pours and a free glass for $15.

name: Geneva Polser
text: Great beer and fantastic artwork. Limited seating, but a lot of space! We will totally be back!

name: Bob Plagens
text:
Outstanding beers. Always something new when I visit. Super dog friendly, Iots of games. Outside seating whenever the weather is nice.

Beryl'd Riga is a must when they have it on!

name: Michael Douget
text: This is my new favorite breweries in Denver. The beer is amazing. The patio is great too.

name: Keith Alexander
text: Cool place had an interesting pickle beer here.

name: Aaron C
text: Beryl's is one of my favourite places in Denver. It's a great little brewery making some amazing barrel aged beers. It is  a super friendly and fun place to hangout. Make sure you try the agaviated gose. This is my favourite of their beer.

name: Harrison Filas
text: Hit this brewery on Shenanigan's Beerathalon #5 and it was the best of the 10 that day. Love their barrel aged beer selection!

name: Noel Kite D.C.
text: Love the beer. Really fun place to play games and meet up with friends.

name: Emily Kincer
text: Beers were phenomenal. I'm not an IPA girl, but their IPA was awesome. Beryls was recommended by the guys at Mockery....another spot not to be missed! #agirlinfoodland

name: Chuck B
text: Ok, someone's tongue was planted in cheek. Beryl's sounds like Barrels. And their barrel aged beers are outstanding. Both the Fireside Whiskey barrel aged Stout and Riga were exceptional.Wait, so were all the barrel aged brews...

name: Jaime Meier
text: Great location, friendly staff, and a variety of barrel aged beers that allow for a new and  different experience than other local craft breweries in the area.

name: Jillian Burkley
text: The atmosphere is not inviting. The waitress I interacted with was non engaging and appeared indifferent when asking questions about the available drinks. Nevertheless the aged beers had a lot of flavor.

name: Marco Polo
text: Fantastic beer!

name: Sebastian Nassau
text: Love this place.  Great staff and even better beer

name: Allison Heintzelman
text: Not impressed. Stopped by this joint on a brewery hop around the area. Unfriendly staff and unable to finish beers. Between the 3 of us drinking, no one liked any of the 5 beers we tried. Unable to finish 2 small pours. Plenty of other places to spend your time in the area.

name: nathan kamins
text: Interesting selections to try. Up and coming brewery.

name: Brian Powell
text: Cool place with friendly servers but if you're going for the beer (from my limited experience) I would say try somewhere else. Their focus on ba stuff is what initially drew me in but upon trying a flight of a couple of their ba beers, I was pretty disappointed. Got what seemed to be apple cider-esque acetaldehyde off-flavors with a both ba offerings. To be fair, their kettle sour was good and I didn't try any of their "standard" stuff so that may be much better. Not trying to throw shade at them but I think their barrel aging program needs work.

name: Kelsey Johnson
text: Okay, so I'm a little biased because I work next door, so I know the people. I love the atmosphere and particularly like the Kolsh and Paper Moon beers. They have giant Jenga, board games, and Cornhole too in case you've been hanging out with the same people for ten years and you honestly just don't have anything to say to them anymore.

name: Kevin Nieto
text: So this brewery has potential but there are a few things that need to improved . Their sitting area is just 3 park benches pushed together. If you dont get to find a seat there, you are left standing in the main tap room. The main tap room consist of two barrels and the main bar so plan to bring a fodable chair just in case. The beer selection is ok but for a place that is this bare on the inside you would expect the beer selection to be above average to keep people coming. Did I mention that I witness a art piece randomely falling of a wall and almost hitting another patron? Now. I know some of y'all might think I'm being harsh since they are starting up but for a city like Denver that has plenty of breweries, you would think that a new establishment would try to make sure they are 100% settled before opening their doors to the public. I will update this post after other visits to see if the ambience improves.

name: John Flaherty
text: Great variety of brews.

name: Sumer Kuxhausen
text: Love this place!  Great outdoor patio for dogs as well!

name: Kirk Metz
text: Burbon imperial Stout was freaking delicious.

name: Chasity Elam
text: Amazing!!!! All we need now is a food truck night!

name: Kerry Foley
text: Great variety and friendly staff.

name: Dunbar The fish machine
text: Key lime pie beer the beez neez

name: Kelsey Young
text: Really amazing, delicious, complex beers. Ooo ooo yeah!

name: Kevin Smith
text: Laid back brewery with a good barrel aged selection.

name: William Cook
text: Awesome brews and great people!

name: Ben Sweet
text: Went here on a weekend night and it was dead. No music playing, just quiet conversation from the few people there. Beer wasn't good.

name: R. Scott Devoe
text: Wonderfully flavorful beer and great place to hang!

name: Jeff Winters
text: Awesome coffee and barrel aged barleywine.

name: Thomas Sclafani
text: Very nice!

name: Bret Mavrick
text: Andrew is really cute!

name: Jeffrey Jackson
text: Phenomenal beer on top of phenomenal people.

name: Chad Griffin
text: Bad beer but you can actually sit down

name: John LeCrone
text: Good

name: Christopher Best
text: Solid beer

name: Patrick S
text: Good selection!

name: Kristen Schelp
text: Fun!

name: Jeffrey Burkhead
text: Great place

name: Monica Kent DeCook
text: Go and enjoy here....

name: Allan (fuebydreams)
text: Great aged beers

name: Zack S
text: Good local beer

name: Charlie Stewart
text: Love the variety of beer and the founders are really cool! There are great spots to kick it outside and play games and a bunch of TVs to watch sports in a new room! You should come here if you want to drink good beer & have the best time 🍻

resp.text: Thanks for the review! We would love to know how we can improve.

name: Seika Omine
text:
Afternoon tea has been on my bucket list forever! I went with a few of my gal friends for an early birthday present.
Amazing experience and the service was delightful!
The tea and the finger foods/ desserts were absolutely perfect.
Highly recommend!!

name: Melinda Hicks
text: Such a charming and lovely experience! Expect to lay around $40 each for your own unique flavored tea and a good amount of appetizers. I ordered the white rose tea from China which was delicious! The curry flavored egg salad sandwhich was to die for, as the were the rest of the snacks. The desserts were so rich and fulfilling. I highly recommend anyone to spend an afternoon at the Brown Palace! We went on a Sunday and there was a piano player and everyone was distanced far from each other.

name: Ruxandra Georgescu
text:
Amazing experience for a Saturday afternoon. Much more enjoyable than the one in London, if possible to believe! Staff is courteous and service is 5 stars.
We will leave the last but not least the pianist's performance which was worth of a piano concert master.
Pianist played all our requested music,  from Moonlight, Debussy, Chopin....to Disney music or classic films movies like Love story.
Wonderful experience, highly recommend!

name: Tyler Morris
text: The Brown Palace is amazing, the afternoon tea was definitely a gem in Denver. It is definitely a real taste of English customs here in the US not to mention the real devonshire cream, direct from Devinshire. The tea selection is amazing as well as the quality of items. The service is impeccable and the tastes are amazing.

name: Dawn
text: Brown's Palace high tea is a must for any trip to Denver. The setting is beautiful and made all the more special by the amazing pianist. I've experienced high teas all over the world and this is one of my favorites.

name: Harriet Jackson
text: Beautiful setting and a great place to bring out of town guests.

name: Janice Formichella
text:
What a great high tea experience!!

I am a big fan of The Brown Palace and look forward to spending many more Sunday afternoons enjoying their high tea. I’m also excited to see what evening offerings they have.

I took my mom for her first high tea this weekend and we loved the service and amazing herbal tea selection. My only ‘issue’ is that the gluten free menu could be improved. Our trays weren’t as full as those around us and the gluten free bread was just slightly bland.

That being said, I will be back!

name: Marcbot
text: Afternoon tea at the brown is always a great experience. Whether you choose to include champagne or not, the tower of quality pastries, finger sandwiches, and desserts is delicious and filling. There are many types of flavorful gourmet teas on the menu, and the attentive staff continuously provides hot water refills (plus 1 complimentary round of sandwiches.) It's hard to beat the ambiance of the Brown's spacious atrium, especially with live music ranging from pianists to jazz bands. The tables were never too close to begin with, so covid precautions haven't impacted things much. It's a great place for a special occasion!

name: Lizzie R
text: So fun! Loved the teas and champagne and the piano player is absolutely amazing very very talented (also so friendly)! Wonderful service. Atrium was stunning. Wonderful experience.

name: Matthew Brake (Naota Nandaba)
text: We enjoyed our tea and staff was very accommodating.

name: Susie W
text: What a treat to have such an elegant afternoon tea with friends in the holiday season!! Be sure to book far in advance. Perhaps a year ahead for time and date you desire.

name: Garrett Munsey
text: Wonderful experience overall. A nice atmosphere with a lovely selection of teas, tasty pastries, and finger sandwiches. The piano player was also great. Treat yourself to something special!

name: Caylee Steenbock
text: I went here for my birthday and had a good time! Awesome service, good food, a great selection of teas, and lovely atmosphere!

name: Colina Hill
text: I do not feel it is worth the money. I also was upset our group of 7 was only allowed to pick 3 teas. If I pay the full price for each person we should all get to pick a tea

name: Sara Line Frisk
text: This has become an annual tradition in our family! Nothing says Christmas like tea at The Brown Palace at Christmas time! The tea service is always amazing, the food selection is delicious and decadent, and the service is excellent! The decorations are exquisite, from the chandelier, to the Christmas tree and all of the garlands all around! One always feels like royalty when at The Brown Palace for tea!

name: Taylor Steiner
text: Dainty sophisticated place with tasty food. Slightly spendy but definitely worth trying for the experience. We got dressed up for Easter and had a great time as a group. The tea, sandwiches, and pastries were all delicious. I’d recommend going all out and sample everything on the menu to fully appreciate this place. We asked our server about the history of the hotel and he told a great story!

name: Deb Maxwell
text: The Brown Palace Tea Room is the ultimate Afternoon Tea experience. I’ve been here for tea many times and never once have I ever been disappointed. I brought my grandchildren today for an early Easter tea. As usual everything was perfect. From the pianist playing to the vanilla tea, the white chocolate cherry scones, the delicious tea sandwiches to the delicate tarts and chocolates. The beauty of that gorgeous old hotel along with beautiful furnishings, flowers on the tables and the wonderful tea service. WOW! The help is and has always been top notch. You can’t go wrong choosing the Brown Palace for special occasion, holiday or simply needing to treat yourself.

name: Cay Strother
text: Tea here is always a treat. What great 3ay to let away stress for just a little while.

name: Nick Lu
text: This place is bomb. We come monthly. Isaac is the head tea mf'er and he will straighten you out properly

name: Randy Kopf
text: If you like classy people and you can take a little while to relax you'll find your self having an exceptional time at the brown palace. Be sure to bring a respectful amount of cash for decent tipping. It's one of the little things that is my version of spreading a little cheer.

name: Jessica Benjestorf
text: I booked a reservation for tea during the holidays to celebrate my mom's birthday...and I'm so glad I did! What a lovely experience. The staff were amazing, the food and tea were delicious, and the setting was beautiful. I highly recommend it.

name: Rebecca Rawling
text:
You cannot beat the stunning venue for tea—straight out of Titanic with the massive chandelier and the holiday decorations this time of year. Finger sandwiches are excellent, but the tea, scones, and jam are lacking especially for $50 a person. The tea is bagged which is a major tea faux pas. For proper afternoon tea you need loose leaf with the strainer places over the cup.

The scones are definitely American—too crumbly to cut in half to properly spread with clotted cream and jam and are also not round so therefore not authentic. I make better scones at home.

The jam is mass produced and come in those tiny personal sized jars you get at hotel breakfast at the holiday inn. I was also disappointed that the clotted cream did not come with its own spoon so you had to use your own. I would expect a fine dining restaurant to know how to properly set a table.

Despite not quite hitting the afternoon tea mark the service is excellent and the experience is definitely worth it. There probably isn’t anything else like it between Denver and the Plaza in NYC.

name: Victoria Jacobs
text: What a beautiful afternoon we had enjoying high tea at the Brown Palace for the holidays!  The beautiful hotel, so rich with Denver history, provides such an elegant and interesting backdrop to this special experience.  The service is attentive and friendly. I always feel so we'll cared for by Isaac, Hiwat, Jessica, and all the servers. This is a special Christmas tradition that my children and I look forward to all year.  I know the magic of it all is creating treasured memories.  What was really touching this year was how attentively the servers and chef cared for my allergies. Over the past year, I have discovered extensive allergies that usually make it very difficult to dine in restaurants. I expected I would only be able to enjoy the tea itself while my children enjoyed the traditional tea sandwiches, scones, and sweets.  Instead, the servers insisted on taking my allergy list to the executive chef, who prepared a beautiful plate of tea treats that were free of wheat, sugar, dairy, and all of my other allergens.  He even managed to make me a sugar free desert!  The food was well seasoned with complex flavors and beautiful presentation.  I was so happy to be able to eat tasty, beautiful food outside of my own home again.

name: Travis Smith
text: Nice afternoon tea. Very accommodating to my two year old.  I would not recommend it if your child is not comfortable at a table with hot tea, etc.

resp.text: Travis, thank you for your review. We love it when families experience Afternoon Tea together! We hope to welcome you back again soon.

name: Zach Raizen
text: Afternoon tea is excellent! Great food, elegant ambience, feels very fancy but comfortable. I highly recommend if you like British tea!

name: James Williams
text: Excellent service and atmosphere. The staff are top notch. Hiwat always remembers us and takes that extra time to make us feel welcomed.

name: Andrea S
text: Best scones I've ever had.  Good, strong earl grey tea. Good service. A bit pricey.

name: Emily M
text: Afternoon tea is my favorite! Staff was pleasant and helpful, tea was delicious! My girlfriends and I loved it! Great experience

name: Melinda Powelson
text: High tea before the Colorado Ballet.  Such a fun and elegant experience.

resp.text: Melinda, thank you for writing your review. It sounds like you had a wonderful day! Afternoon Tea is the perfect way to spend time before watching the Colorado Ballet, or any show for that matter! We hope to welcome you back soon.

name: Rachel Moore
text:
I've lived in Colorado over half my life, and today was the first time I made it to their afternoon tea.
From the moment we were seated, we couldn't stop thinking how fancy it was! The tea was delicious, and the finger sandwiches were AMAZING. A live pianist completed the ambience, and I came away really understanding why it's such a must-do experience.

name: Amy Korb
text: Fun experience! Pastries and sandwiches were tastier than I expected. The buttermilk scones are phenomenal! I think little ones make the experience a little more magical. A nice place to spend an afternoon.

name: Tiffany Lamm
text: We have a tradition to go every year when they get the Christmas decorations up!  They never disappoint!

name: Mark S
text: A fancy and unique (in Denver)  experience. Fun for families and dates!

name: christine abbott
text: A nice place to try something new. Laid back, good service, food was average, a bit pricey.

name: Sally Glass
text: We reserved a table and were greeted warmly, we had to leave because it is was so noisy.  Held in a beautiful atrium but the sound bounces off everywhere, seated by the piano made conversation too hard.  I gave it three stars for lovely staff, beautiful surroundings and the teas that came out looked amazing. But is is very loud. hectic and be prepared for large noisy family groups.  We were on a romantic weekend so just didn't suit.

name: Sadie Peak
text: A classic afternoon tea in a beautiful setting.

name: Rebecca C
text: Wonderful staff, great food and tea. A fantastic, classy atmosphere with a piano player. I go every year with a group of girlfriends, they always give us extra sandwiches if we want them.

name: Lexi Lulu
text: What an indescribable birthday treat. My 3 girlfriends and I shared the Moet Chandon package. It came with delicious scones, finger sandwiches and the most decedent little desserts! We each got our own pot of tea and we shared a bottle of champagne. The service was impeccable. The piano music was an absolute delight, a perfect addition to the atmosphere.

name: Mary White
text: Very nice ambiance, but wasn't impressed with the food offerings.

name: Amanda M
text: Such a fun experience to take out of town guests or family.

name: Sara Akins
text: Had a wonderful time at tea.

name: LoisMargaret
text:
Delicious afternoon tea for both the standard and the gluten free options. Although the kitchen should invest in some slightly nicer GF bread for the sandwiches :)
Piano player and staff were all wonderful though!

name: Denise I
text: We had a wonderful time. Scones were superb. Third visit this year.

name: John Trost
text: Lovely, sophisticated, wonderful teas from around the world, also champagne option if interested, and gracious service

name: Kim ODay
text: The entire experience is magical! The service is top-notch & the food was delicious. Don't miss the Christmas Blend Tea.

name: Adam Follett
text: Great tea selection service was very friendly!

name: Nichole Rairigh
text: Great birthday celebration. Tea and food is top notch. Service was top notch too! I had the Darjeeling tea. The egg salad sandwich was delish. The piano man suprised me with happy birthday and a fancy cupcake. So sweet!

name: Jennie Robledo
text: Well worth the trip!

name: Summer DeSimone
text: Beautiful hotel, very romantic during the holidays!  High tea is a must!

name: Heather Pulley
text: The hotel is beautiful and the food is delicious. My only issue is that tea is served in an area in the lobby. It's loud and hectic, with lots of people walking around.

name: Drew Blackman
text: Always a terrific experience!

name: Randy Majors
text: Very enjoyable afternoon tea, especially for out of town guests that enjoy an historic setting.

name: Carman Beck
text: Awesome birthday tea with my family!! From 1 to 10 I would give it a 15!!

name: J States
text: Tea with the Grand Champion Stock Show Steer!

name: Donnetta Phillips
text: A great day for a afternoon tea, with friends.

name: Robin Sanders
text: No validating parking after spending 200.00 at Tea Time!   Brown Hotel you've got to get your priorities straight.

name: Brian Sullivan
text: Great tea!

name: James Garvin
text: Amazingly delicious, decadent, and just a fantastic experience

name: Wendi Merrill
text: It's a unique experience. Enjoyed it completely.

name: Deanna Alcorn
text: The tea service was very good, but also very expensive.

name: Me Ward
text: A wonderful experience!

name: Lisa Hardy
text: Go Go Go! A tradition for me and my family and friends!!!!!

name: Libby Hess
text: Wonderful! Perfect.

name: Micaela Thomas
text: Always a good time!

name: Jonathan Lorber
text: It's a neat place, but very expensive for what it is, and the service is pretty lacking.

name: Deborah Sampson
text: Luxury Tea

name: Michael Scanlon
text: Authentic Nepalese food, very similar to Indian food. At lunch they offer a buffet. The food is particularly alluring to vegetarians, but there are also plenty of chicken options and some seafood also. Great international beer selection. Very friendly service. Locally owned and operated.

name: Nicholas Chantala
text:
The food is very good, nothing disappointing about it yet.

BUT, we ordered for delivery tonight at 6:12 pm and it is now 7:49 pm, and we have not received the food. We have called the restaurant twice about what's going on but we've just been told the driver is lost. It's one thing if we are living off some county road that doesn't register on a map but we live right up Chambers from the restaurant.

We have really enjoyed the food but it's hard not to be put off a little bit when it takes well over an hour-and-a-half for delivery from a restaurant that is less than 2.5 miles away.

UPDATE: It was finally delivered at 7:59 pm. Food was good but unsurprisingly cold. The driver kind of apologized, if you want to call it that, just saying he couldn't find the home numbers on the house...

We were offered nothing to make up for the 1 hour and 47 minutes it took to get our food. The Jimmy John's in Commerce City once forgot a bag of chips with our delivery order and within 5 minutes, they sent a credit for a free sandwich on our next order. This was done without us even asking for anything as it was just a bag of chips; hardly something to really even care about.

Long story short, that will be the last delivery order we place with Royal Nepal II.

UPDATE: The restaurant/Yelp reached out to us in regards to our issue. They have definitely worked to make things right and thus the change from 3 to 5 stars. Like I said, the food is always very good but the issue was the lack of customer service previously.

name: Ed Ogle
text: Very good if you like this type food.

name: Lance smith
text: Excellent food and best Indian in the area. Love the buffet and prices are competitive. Love the fact that it's never crowded. We've been coming here since they opened and the people that run the restaurant are very welcoming. This is our weekly reward to ourselves for being responsible adults.

name: Lauren Motl
text: So happy to have a sit down restaurant with great food in the neighborhood. The restaurant is pretty quiet when we go in and the staff is very attentive. We also frequently order delivery which arrives within an hour. I can't speak to authenticity because I wouldn't know, but the food is delicious. If you like this flavor profile (cumin, turmeric, curry spice mix, coriander/cilantro, saffron, etc.), you will like this restaurant.

name: Katie Senk
text:
Good food, but when I ordered, and they did not bring the coconut shrimp, or the right entree, I simply called for a refund.  They offered a credit.  Why would I want a credit if they didn't get my order right?  We ate the entree, which was good............ waaaaaaaay off from what we ordered, but still good, so didn't even bring it up.  They denied me a refund.  So I paid for what I didn't get.  Feeling pretty ripped off, the delivery driver took FOREVER, I get it, we aren't close, but to not get the right order, and not get part of it, and then have to pay is pretty shady.
I'll go to yak and yeti next time......... I get what I pay for there.

resp.text: We apologize for the missing order I.e. coconut shrimp. However, an honest review from your behalf will be highly appreciated. We did offer you cash refund from the restaurant and you agreed on it. We cannot process refund for a single item out of whole order as it was ordered from Groupon. Once again we apologize for the inconveniences.

I did not do the buffet. Instead I went inside and sat at the bar to place a to-go order. Had a vegan chai that was perfect for sipping on while I waited on my order. I finished it right around the time my food was ready. I get home and the food was delicious. Highly recommend the cheese naan with any order. It was so delicious. My main course was the Chicken Tikka. That was also good. Definitely coming back for the chai and cheese naan and can't wait to try their other menu items.

name: Mary Alico
text: I was contacted on 02/22/2021 by a Jessi McKinney because I had applied to an HR Assistant role at their main office in Denver. She requested I send her dates and times of a good time for her to reach out to me for a brief phone screen. I provided her dates and times that same day and the entire week went past without as much as a follow-up email. I sent her a 2nd email asking if she had received my email and if she would be reaching out to me. Most people are excited to get a phone call or email regarding a possible job. Jessi never responded to that email as well. My image, impression and thoughts about the company are now less than stellar. What employees like Jessi do not grasp is the reflection their actions have on the company from an outsider  point of view who are treated as such. Maybe it's a good thing I saw the inner workings. It is certainly not a place I would recommend and I hope the CEO and executive chairman see this review. I am shocked these days at how some people do their jobs or better said don't do their jobs.

resp.text:
Hi Mary,

I apologize for your experience with us as a candidate for our HR Assistant position. You are right, we did a poor job following up and I take full responsibility for that. Ultimately, the responsibility falls to me as CEO and I failed to provide enough resources to our people running the hiring process to ensure timely communication and follow up. I’ve taken steps this morning to add more resources, address where we have let down candidates, and get personally involved to help.

I’m proud of Seattle Fish Co. - our history, how we engage our employees, open systems management, and deep adherence to our core values. The hiring process is a reflection of who we are, and in this case, we fell short of showcasing our company, our brand, and representing our Seattle Fish Co. family.

Your experience with us is unfortunate, and it’s one we plan to learn from moving forward.

Sincerely,
Derek Figueroa
President & CEO

name: Krissy Calloway
text: So I have this little group of three good friends and we like to go out about once a month. We decided to  go to The Triangle after one of my friends saw their add on Facebook. It was easy to make reservations and they have amazing tables, that maintain social distancing, with little fire pits in the middle for heat. This is real nice to have in Denver during the month of December. The attraction was bingo hosted with a drag show. The two girls in drag were super funny and I really enjoyed the show. It was super fun. Someone that stuck out to me was the hostess Jordan. She is the worker bee of the triangle and dies an absolutely amazing job hosting the tables. I will most definitely be going back in the near future. I was treated with the upmost respect as was everyone else. Just a wonderful LGBTQ friendly establishment. I would recommend this place for anyone that is looking for a judgement free establishment to have a good time.

The waitress was blonde didnt have a name tag and acted like we were not even sitting there she just wanted the group of guys to tip her more there was another table saying they were there waiting first to. How do they expect you to play trivia in the dark?
So weird.  Dont bother coming here.

resp.text: Hey There Barbara. We apologize that your experience was less than stellar. Our bar staff did adjust the lights to a brighter setting but it does take a couple of minutes for the system to fade the lights up. We will adjust the schedules on the lighting system to stay brighter on Tuesdays. We hope you give us another chance and that you come back to enjoy one of 14 locally brewed beers on us.

text: Awesome, fun spot to get together w/ friends and enjoy some libations. Staff is very friendly, great atmosphere  and Sean's just the best. Truly amazing customer service - I was there for St. Patty day and spent quite a bit. My credit card company emailed me to say that the tip was disproportionately large compared to the tab, which alarmed me so I reached out to them through FB and Sean followed up shortly thereafter, and wanted to make sure that everything was ok. He looked up my receipt/tab which confirmed all was well and nothing nefarious had occurred - turns out my CC company had misinterpreted the way their tabs calculate. Wasn't expecting such quick, kind and professional service - Great job Sean and Team! Look forwarding to getting back up there soon.

text: Great local coffee shop on South Broadway and not far from other great eateries such as the Denver Biscuit company. The espresso here is exceptional and smooth with alternative milks such as soy or almond to choose from. They also serve cold brew coffee and iced drinks. There is a good selection of seating including an upstairs area with a couch and one large community table with a bar like setting. This place is very laptop friendly with plenty of tables and a bar area with electrical outlets. A+

Now, I've found one.

name: Shayna M
text: If you need a place with great coffee, light bites, friendly staff as well as a productive work environment, this is the place to be! There are plenty of plugs to use your laptop, and an additional upstairs area if you get distracted by people ordering/coming and going. They also typically have a unique alcoholic drink such as mulled wine available for when you are done with your work!

name: Kent Heaton
text: Good coffee and a relaxed atmosphere. Nice place to spend a Saturday morning with nothing to do. Parking can be hard to find during peak hours.

name: Johnica Grover
text: Yummy food and very pretty cappuccino.  Sadly the cappuccino was terrible.  My Husband ordered a regular coffee. He did not drink it. We poured both drinks out. The coffee smelled and tasted much like a Folgers or something to that bean quality. I'm hoping they just had a very off day. Maybe a bad shipment? I will try them again. I did have an empanada and it was delicious.

name: Lily Calfee
text: Friendly, hip staff, great ambience (music/plants/art) and very, very good coffee. Also! Oatmeal, almond milk, and soy milk plus some gluten free and vegan goodies.

name: Nick S
text:
The decor is decent, location is convenient, and coffee is passable but that's really where the good ends.  The Baristas tend to be not very personable, and the music is often too loud to concentrate.  The selection of food is pretty lacking, as well. While the upstairs area is an excellent place to work, it's ruined by the constantly blasting music.

There are much better options in the area, such as Bardo, or Mutiny.  While I often hesitate to recommend it, Starbucks might even be a safer bet if you need somewhere to work/study/concentrate.

With an attitude adjustment and an adjustment of the music volume, this would be 4 stars for sure

Unfortunately, if one of the female barista's is there I don't feel as welcomed and my chai never tastes right, but for the majority of the time the drive is worth it! name: Rebeca P.
text: First time here trying Indian food. Incredibly delicious I ate extremely fast, it was so good! They also have an entire section for a vegan menu, and they have Indian beers as well. Many different options on the menu including lamb, chicken, and shrimp. Have a great patio outside so you can people watch. Definitely coming back to this place! We found that it was much cooler, temperature wise, to sit outside than on the inside where it was warmer. They also have small plates if you'd rather share with someone, as well as a ton of sides. I also overdosed on the delicious naan bread as it was straight out of the oven, toasty, and flavorful!

resp.text: Thank you for sharing your experience, Rebeca. We appreciate your support and kind words! Thank you!

name: Jess Harmon
text: Relaxing atmosphere and decor paired with friendly, speedy service and delicious food! Lunch buffet was on the smaller size, but plenty satisfying. I do not eat meat, and there were plenty of vegetarian entrees on the buffet: one stew, a chickpea sauce, a spinach dish, and a mix veggie korma sauce (plus a few vegetarian side dishes). The buffet is quite inexpensive at $10.99 per person. I will definitely be back!

resp.text: Thank you very much, Jess. I'm so glad to hear that you enjoyed our vegetarian offerings and that we made you feel welcome. We appreciate you - see you next time!

name: Anthony Prichard
text: It was quiet and nice to sit and talk in the booth. We had good service and there was an authentic sitar player.

name: Steve Replogle
text:
Sadly, this charming, delightful restaurant is now closed. It was the victim of the seemingly-endless construction in Cherry Creek North generally... and the multi-use high-rise right next door, in particular.

Here’s what I wrote back when Bombay Clay Oven was still open: “My family and I love to visit Bombay Clay Oven for special occasions. We also enjoy taking out-of-town friends to this jewel of a restaurant and our guests are always quite impressed. The food is wonderful and the atmosphere is very enjoyable. I have had tikka masala and vindaloo dishes and found both styles to be superb. The pakoras, naan, and samosas are all quite delicious, too.“

Again, it is a great loss that this restaurant is no longer in operation. Fortunately, their fast-casual sister operation, Saucy Bombay, remains open and offers many of the same wonderful dishes to customers.

resp.text:
Thank you so much for the kind words here, Steve! It's wonderful to know that we've become a go-to for special occasions and when you have guests in town -- especially in a delicious city like Denver! We'll look forward to seeing you the next time you have a craving for a tasty Indian meal!
Cheers,
Marshall, Owner

name: Pernilla Paquette
text: Looked for places in Denver where you can sit on pillows. Loved it. Atmosphere, service, food, music... Great. And I am an atmosphere snob... I don't hear very well so having the "booth" with pillows and curtains helped a lot. Not very noisy. I know nothing of Indian cuisine so getting service minded and easy to understand guidance was appreciated. Fantastic sauces.

resp.text: Thank you very much for trying us out, Pernilla. We're so glad you enjoyed the overall experience and that you were pleasantly surprised. Hope to see you back here soon!

name: Lucinda Uvalle
text: Delicious food! Great atmosphere. Our server walked us through the menu and asked our food preferences then made a recommendation. Great place if it's your first time trying Indian food or your 100th!

name: Saket Doshi
text: Great decor and ambience. The food was good as well. We had lunch buffet. Decent vegetarian options. Non-veg options were better than veg ones.

name: Keri Peacock Wilson
text: This was the perfect setting for our end-of-the-year team banquet of 40+ people. The food was delicious, the space was comfortable, and coordinating the event with the owners was a breeze. The restaurant was able to create a menu based on our price point and was prepared with attentive wait-staff. I am already looking forward to coming back here with the family!

resp.text: We're so happy to hear that your party enjoyed dining with us. See you next time!! :)

name: Jesse James
text: Buffett was delicious! Nice quiet atmosphere.

resp.text: Thank you, Jesse!!

name: Matt Hendrix
text: This is the first Indian restaurant I have ever been to, and if all Indian food is this good then I might have just found one of my favorite types of food. The atmosphere is nice and fun. I had my meal in their version of a booth where you can take off your shoes and relax on pillows while you enjoy the chai and naan. I have returned a few times since trying here, and that was only a month ago.

name: Chelsea Klein
text: Fantastic Indian food! Great service, very friendly & welcoming. I love the comfy booths. Definitely turned me into a repeat customer.

name: ben fromboulder
text: Great service and good food! Owner has a great new Indian restaurant with a really Hip new concept. Worth stepping in just to try the food and relax.

resp.text: Thanks so much, Ben. We appreciate your support!

name: Anne Aragon
text: Great atmosphere and food. Also, excellent friendly service! Will definitely go back!

resp.text: Thank you so much, Anne!! We're so glad you enjoy dining with us. :)

name: Richard Debellevue
text: The brunch/lunch buffet was delicious, service is excellent. Definitely going to be going back!

resp.text: Thank you for the kind words and for trying us out, Richard. See you next time!

name: amber perlman
text: This place has the sweetest atmosphere!  I haven't eaten here yet but am looking forward to it. I know it must be good because I get a huge amount of delivery request through Uber Eats for this restaurant. And it always smells so yummy! Plus the staff are always friendly and I never wait long to pick up deliverys.

resp.text: Thank you so much, Amber! We hope you have a chance to come in and dine with us soon. :) We appreciate your support!!

name: V P
text: The quality of this place has definitely gone down. The food was not good and the server had no idea what she was doing. We asked to get our food in a to go box and she threw it away.

name: Nese Sahin
text: Bombay Clay Oven is very authentic. We went there with our kids multiple times our kids love sitting at the area with the curtains and pillows.  Both the owner and the staff was very friendly they make you feel like kings and queens. Their naan and mango yogurt drink are to die for. My family especially love their appetizers and chicken tandoori.

name: Antonio nash
text: We very much enjoyed the food, service, and atmosphere of the Bombay Clay Oven in Cherry Creek. All the food was great, especially the Tandoori chicken! And they are digital: you can catch a Pokemon there!

name: George Rapko
text: the food is good, but the interior is getting dated.  The service can by a little laggy when you get there, but generally it's okay.  The prices are bit higher than your run of the mill Indian place.

name: Sarah Trento
text: Love this place! The food is so good and we love the guy playing sarod and citar while we eat. I have been coming here since I was a little girl and I love it!

resp.text: We're so happy to hear that you enjoy the music and food, Sarah! Thank so much for your continued support over the years. We appreciate you!

name: Andy Case
text: The best thing about this place was the Naan, and the Mulligatawny was decent. The 2 entrees we had were not good though, below average Indian food in my opinion. The prices are much higher than other Indian restaurant's. I'm not sure why anyone goes here.

name: Joshua Klomp
text: Overpriced for small portions (even the rice was small). The chicken tikka masala was hard and dry, the mali kofta was not good on any level. Paid $40 for the two entrees and kheer and we were still hungry (and our taste buds disappointed). Definitely not going back.

name: CJ Rapp
text: Great place for a week night outing! Great food, good staff and reasonable prices for Cherry Creek ~ ♥ ~ Located on the edge so parking is never a problem after 6:00pm

name: Jasmine Nicole
text: Previous experiences had been better. I Was really looking forward to coming to this place but I really wish I hadn’t. We Were served Burned naan, soda that tasted like cleaning solution, and there was a long black hair found in our food. The manager took half off the meal, which was courteous but didn’t make up for it.

name: Rally Vincent
text: Good buffet but the service when getting refills or the check can leave something to be desired. Great if you have a lot of time on your hands.

name: Johnny Shen
text: Just moved to Denver and trying Indian places out.  Food during lunch buffet was tasty,  BUT it was lukewarm at best... almost like leftovers sitting for a while. I came at 1:15 pm and was only 1 of 3 patrons there on a weekday.  Now I see why.

name: Ammar Malik
text: Seafood is decent, the prices are steep, the service is great, however, the owner/manager treats his staff poorly, I can hear it, see it and sense it. The servers are forced in trying to over sell. Place is usually quaint so the service is fast. The chairs and tej carpet need cleaning!!

text:
This is way better than 3.9 stars!  The ambiance was great, Marshall's service was excellent and the Chicken Tikka Masala was so good!  I also had an appetizer that was potato cakes with yogurt and tomatoes...forgot the name, but that was excellent as well!  You will love this place!!

P.S.  I have Celiacs Disease and there were lots of GF options and Marshall was great at making sure there was no cross-contamination.

text: Really delicious sauces. The vindaloo, masala and korma all have great flavor and diversity. I had the lamb vindaloo and it was magnificent, deep but almost tart in flavor. Blue moon topped it off nicely.

name: Ryan Austin
text: Ultimately, the food was just boring. The dishes sounded great, but just didn't have the flavor of other restaurants. There's no excuse for bland Indian food!

text: Good bar prices at happy hour. 3 to 6 pm mon to fri.

name: Harrison Lewis
text: I ordered chicken tikka Korma to go. What I was given was masala very bland tomato paste with 3 small pieces of chicken. I paid 30 bucks for soggy naan and tomato soup that taste better out of a can. I called to have this corrected and they argued with me over the phone about what I was given. This is not how you treat a customer. I will not come here again and will stop recommending this to everyone. All you had to do was correct to issue, cook served the wrong food. I hope this closes and a real bussines is opened here. This place is never open in the first place. Dishonor on your company.

name: Reni N
text: Great to go with a Groupon. I thought it was a bit expensive for the quality by 2 dollars. I thought the nann bread was good and crispy at the bottom. I would go again with a Groupon

text: So far this is the best Indian food in Denver that I have had. My favorites are chicken tikka masala and the saag paneer. Generally, I order take out for dinner. The few times I have dined at the restaurant was good as well.

text: Great environment with luxurious seating. Three beers on tap in addition to standard bottled Indian lagers.  Try the chicken tika and the biryani and pair them with the fruit and nut naan

text: Good service, but the naan was burnt, the vindaloo had aluminum foil, and my first beer was flat.  The server tried her best, but she didn't have much to work with.

I felt the portions were small for the price and the food was under seasoned and not even a little spicy (I know you can't please everyone here). I should probably give 3 stars but I'm bitter I spent a lot of money for ok Indian food. I thought the staff was very friendly and hard-working.

name: Linnet Agnes Jose
text: I am an Indian and the dishes I had at Bombay Clay Over is far from being authentic. Me and my friends ordered Masala dosa, Combo biriyani (chicken and shrimp), tandoori chicken and chicken tikka masala. We had first asked how many dosas would come in the order and we were told 2, and it turned out that one dosa was just cut into 2. Biriyani was not good. Overall quantity of all dishes were very less compared to their price and what is available other restaurants at least in Fort Collins (to be fair). I would say tandoori chicken and chicken tikka masala was comparatively alright. But, they ended up not delivering the naan that was ordered and I was not happy with the general service either, especially that of a man who seemed like the manager.

resp.text:
I'm so sorry to hear that this was your impression of us, Linnet! We pride ourselves on serving up authentic, flavorful Indian cuisine, so I'm disappointed that you didn't find it to be that. I'd love to chat with you in more detail about what just wasn't hitting the spot, so please feel free to reach out to me directly -- we'd welcome the opportunity to make a better impression!
Cheers,
Marshall, Owner

I was surprised to even see that there was still a Quiznos actually left thats still in business, but I am happy to know that's the case!

name: Grant Hilti

text: I get the chipotle turkey sandwich and it always hits the spot.  There is never a line here!  They have chili and soup every day.  All of their sandwiches are hot, which I really appreciate.

name: Andrew Daleigh
text: Love the food, that's why I worked for a franchise for 7 years.

Andrew,
Thank you for your visit and generous Star Rating for our Quiznos in Thornton CO!

name: Jessica Olivas
text: Walked in and the guy behind the counter was taking care of a guest cashed her out and kept gloves on. I had to ask yoong to wash his hands and glove up to handle my order. The lobby area was a mess but he was alone so we overlooked it and decided to dine in. When yoong rang us up he was overcharging us I asked what the extra charges were for and he had a hard time explaining we then told him to take off the drinks and chips and do not make our orders a meal if you are going to tack on extra charges for a meal. Yoongs ability to handle a restaurant need to be improved especially with cleanliness. I hope corporate sees this and advises the franchise owner. Oh and I forgot he grabbed a dirty rag with the gloves on and then wanted to garnish my sandwich so I had to tell yoong who I just found out is the franchise owner to wash his hands AGAIN and glove back up. SMH

resp.text:
Jessica,
My apologies.  I will visit Yoong and review your comments.  Again my apologies.

name: Stephen Petrock
text: Tried making an order online with the app. The app stated that the restaurant was 1.2 miles away, which it was on the other side of town. I placed the order  and the default tip was 25%!!! I changed the tip to 0 since there was no option for 0. What a scam. I  called the store which I placed my order and the employee was not able to cancel my order from the app. Out of $32.09! When I placed an order to the  correct store, they we're  ignoring me and we're somewhat rude! Not to mention, The employee had her 5 year old standing on the counter, prepping food. Food was amazing though.

name: John Brosz
text: Great sandwiches however at the price it would be better to just buy from Subway.

resp.text:
John,
Thank you for your visit and generous Star Rating.  Yes our prices on average are higher than Subway and this is due in great part to the ingredient we use to make our subs.  We do offer a daily $5 Sub to try and help those looking for a greater value.
Thank you again,
Mike Evans
FBC Quiznos

name: happy mirth
text: While the sandwiches can be made vegan, the concept was utterly incomprehensible to the staff of this store.  When asked if the vegetables were cooked in butter, they said "I don't know."  When asked if they had any way to find out they simply replied "no."  Your staff should know what is in your food.  Period.

The people there are really friendly as well.

name: Alexander Woodcock
text:
Tasty Ethiopian food... We enjoyed a couple of veggie sambusas and meat combo platter for two. Generous portions, reasonably priced, and friendly service.

The chicken is always our favourite, the beef was nice and spicy, but found the lamb a little chewy, with plenty of Injera for eating everything with.

The food takes a while (30+ mins) to come once ordered, but this is consistent with other Ethiopian restraunts and good food is worth the wait!

I highly recommend it!

text: Great food and service at very reasonable prices. I usually get the vegetarian combo and it's always been delicious. Highly recommend.

name: brittini reitz
text: This was our 1st Ethiopian food experience and it was excellent. We got the meat combination and the vegetable combination which gives you a bit of everything.  Served with injera (flat bread) you eat with your hands and scoop up the food served family style with the bread. Very flavorful but not spicy. We also got the coffee ceremony at the end.  Staff and patrons where very friendly. We will come back for your next Ethiopian fix.

name: Bob Yu
text: My favorite Ethiopian restaurant. Their injera bread is easily the best in Colorado. I highly recommend the vegetarian platter.  Even as a massive carnivore, I found this option to be the most delicious. There's plenty of lentils in this option, so that you aren't starving for protein. The Kitfo is also very good. I recommend eating it raw, as that's what has the most flavor, but it might be too much for some people.

text: charging to match I order Paterno with pineapple they charge me for pineapple.and I asked for side spinach they don't have.

name: Lisseth Makhael
text:
Terrible experience unfortunately.
I called at 720pm to ask if there was a wait as we were a party of 5 and if they had gluten free theft. They told me no wait and yes to the theft. We were there at 740pm. Apparently a party of 2 adults and 3 kids had just walked in and prior to them a couple.
We waited a few minutes as another table was just leaving which left the space for us.
The waitress told us to sit with the table all dirty. I told my party to wait until the table was cleaned. When she came back again and told us to sit I ask for the table to be cleaned before we were seated, she grab couple of napkins and proceeded to wipe the table, no sanitizer was used to clean the table.
We sat as she had no intention to sanitize the tabl
She took a while to get to as and when we order I almost didn't order appetizers but she insisted. I asked how many pieces came in the app plate she said 5. So I said yes, bring that.
Someone in my party pointed out later on that it had been 40min so I called on her and ask about the appetizer. Then she brought One piece just apparently deep fried. Super hot, very spicy but only one.
My party ate it because they were starving. When I asked about the other 4 pieces she said it was only one and she could order for more I asked just to bring the regular food.
While they ate I approached the server and asked if it was take longer because my party was starving,she said it would be ready soon, they had another big party (the other 5) which made them busy.
This was not communicated at any moment when we got there that because of one table of 5 we would be delayed one hour.
Another 10min went by and some in my party where literally about to faint. So we decided to leave 1hr and 10min after we arrived with pretty much our bellies empty.
I was pretty upset as we chose to go there as opposed to go to The Post where the wait was 45min but I knew at least we had to wait.
Here we waited without knowing we would be waiting for soooo long and still left without food.
We went to the other restaurant and it had been free for a while. We could have eaten way earlier if it weren't because we pretty much got held up waiting forever in this cafe.
So, no. I would not recommend this place to anyone.
I never wait more tha  35min for food unless I am inform and I choose to wait for the food.
I don't know what would take them so long, maybe they make it everything from scratch, which would make sense for the delay but not for a restaurant as you expect no more than 20min wait.
Whatever their reason was I would not know cuz nobody ever came to talk to us even though the owner was sitting at the back.
I was hosting for people out of the country and this was a very embarrassing experience.

text: Good food but bring a jacket, cold af!

Another, I was in there with minimal people waiting for an order and they refused to acknowledge my prescience and just went along making everyone else's drinks while I was patiently waiting rather than being proactive and asking why I might be standing there.  Also, the bathrooms are DISGUSTING.  I'm typically a very patient and understanding person as I also am in the service industry.  This place is terrible and I'm sure it trickles down from management so I don't know that I'd blame the main staff so quickly as I would the management that allows that behavior and their store to run that way.

text: First time visiting this place and I will be back, always support local small businesses especially now during these times. The location was decent! Staff was superb! Thank you!

resp.text: Thank you so much, Amy! - Talia

name: Ariel H Curran
text:
Had a nice little evening here while on a date.  Though it is small, it is VERY nice, new and clean. I wasn't a huge fan of the location but you would never guess this nice little cidery would be inside the walls of the industrial building.
There wasn't a single cider we didn't like.
The people here also were very personable. Definitely recommend and will go again.

resp.text: Thank you so much for stopping in! The location is a bit different but we hope the warm environment and tasty cider makes up for it! :)

name: Shazlynn Bonich
text: My husband and I absolutely love your cider! I've never had anything like it and will be ordering more from you in the future.

resp.text: Thank you so much for stopping in, Shazlynn! We appreciate your visit and your kind words!

name: Andy Giesen
text: We're very lucky to have some outstanding cider producers in these parts, but these guys are on another level. It's just pressed apples, no additional anything, fermented and highly carbed, leaving well-balanced ciders finishing with layers of flavor notes. Very much worth every effort to get here or to find bottles out in the wild - I really can't say enough good about them.

resp.text: Thank you so much, Andy! We are glad you found us.

name: Erik J.
text:
The best cider you will ever have! We got hooked after purchasing a bottle from a neighborhood liquor store (Pearl St. Wine) here in Denver.

Haykin does an amazing job at showcasing what makes cider amazing - the apple itself! Instead of taking a basic cider and adding flavors (barrel aging, hops, other fruit
juices,  etc.. ), each Haykin cider is unique because of the individual apple that they choose for each bottle.

If you like ciders, then you will LOVE all the Haykin ciders!

resp.text:
We are so glad you found us, Erik! Pearl Wine is an amazing supporter of ours and we are so thankful they stock us! <3
- Talia Haykin

name: Luke Glenn
text: Hands down this globally recognized, award winning cider is the best cider you can get your hands on. Cool ownership, awesome ambience and we are fortunate to have this place right in our backyard. Highly recommend stopping in here!

resp.text: Thank you Luke! You are so great. We are lucky to have 'neighbors' like you! - Talia

resp.text: Thanks for coming by, Lance! We really appreciate it. Stop back in and see us again!

text: Went for the first time today since I was in the area. Limited menu, which isn't always a bad thing. Honestly when I see a limited menu I expect them to excel at whatever the items are. I bought the flautas and the smothered burrito. The burrito is not advertised as spicy, but it packs a punch. So much so that for most people it would probably be inedible. Got through half before I have up, leaves a lot to be desired. The flautas: texturally, they're amazing! Nice crunch to them. Unfortunately they chicken was not well seasoned, requiring you to use the salsa they include. Not terrible but still I'd like a little salt. I ordered the extra side of rice and beans with the flautas. Again, lackluster in seasoning, good value as far as price goes. Overall, too many small issues for this to be a go-to spot of mine. Probably won't be back as there are better options in the area.

name: kennethconnection
text: This rating is based on the beer only. The staff was super friendly and certainly aimed to please. I was not a fan of the beer however. The 8in double IPA was the only beer that was serviceable. A citrus hop profile with lemon and orange but lacking in body. This beer would be much better with a lower ABV and sold as a session IPA. The pumpkin ESB and Golden ale were way, way to sweet with excess sugars, these beers both tasted incredibly green, like they didn't have enough time fermenting. The Amber Ale was the worst of all, tasting like someone's first attempt at home brewing from a generic beginners kit. It had no body, no malt flavors, water down, with a seperated taste of alcohol and water, with no hop profile to speak of. I'm sorry for the harsh criticism but There are just too many breweries in Denver to spend the time and money on something sub par. Please improve your beers.
